{["internalId"]="5796",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Greenshade.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6267",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cyrodilic Collections needs someone to rescue some well preserved relics from the Blackguards occupying the Teeth of Sithis.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3277",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The wizard Gabrielle Benele asked me to help her recharge the Midnight Talisman. It could be a powerful weapon in the battle against Angof the Gravesinger.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3338",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Sir Lanis and the Knights of the Dragon are ready to march into Cath Bedraud to deal with Angof, but the mist rising from Angof's vines creates a hazard they can't overcome.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3357",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The final battle against Angof begins now. I need to get inside and navigate the labyrinth of catacombs to find a safe place for Gabrielle and the soldiers to teleport into.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3379",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Darien discovered that we need three shard-keys to open the three locks that protect Angof's inner sanctum.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3412",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A Lion Guard patrol on its way from Daggerfall to Wayrest was attacked by Daedric Cultists who referred to themselves as 'Supernal Dreamers'. The cultists kidnapped the guard captain.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5643",["level"]="16",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Some law-abiding citizens have been meddling in the affairs of the Thieves Guild. The guild wants its pickpockets to teach the meddlers to mind their own business. I should look for ornaments, writings, or other oddities, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5645",["level"]="17",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rumors are floating around that the Thieves Guild isn't a threat anymore. The Thieves Guild wants to quash the rumors with a series of conspicuous thefts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5647",["level"]="17",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rumors are floating around that the Thieves Guild isn't a threat anymore. The Thieves Guild wants to quash the rumors with a series of conspicuous thefts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4176",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="There's a coven of Hagravens in Northwind Mine. They need to die.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4253",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Nord named Eirfa at Geirmund's Hall. She asked if I'd be interested in participating in a drinking contest. Let's see how this goes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4869",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6251",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="A scholar by the name of Tharayya is searching for an elusive artifact hidden somewhere within the ruins of Garlas Malatar. She's enlisted me to help her deal with the hazards of the lost Ayleid city and recover her quarry.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4072",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rock Bone Goblins have made camp to the northeast of Vlastarus.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4081",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jurana asked me to gather some silver scales for the local artist to use in her next project.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3880",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Ordinators are outnumbered. They asked me to reduce Vox's forces to help even things up a bit.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3838",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Priest Dilyne asked me to close the Daedric portals that Vox opened within the shrine. All kinds of vile creatures are emerging from these blasphemous wounds in the world.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3818",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Shrine of Saint Veloth has been desecrated by Magistrix Vox. This Daedric attack has left the spirit of Veloth in a weakened state.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6252",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Depths of Malatar.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5244",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to delve the Banished Cells beneath Auridon.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5309",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Vaults of Madness, a dark labyrinth at the heart of Coldharbour.",["poiIndex"]="39",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6250",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Frostvault.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode.",["poiIndex"]="60",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5381",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore beyond the portal in Veteran City of Ash in Greenshade.",["poiIndex"]="58",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5520",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Before he died, I met an Orc named Nashruth. He belonged to a holy order that lights Malacath's pyre once every decade, but was ambushed before he could do so. I swore to head to the heart of Old Orsinium and light Malacath's pyre.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5881",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="According to a Khajiiti farmer named Halinjirr, a flock of bandits claimed the cavern of Zainsipilu and seized his stock of valuable crops.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5102",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="I've discovered the Aetherian Archive, an enigmatic tower that had previously been sealed. Mighty Mordra and her Undaunted had planned to climb the Archive, but her allies are missing. If I choose to, I could explore it and reach the top before them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5087",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="People venturing into Hel Ra Citadel have mysteriously vanished, including a group of Undaunted led by Kailstig the Axe. I should enter the Citadel to find out what happened to them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6454",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jorunn the Skald-King requested I meet with his agent to look into a plot that threatens not only Skyrim, but potentially all of Tamriel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6463",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lyris Titanborn and I uncovered a conspiracy involving the witches of the Icereach Coven. The trail leads to an isolated inn somewhere in the wilds of Eastmarch. We need to determine what the coven has planned before it's too late.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4812",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I was lead to an old instrument in the ruins of Thibaut's Cairn by a spectral woman. The recoder was engraved with \"Valencia Nasica, the Exalted Bard of Dune.\"",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6412",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A band of smugglers have turned the sacred Moonlit Cove into a skooma distillery and poisoned the waters with their shoddy spirits.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6024",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Bursar of Tributes seeks a particular treasure to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6077",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I have accepted a contract to defeat the creature Wraith-of-Crows and other Daedric incursions in Clockwork City's Radius.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6171",["level"]="16",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can show that I know how to make a ring, Felarian will certify me as a jewelery crafter.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5231",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5572",["level"]="17",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I was tipped off about treasures stashed in The Hideaway. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved, so I should act quickly on this lead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5549",["level"]="17",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The merchant lord Cosh claims to have found Magnifica Falorah's dowry, and for his trouble she has agreed to marry him. Zeira suspects Nicolas, the treacherous former guildmaster of the Thieves Guild, is behind it all. She wants him to pay for his betrayal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4088",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Finvir, a Wood Elf down in the Bad Man's tunnels, claims he is one of the mages that originally summoned the Dremora Lord now posing as the Bad Man.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4080",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I entered a secluded grove near Daggerfall Harbor called Bad Man's Hallows. The people here are engaged in a festival honoring the Bad Man, an ancient harvest god.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5545",["level"]="18",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Silver-Claw found out the Iron Wheel is planning to ship Zeira to Taneth. As acting guildmaster, I've called on the Thieves Guild to do something about it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6084",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Divine Prosecution has charged me with clearing out Welenkin Cove and eliminating the threat posed by B'Korgen, the Sea Sload alchemist.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6145",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Esterdel asked me to find Niralin, his missing bride-to-be. He tracked her to Archon's Grove, which has been overrun by werewolves. He's hired me to rescue Niralin, or at least collect proof that she's died.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6157",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Divine Prosecution has tasked me to recover several blossoms of the Rose-Of-Archon flower, needed by Sapiarchs for their religious rites.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5637",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I have been welcomed into the bizarre realm of the Daedric Demiprince Fa-Nuit-Hen. In order to test my mettle and demonstrate my skills, I've agreed to enter the Maelstrom Arena, where deadly challenges created by Fa-Nuit-Hen's Barons await me.",["poiIndex"]="55",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6138",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mehdze the Maestro is on an exploratory journey into King's Haven Pass to research his next epic. Unfortunately, things aren't going according to plan.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5984",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6352",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Lair of Maarselok.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode.",["poiIndex"]="62",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5680",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5663",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5933",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="With the revelation that Veya's brother is dead, Councilor Eris has asked me to keep his daughter away from Balmora and House Redoran while he looks into what happened. In the meantime, Ashur asked me to talk to Veya.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6181",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Loremaster Celarus's apprentice, Josajeh, charged me with sealing more time breaches for the Psijic Orderâ€”this time in the Iliac Bay region.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6185",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A new cluster of time breaches appeared in northeastern Tamrielâ€”specifically the lands of Stonefalls. Eastmarch, and The Rift. As an agent of the Psijic Order, I need to seal them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6197",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An artifact known as the Staff of Towers has returned to Tamriel. Loremaster Celarus urged me to recover four pieces of the staff.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6194",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Loremaster Celarus charged me with sealing more time breaches for the Psijic Orderâ€”this time in the Wood Elf homeland of Valenwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6190",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="My allies in the Psijic Order discovered another cluster of time breaches in the northernmost regions of Black Marsh. I need to seal them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6198",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Loremaster Celarus and the Psijic scryers have finally discovered the four remaining pieces of the Staff of Towers. I must travel to remote locations to find and recover these artifacts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6195",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Even with all eight fragments of the Staff of Towers collected, time breaches continue to open all across Tamriel. I must seal a new cluster of these rifts in the land of Rivenspire.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6196",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Loremaster Celarus feels confident that the threat posed by the Staff of Towers is nearly dealt with. Unfortunately, there is one final cluster of time breaches in the land of Craglorn. I need to seal them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6199",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Loremaster Celarus's apprentice, Josajeh, stole the eight fragments of the Staff of Towers and fled to Tamriel. She no doubt plans to reforge the staff and use it to alter time. The results could be catastrophic. I must stop her before it's too late.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5888",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Archcanon Tarvus agrees that Chodala is somehow involved in Lord Vivec's loss of power. He wants me to confirm his involvement and find a way to get his staff without starting a war with the Ashlanders.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6234",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe, which he calls the Naga-Kur, wants me to go to the Echoing Hollow and accomplish the task he set before me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5738",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolgrul, one of the Undaunted, gave me a challenge to complete in Wormroot Depths, located in Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6235",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe, called the Naga-Kur in the Argonian tongue, wants me to go to the Echoing Hollow and accomplish the task he set before me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5734",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolgrul, one of the Undaunted, gave me a challenge to complete in Shael Ruins, located in Malabal Tor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6359",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Euraxia's troops have descended upon Desert Wind Caverns, scouring the ruins for ancient scrolls. Nisuzi, the Baandari job broker, wants me to claim these texts before the Imperials.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5276",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ancient complex beneath Elden Root, the Elden Hollow, in the center of Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5305",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the island of Blackheart Haven in Iliac Bay.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4494",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered the body of a Dark Elf in a cave. There's a note next to the body.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5312",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath wants to introduce me to the Undaunted pledge.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5863",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A group of ghost hunters hired me to protect them on their current job. They've been contracted to clear out a fortress to the north that's infested with spirits. I need to keep them safe while they do whatever they do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4263",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lliae the Quick asked that I eliminate four flame atronachs issuing from the lava fissure in Chorrol.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2694",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Ash Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5288",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ruins of Arx Corinium, the old Imperial pile sinking into the marsh of Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="39",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6417",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Unhallowed Grave.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode.",["poiIndex"]="65",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5636",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Ruins of Mazzatun.",["poiIndex"]="62",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5246",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to delve the Banished Cells beneath Auridon.",["poiIndex"]="61",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6363",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nisuzi's Baandari caravan suffers a tea shortage, but not just any tea will do as a replacement. Apparently, rare Samar tea shrubs grow in the Tangle, and the pekoe leaves they produce are the finest in Tamriel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6237",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe, which calls itself the Naga-Kur, wants me to go to Bok-Xul and accomplish the task he set before me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5952",["level"]="50",["type"]="13",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Battlemaster Rivyn has challenged me to win three Battleground matches.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6107",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Bursar of Tribute demands compensation for the Blackfeather Court from mortals who refuse to allow them to play with their games and toys.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6451",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5431",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane has challenged me to explore the White-Gold Tower in the Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="105",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5274",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the kwama mine called Darkshade Caverns, which lies beneath Deshaan.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5283",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ruined halls of the Crypt of Hearts. It lies beneath the stones of Rivenspire, a former school for might and magic.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6379",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An ancient dro-m'Athra called Zalsheem lurks in the ruins of a Hidden Moon shrine south of Predator Mesa. Her corrupting influence will surely spread if I don't act quickly.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5352",["level"]="50",["type"]="6",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="The Khajiit's ancient enemy, the dro-m'Athra, have emerged from the Dark Behind the World and claimed the Temple of Seven Riddles for the Ghost Moon, Lorkhaj.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5780",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Cradle of Shadows.",["poiIndex"]="61",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5303",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Dwemer tunnels of Volenfell, deep beneath the stones of Bangkorai.",["poiIndex"]="42",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5043",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A soldier at Fort Virak told me the Pact military is focusing their efforts at the land coral maze known as Vivec's Antlers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5044",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A Pact officer at Vivec's Antlers suggested I assist the generals at Ash Mountain.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5042",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I met a soldier at Ash Mountain who said the defense of Davon's Watch could use some help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6297",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Before we killed the Usurper Queen, Euraxia issued a final order. We need to ascertain what she ordered her soldiers to do and see how it connects to the plans of the Dragons and the necromancers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5260",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the cavern called Spindleclutch beneath Glenumbra.",["poiIndex"]="42",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5382",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane has challenged me to explore the Imperial City Prison in the Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="104",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4336",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="A tribe of Wood Orcs is protecting Canonreeve Oraneth in Elden Hollow I . Bakkhara, a member of the Mages Guild, wants to stop them, but can't attack the Orcs directly due to their association with Canonreeve Oraneth, who is a member of the Thalmor.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5120",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Fingaenion attempted to enter an Oblivion Gate with a group of Undaunted to save his wife, Gilraen. He failed. I'm to help him get her backâ€”if she still lives.",["poiIndex"]="58",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4846",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I have found the notes of a mage named Mercano from Woodhearth in the depths of an Ayleid ruin where the Veiled Heritants were raising undead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4779",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="It appears a hunting band was overcome by a powerful wispmother, as their frozen forms are scattered about the mire.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4737",["level"]="37",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the journal of Graccus, an Imperial who destroyed a Bosmer village to find a treasure buried below.",["poiIndex"]="23",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6154",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Scalecaller Peak.",["poiIndex"]="66",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6317",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mazdurr the Moonstruck, a Khajiit dedicated to the Daedric Prince Azurah, is trapped by bandits in the caverns of the Tangle. I agreed to help him escape.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4246",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Wayrest authorities were investigating reports of heavily-armed ruffians in the city sewers when they were betrayed by one of their own, a necromancer named Garron.",["poiIndex"]="20",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4583",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a diary on a dead man in Icehammer's Vault. It described how the man and his family took refuge from a storm in Icehammer's Vault. They were eventually killed by the draugr that roam the burial chambers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5789",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Deshaan.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5823",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5745",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolgrul, one of the Undaunted, gave me a challenge to complete in Aldunz, located in Alik'r Desert.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5719",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I received a contract from the Speaker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5573",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I was tipped off about treasures stashed in Underground Sepulcher. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved, so I should act quickly on this lead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5687",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5275",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath has challenged me to explore the kwama mines of Darkshade Caverns beneath Deshaan.",["poiIndex"]="60",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5301",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Tempest Island, a storm-tossed outcropping off the coast of Malabal Tor.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5829",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6428",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dirge Truptor said the New Moon are scheming with a necromancer in the Bone Orchard of Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5724",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I received a contract from the Speaker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5577",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I was tipped off about treasures stashed in the Secluded Sewers. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved, so I should act quickly on this lead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6427",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a crafting writ related to the Witches Festival.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6439",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a crafting writ related to the Witches Festival.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6236",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe, which calls itself the Naga-Kur, wants me to go to Bok-Xul and accomplish the task he set before me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6450",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4733",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Mages Guild has launched an expedition into Selene's Web to seek out and study an ancient forest spirit rumored to live here.",["poiIndex"]="29",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6071",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Bursar of Tributes seeks items of flesh to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6429",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dirge Truptor informed me that an Akaviri solder was interred in a crypt in Deshaan. He's asked me to search it for secrets of the Dragonguard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2873",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Brindle Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6155",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Fang Lair.",["poiIndex"]="64",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6433",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dirge Truptor asked me to remove an Order of the New Moon recruiter operating in Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6149",["level"]="20",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Altmer woman approached me with questions about her father, Curtaros. His angler fleet is long overdue from their voyage to Wasten Coraldale and she's concerned for his safety. I have agreed to locate her father for her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4961",["level"]="20",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="A strange woman met me at the gates to the city. She may be a werewolf. She told me I am on my way to becoming one as well.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6430",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dirge Truptor told me to recover some old Dragonguard scrolls secreted away beneath the Reliquary of Stars.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6159",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Justiciar Tanorian of the Divine Prosecution requested assistance in curbing a growing reef viper population threatening Summerset's mainland.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6514",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a recruitment letter offering membership in a scholarly society called the Antiquarian Circle. Joining this fellowship could lead to some exciting discoveries.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6515",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I joined the Antiquarian Circle. Now I need to learn how to find and recover rare antiquities.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6492",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a notice seeking brave and able-bodied adventurers for work.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6467",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I need to meet with Jorunn the Skald-King's agent in Solitude, the capital city of Western Skyrim's Haafingar Hold. The agent is investigating a potential threat to not only Skyrim, but to all of Tamriel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6504",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="Sea Giants and vampires have invaded the island of Kyne's Aegis. I must rally a group of allies to face this threat from the north.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6533",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the body of a Nord miner, Kelbarn. It looks like he died while prospecting.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6534",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dead Nord woman in the caverns of Blackreach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6535",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found Reeh-La, an Argonian prospector, dead in an out-of-the-way corner of Blackreach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6538",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note in the passages of Blackreach. There was no sign of anyone around.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6536",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dead miner in the passages of Blackreach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6496",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a wounded, former Frostbite Raider named Magreta who asked me to reunite her with her partner, Nelfthea, who is still with their raiding band on the Frozen Coast.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5233",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6513",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Aerolf spent his life hunting the monster he calls the Pale Man which he claims abducted his brother. He asked me to help track down the creature so he can avenge his loss.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6520",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Coterie of Organized Scholars has tasked me with collecting fresh spriggan bark.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6519",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A local scholar made the unpleasant discovery that a terrible creature of legend known as the Shademother is very much real and currently working unholy magic around Morthal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6498",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a strange talking doll. The soul trapped inside insists that the Dragon Cult is responsible for imprisoning her. She seems confident that if I help gather her belongings, she can use them to reclaim her body.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6475",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alwyn Felsdottar has been haunted by visions ever since someone scattered her ancestor's bones and belongings in Midnight Barrow. I promised to help her retrieve his remains to uncover the truth about his past, and allow his spirit to rest again.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6499",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The High Elf Neramo needs to acquire special Dwarven power nodes and a master scepter in order to conduct his experiment. He asked for my help retrieving them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6500",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A priestess of Kyne named Yrsild asked me to investigate the ancient ruins of Labyrinthian in order to find her grandfather, Keldnyr, who has gone missing.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6497",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Kireth Vanos enlisted my aid in helping her and her brother, Raynor, investigate the ancient Dwarven ruin of Nchuthnkarst.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5800",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolgrul, one of the Undaunted, gave me a challenge to complete in Norvulk Ruins, located in Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6305",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="We recovered the Dragonhorn, but we have no idea what to do with it. While Abnur Tharn attempts to learn more, Khamira wants me to stop Zumog Phoom from reassembling Cadwell's original bodyâ€”the evil Cadwell the Betrayer.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5894",["level"]="50",["type"]="6",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="Strange contraptions have emerged from a rift in the caverns beneath Tel Fyr and killed most of the Telvanni who were growing the tower. The renowned mage Divayth Fyr has asked me to accompany him in investigating this threat.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6512",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Swordthane Jylta charged me with finding allies to assault the harrowstorms forming around Western Skyrim.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6482",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Leiborn intends to host a salskapâ€”a bard's gathering to celebrate the recovery of the Bards College instruments. It's sure to be quite a show.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5491",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Legate Gallus has a strange plan to spy on the Worm Cult, but he needs help to see it through.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6510",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A prideful historian named Narsis Dren found himself trapped in an illusion while researching an ancient mage. Assisting him in his investigation may lead to some exciting discoveries.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6172",["level"]="20",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Loremaster Celarus, a prestigious Psijic monk, invited me to join the Psijic Order. My first task involves closing breaches in time on Summerset Isle.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3626",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The lands of the mighty Hrogar are overrun with Goblins and spiders. The Nord has lost many men to the beasts, and he's under siege.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5450",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I received an invitation to go to Wrothgar and present myself to Forge-Mother Alga in the city of Orsinium. It appears that the Orcs of Wrothgar need some sort of assistance.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3581",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Priestess Brela believes the tormented spirits of a Dark Elf army haunt Vivec's Antlers. They died in a great conflict with the Akaviri. She was captured while consecrating their bones.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3584",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Captain Noris came to Vivec's Antlers to defend against an incursion by Alexandra Conele of the Covenant. Alexandra wants to retrieve an artifact known as the Coral Heart from Vivec's Antlers. The Pact is barely holding its ground.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4286",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A group of researchers were ambushed by the Worm Cult at Pinepeak Caverns.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5476",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The House of Orsimer Glories, a museum in the rebuilt city of Orsinium, seeks to fill its displays with relics and other items of historic importance to both the Orcs and the land of Wrothgar.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6528",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Swordthane Jylta charged me with finding allies to assault the harrowstorms forming around Western Skyrim.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6461",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A sickness is spreading through Dark Moon Grotto that is causing werewolves to act violent and feral. They were close to a cure, but the alchemist working on it, Alchemist Rasir, disappeared. I should investigate to see if the cure can be found.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6476",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Icereach Coven and its allies can call down devastating and unnatural harrowstorms on Western Skyrim. Fennorian thinks these storms can turn people into harrowfiends and mindless harrowed. We need to inform Solitude.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6462",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="With the high queen's murderer brought to justice and a clear connection established between the assassin and the Icereach Coven, Svana thinks we have enough evidence to convince High King Svargrim that the threat to his kingdom is real.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6466",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The high king has finally taken steps, but it isn't enough. Svana thinks we need to develop a defense against the harrowstorms. To that end, she wants to recruit the vampire scholar, Fennorian, to aid us.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6456",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="High King Svargrim refuses to act, so Svana has decided to take matters into her own hands. With Fennorian's help, she plans to develop a strategy for fighting back against the Gray Host.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6464",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="High King Svargrim revealed his alliance with the Gray Host and their plans to unleash a harrowstorm over Solitude. I need to help Svana find a way to stop him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6481",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Solitude has survived High King Svargrim's harrowstorm, but the damage done by his betrayal remains. Can Princess Svana pick up the pieces and carry on for the kingdom?",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5171",["level"]="50",["type"]="6",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="Turuk Redclaws told me of the dangers of the Serpent. How it wants to destroy the cities of Tamriel, and see the forest overtake the land.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6516",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a scholar named Yvara Plouff near a broken down cart. She asked me to help her research some nearby Dragon mounds.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6474",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a wounded High Elf named Rafilerrion who requested my assistance stopping a Reachmen's ritual in the Shadowgreen that could cause the eruption of the mountain above it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6465",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A strange storm has devastated the area around Kilkreath Temple. Now the priests of the temple want my help to find the priests and pilgrims that were lost in the storm.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6523",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Coterie of Organized Scholars wants me to test a Dissonance Apparatus on Dwarven constructs in the Scraps. They would also like me to recover a Dwarven heartcog.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6460",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Silver Cormorant was hit by a strange ice storm that seemed to come out of nowhere. The ship is locked in ice and unable to move. I offered to help the crew.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6524",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Coterie of Organized Scholars tasked me to destroy several umbric urns in Midnight Barrow.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6509",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Swords of Solitude asked me to kill a Sea Giant on Western Skyrim's northern shore, and recover information gathered by scouts who fell victim to the brute.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6349",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Chevalier Renald enlisted my aid in stopping his comrade, Grundwulf, from consuming the blood of a Dragon that he's trapped inside a ruined Khajiiti temple with the help of the Hollowfang vampire clan.",["poiIndex"]="48",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5949",["level"]="50",["type"]="13",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a pamphlet describing the Battlegrounds, a place where contests of strategy and skill are held daily.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6350",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Moongrave Fane.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode.",["poiIndex"]="48",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4147",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I met a Dunmer fleeing a Worm Cult attack at Taarengrav. He told me the Worm Cult attacked a nearby dig site, hoping to unlock an ancient puzzle.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4185",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Valdur spoke of a dark gathering at Honrich Tower.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4139",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Ebonheart Pact has come together under King Jorunn's command to battle the Worm Cult at the ruins of Honrich Tower.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6537",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a strange note. The author promises a reward if I return it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5733",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolgrul, one of the Undaunted, gave me a challenge to complete in the Crypt of the Exiles, located in Bangkorai.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6471",["level"]="45",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Miners working in Blackreach have gone missing. Some of the miners believe spirits are to blame, and ghost hunters were hired to investigate. I should look into these disappearances.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6473",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Supplies for the Dragon Bridge Garrison keep mysteriously disappearing, which puts a strain on their operations. I should investigate and see what I can find out.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6484",["level"]="21",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An accident at the Mor Khazgur Stronghold trapped many Orc workers inside the mine. Unfortunately, a conflict between the clan's chief and the mine's overseer have only added to the crisis.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4379",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Alanwe lives a tortured existence in the Crypt of Hearts. Her soul has been shattered, and the pieces strewn throughout the Crypt. I have promised to help her.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6130",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I learned of a free inn room being offered to a tenant of good reputation. I should seek out the broker in order to ask for more information about this amazing deal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4337",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Khajiiti merchant calling himself Jurak-dar claims to have found a way inside Belarata, a long-sealed Ayleid ruin.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6501",["level"]="21",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rigurt the Brash is in Western Skyrim on behalf of the Skald-King. He needs my help to complete his mission.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6315",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The moons have begun to align. When the eclipse occurs, the Moon Gate of Anequina will open and grant access to Jode's Core. We need to try to prevent the Dragons from accessing the portal and attaining the power stored there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6328",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Despite our victories and the events on the Plane of Jode, Khamira is not yet officially the queen. Before Khamira can receive the crown of Anequina, she needs to receive the blessing of the Mane.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6494",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Coterie of Organized Scholars has asked me to discover evidence of an undiscovered tribe living in Chillwind Depths.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6517",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Swords of Solitude tasked me with dealing with a pack of werewolves preying on a local goatherd's stock.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5448",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I have been welcomed into the bizarre realm of the Daedric Demiprince Fa-Nuit-Hen. In order to test my mettle and demonstrate my skills, I've agreed to enter the Maelstrom Arena, where deadly challenges created by Fa-Nuit-Hen's Barons await me.",["poiIndex"]="55",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2495",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Count Hosni at-Tura wants his father's signet ring, and he's tasked me with getting it. If I can retrieve the ring, he says I can name my reward. The Dream Shard, perhaps?",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2496",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lady Sirali at-Tura believes that Lady Adima is controlling her son, Hosni. If she can get proof that Adima is behind his actions, then she'll have the evidence she needs to prove her son's innocence.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2497",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lady Sirali at-Tura believes Adima controls Hosni through his dreams. She thinks I can save her son, Hosni, by entering his dreams as well.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1633",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Now that I've retrieved the Dream Shard, I can finally return it to the Spirit Wardens at Pariah Abbey.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1485",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Adiel Charnis is distraught. Dreugh attacked her home in the Dreughside district, and her husband fought back. They wounded him and dragged him off toward their spawning pools. Adiel holds out hope her husband still lives.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1527",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Arcady Charnis believes someone ordered men to plant dreugh eggs in the Dreughside neigborhood to cause the dreugh to attack.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2068",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dreugh are mysteriously attacking the Dreughside district. Sergeant Stegine is organizing a defense. I should lend my aid.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5739",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bolgrul, one of the Undaunted, gave me a challenge to complete in Ilessan Tower, located in Glenumbra.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6480",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A High Elf woman named Telline is worried about her husband, Viggol. He wants to go on one last adventure that involves hunting rumored creatures in the mine.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6188",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Ashlander Hanu has recruited me to join her hunting team within Hircine's Hunting Grounds. We must hunt down an indrik and present its heart to Hircine in order for Hanu to win a boon from the Daedric Prince and save her father.",["poiIndex"]="61",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6491",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hedrynne, sister of Hamvir, has been poisoned by the bite of a giant insect near the cave known as Chillwind Depths. I should see if I can help save her life.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5306",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to survive the Blessed Crucible, an unforgiving arena deep in The Rift.",["poiIndex"]="42",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5278",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the complex of sewers beneath Wayrest, dead center in the region called Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="20",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6459",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Attacks by unnatural forces plague the area around Morthal. Villagers report undead wolf attacks and visions of ghosts. I should find the source of these attacks and stop them.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6468",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A harrowstorm destroyed the town of Karthwatch and left it overrun with monsters. I agreed to help with the efforts to rescue any survivors.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6472",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Gwendis of House Ravenwatch recruited me to help free captives trapped inside Greymoor Keep by Lady Essenia, a cruel vampiric sovereign. Gwendis's friend, Adusa-daro, is among those prisoners.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6526",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Swords of Solitude tasked me with hunting down vampires who are dragging their victims underground to feast on them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6493",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tinzen, of the Coterie of Organized Scholars, asked me to help him complete an alchemical tonic that will imbue those who drink it with the strength of Giants.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6527",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An explorer reported the discovery of a gigantic Dwarven colossus that appears to be building upon itself using scrap it finds. They believe that this construct will pose an even greater threat if left unchecked.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5830",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5248",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to brave Fungal Grotto in the caverns beneath Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="66",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5284",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the ruins and hallways of Veteran Crypt of Hearts, beneath Rivenspire.",["poiIndex"]="58",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4303",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Spider Cult has come to Fungal Grotto. Members of the Fighters Guild, led by Defender Two-Blades, are determined to stop the Cult from raising an army of shadows that will destabilize the region.",["poiIndex"]="66",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3819",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Acolyte Eldri collected Dremora hearts for Healer Dalen. He can turn the hearts into healing potions and wanted them to help the troops at Eidolon's Hollow. Unfortunately, Dalen departed before Eldri could give him the hearts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5080",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An aging Bosmer named Hartmin brought his dying husband to a grove near Greenheart where they share memories from their youth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6023",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A junior member of the Mages Guild named Skaldir insists that he and his associates have made a significant magical discoveryâ€”one that could prove disastrous if left uninvestigated.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4827",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ledronor, a member of a hunting order called the Hounds, asked for my help in hunting a troll.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4770",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found an odd, glowing handaxe in a pack at the bottom of Gurzag's Mine. A note of sale indicated a Bosmer named Forthor sold it to the Orcs. He's part of the Marbruk Mages Guild.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4849",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dead adventurer in Barrow Trench. They entered the mine to collect rare ingredients for an alchemist in Woodhearth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4793",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Khajiit called Cold-Eyes who is looking to collect a debt. He'll give me a cut if I help him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5935",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An oracle of Azura named Rhea Opacarius needs my help. Some malevolent force conspires to destroy her order and, perhaps, all of Tamriel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4462",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult has invaded the ruins of Rulanyil's Fall, intent on raising an Ayleid warlord from the dead. Endarwe wants to ensure the body is not disturbed.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4463",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Merethic Society hid several of its most valuable treasures throughout the ruins of Runanyil's Fall.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4784",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sorderion has charged me with apprehending Aldolin, a traitor to the Dominion who has been giving aid to the Ebonheart Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4788",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A small group of Wood Elves entered the Falinesti Spring Site, which has been taken over by Wood Orcs. When they petitioned the Wood Orcs to leave, they were taken prisoner. Egannor managed to escape, but his friends are still in the camp.",["poiIndex"]="46",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4785",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Haras, the hunter, has asked me to hunt the rare pale senche. I must follow the tracks to find the pale senche.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4636",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I need to halt the Daedric invasion from Moonhenge.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4302",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult is raising dead giants to fight Pact soldiers.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6217",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a bonus for any Covenant soldier who slays 40 enemy combatants.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6455",["level"]="1",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I awoke in a cold stone cell after my caravan was attacked on the way into Western Skyrim. I have no clue where I am, but I need to find a way out of here.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6112",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Ritemaster Iachesis of the Psijic Order plans to use an augury ritual to reveal the secrets of the strange pearl we recovered from the Monastery of Serene Harmony.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6132",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Ritemaster Iachesis of the Psijic Order hopes to learn more from the abyssal pearl. Specifically, he wants to determine where K'Tora and the Sea Sload cabal are hiding. I agreed to help in any way I can.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5259",["level"]="7",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Master crafters are offering free training and certification in their professions. Crafting certification will allow me to fulfill crafting writs.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5289",["level"]="7",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can prove I know my way around a cooking fire, Danel Telleno will certify me as a provisioner.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5314",["level"]="7",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can prove I know my way around an enchanting table, Danel Telleno will certify me as an enchanter.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5315",["level"]="7",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can prove I know my way around an alchemy table, Danel Telleno will certify me as an alchemist.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5302",["level"]="8",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can prove I know my way around a workbench, Millenith will certify me as a woodworker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5249",["level"]="8",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can prove I know my way around a forge, Millenith will certify me as a blacksmith.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5310",["level"]="8",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="If I can prove I know how to use a needle and thread, Millenith will certify me as a clothier.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6012",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Wardens.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6431",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Senchal job broker, Guybert Flaubert, asked me to travel to the Forsaken Citadel and acquire cursed swords.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6421",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A rogue Goutfang monk trains students in forbidden techniques where a rare herb grows. I agreed to help kill the monk, plus gather herbs to help heal Dragon hunters.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4538",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Battlereeve Alduril would like me to assist her in her assault on Tempest Island.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6432",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Senchal job broker, Guybert Flaubert, urged me to place enchanted candle orbs in the halls of the Forsaken Citadel. According to his client, the candles may help the restless dead that dwell in the Citadel find peace.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6518",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="There's a cheater among Mor Khazgur's Circle of Champions and I have been tasked by the Swords of Solitude to deal with the troublesome champion before his actions provoke a civil war among the Orcs.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6495",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tinzen, representing the Coterie of Organized Scholars, has asked me to recover research sampled from Dragonhome.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5828",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5794",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6054",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to defend the besieged city of Falkreath Hold.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6150",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Kinlady Helenaere of Sunhold needs my help to fight back against a Maormer raiding party and rescue her city.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4778",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Whisper Grove has been turned to a City of Ash by the forces of Mehrunes Dagon. If I don't intervene, the remaining Bosmer will be slaughtered.",["poiIndex"]="39",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3996",["level"]="20",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note on a dead bandit. Their leader, a man named Oath-Breaker, has orders to capture villagers, so he can trade them for supplies.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5290",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the City of Ash, a Wood Elf village in Greenshade.",["poiIndex"]="39",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6422",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A rogue Goutfang master and his students waylaid a supply caravan, stealing all the rice. I agreed to deal with the master and return any rice I find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6503",["level"]="50",["type"]="6",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="An unlikely alliance of Sea Giants and vampires invaded Kyne's Aegis. If the survivors are to have any hope of escape, I must drive these monsters back into the sea. Hopefully, the island's defenders will rally behind me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6306",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I helped Abnur Tharn decode the Wrathstone tablet and determine the location of the hidden weapon. Now we need to travel to the Halls of Colossus and find it before his half-sister, Euraxia. Khamira has decided to go with us.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6343",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2016",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Hallin's Stand is under the control of the Seventh Legion, an Imperial military force.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2017",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Yarah needs to discover the identity of whomever betrayed Hallin's Stand and allowed the Seventh Legion to enter the city.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2018",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Ufa the Red Asp and I must work together to locate the traitor identified by Captain Dhakir's men in order to save the grandeya of Hallin's Stand from execution.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4918",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Hallin's Stand is ready to take back their town from the Imperial's Seventh Legion.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6170",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Divine Prosecution seeks able-bodied adventurers to assist with the enforcement of laws by performing contract work throughout Summerset.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6116",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A distraught mother named Lanarie cannot find her son, Arathel. The youth surrendered to the authoritiesâ€”saying he was part of a plot to kill a Sapiarch. But he disappeared from his cell shortly thereafter. I promised Lanarie I would find her son.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5519",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A caravan bringing books to Orsinium has been waylaid by ogres. The books have likely been torn to pieces. If I'm to reassemble them for their rightful owner, these creatures will need to be dealt with.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5222",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6162",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Renzir, a Khajiit merchant, was betrayed by his first mate Madja. He requested that I recover his trade shipments, kill Madja, and find out what happened to his wife, Nubani.",["poiIndex"]="26",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6176",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the corpse of Nafarion, a High Elf who turned into a vampire. His dying wish was for his betrothed to know the truth about what happened to him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5912",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the dangerous cliff strider they call Old Stomper.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5929",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Dushariran and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5915",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Ashlanders of Zainab have been run out of Nchuleft, stopping them from scavenging the ruins for items to trade. The Temple wishes to better their relations with the tribe by gathering tools and parts which were left behind.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5906",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Gold Coast Trading Company ship was lured ashore by a powerful nereid. I've been hired to defeat the nereid and recover the cargo in the wreckage. She's protected by a group of sailors who she controls through a magical song.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="614",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mathias Raiment met me on the road into Wind Keep and asked me to help the countess. She's acting strangely and it's put the entire town on edge.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1383",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Michel Helomaine had a Bosmer wife named Breloth who died recently. He's asked me to help him get things to give her a befitting burial.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6437",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Senchal job broker wants me to harvest the mushrooms found in Moonlit Cove. The fungus' unique flavor is greatly prized by some Khajiiti cooks.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6424",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A scholar made an ill-advised trek to a guarded temple. Now I must destroy the temple guardian and gather the scholar's scattered notes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6447",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nomu and his friends from Murkmire were chased out of the quarry by cultists and now his friends are missing. I promised to try to find them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2240",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The scholar's apprentice Shiri has studied a book from among Alasan's possessions. Shiri suggests I begin my search for the third Ansei Ward in HoonDing's Watch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4472",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Pierre Lanier got locked in a cage just before the Goblin invasion of Cumberland's Watch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1554",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Goblin tribe has invaded Cumberland's Watch. A soldier asked me to help fight them off.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3280",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The city of Evermore is in dire straits. King Eamond is dead and Reachmen are bearing down on the city from the north. Duke Renchant plans to hand the city over to Imperial control, but I have agreed to work with Queen Arzhela to stop him.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4265",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lliae asked me to trigger a Black Dagger ambush north of Chorrol.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4226",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lliae the Quick asked me to travel to Hackdirt and take revenge on the Black Dagger bandits for the deaths of her friends.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4247",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lliae the Quick has asked me to travel to Narsinfel and return Captain Minwe to rest.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4270",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lliae asked me to bring supplies to one of her caches out in Cyrodiil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4568",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hjorik needs his restoration scrolls charged.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4561",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hjorik is running low on supplies to help the many wounded in his care.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4569",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hjorik has received word that more Dremora are entering the city from the north.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3141",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4543",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mezha-dro, a Khajiit servant of Meridia, asked for help sealing tears in Oblivion before more material from Tamriel falls through.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4403",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The slavers have captured the crew of a ship that crashed on the rocks. Captain Albert Marck has asked me to free them.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6189",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Hircine's March of Sacrifices.",["poiIndex"]="61",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5071",["level"]="23",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Magister Curinure asked that I speak with him about the Mages Guild in the Vulkhel Guard guildhall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5073",["level"]="23",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Hall Steward Aicessar asked that I speak with him about the Fighters Guild in the Vulkhel Guard guildhall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4296",["level"]="3",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I died, but that was only the beginning â€¦.\n\nI awoke in Oblivion. My body is intact, but my soul has been torn from my body. I must find a way out of this nightmare place to reclaim what was lost to me, or I will be damned for all eternity.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6207",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture the towns of Vlastarus, Cropsford, and Bruma for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6106",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Bursar of Tribute demands compensation for the Blackfeather Court from mortals who insult them and chase them away.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4257",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Captain Erronfaire is desperate to leave port, but she's lost track of some of her crew. She needs them found so she can set sail for Velyn Harbor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3029",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Imperial invaders ransacked the Temple of Satakalaam, killing the priests, defiling the temple, and stealing the relics. High Priest Zuladr has asked me to reclaim the relics so he can restore the temple.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4731",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bandits roughed up a volunteer near the Saltwalker Militia camp, and it doesn't sound as though the militia came out to help him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4404",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Eryarion and some of his inn workers were meeting a trader to restock supplies when pirates invaded Haven. Everyone scattered, and now his workers are lost in the marsh.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4396",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Haven, the largest port on the Long Coast, has been taken by a powerful band of pirates!",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4405",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Khezuli wants my help to keep her \"side business\" going. She assures me it isn't technically illegal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4896",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Queen Ayrenn has heard rumblings of discontent in Elden Root, the Aldmeri Dominion's capital. She wants me to travel ahead of her and assess the situation.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4833",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've discovered an order of hunters called Brackenleaf's Briars. They protect a tree they say was planted by Y'ffre at the creation of the world.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4946",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mendil is concerned for her friend Firaelion. He recently entered a cave full of deadly spiders and hasn't been seen since.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4445",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A polite spirit named Decius haunts the Cave of Broken Sails. He asked for my help in stopping the necromantic ritual that binds him to this place.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4436",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Brauti Bloodshark led a mutiny against the captain and crew of the Albatross as they searched the Cave of Broken Sails for ancient treasure.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4768",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dominion soldiers erected barricades around a tribe of Argonian refugees living in the Gray Mire. Officer Parwinel needs help resolving the Argonians' situation.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4943",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="All is not well in Elden Root. The Khajiit lack an embassy, which is the cause of tensions in the capital city of the Aldmeri Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="24",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4868",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Southpoint's citizens are killing one another in the streets. Dominion soldiers cordoned off the town, but are in dire need of assistance.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4773",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a talking skull named Dringoth near the Bone Orchard. He wants me to piece him together so he can help thwart Worm Cultists in the area.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4882",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Enda's husband, a minstrel named Sorion, went missing after going on tour through Grahtwood. I agreed to help track him down.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4963",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Redguard forces are massing inside an old Ayleid ruin, and the Dominion believes they've opened up a magical gateway from Alik'r to transport their troops into the heart of Grahtwood unopposed.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4976",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sarandel's Carnival came all the way from the Summerset Isles. Unfortunately, they've suffered numerous setbacks in performing for the Wood Elves of Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4406",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A researcher named Sirdor is trapped in the ruins of Root Sunder.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4339",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A research team from Elden Root has rediscovered the ancient city of Root Sunder. Unfortuanely they've also been mauled by wild animals. Tandare, the last survivor of the research team, needs the journals of her dead comrades.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3995",["level"]="3",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Rolunda came to Orkey's Hollow looking for her brother, Eiman. The cave is said to be haunted, and young Nords on the island sometimes enter it to prove their bravery. Eiman went in, but he hasn't come out.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3988",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a Fighters Guild camp where an Argonian soldier is recovering from a fierce battle with spiders.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3987",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I met up with Seyne near Hozzin's Folly. Bandits have landed on the island. They're exploring an abandoned mine that was once home to Daedra worshipers.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3999",["level"]="5",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Halmaera has lost track of her husband and her dog. I've offered to help her look for both of them.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3986",["level"]="3",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A strange woman came up to me as I was walking through the woods. She said something about skeevers before leading me into the hills.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3985",["level"]="5",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've encountered a wounded hunter in the wilds near Bleakrock Village. Hoknir is seriously wounded. He wants some help killing his prey.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3992",["level"]="6",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I caught up with Darj near Skyshroud Barrow. Skeletons attacked and wounded him before he could find a way to get its door open.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4016",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've found evidence that the Daggerfall Covenant may soon attack Bleakrock and the rest of the Pact. We need to evacuate as soon as possible, but anyone who doesn't rally to the village will be left behind.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4002",["level"]="7",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've helped the community leaders of Bleakrock Village. Rana's preparing the villagers to evacuate.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3991",["level"]="7",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Daggerfall Covenant has assaulted Bleakrock Village. Captain Rana sent the surviving refugees to Last Rest, a tomb near the town. Rana and I must clear a path through the tomb for the refugees.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4693",["level"]="3",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A moon-sugar plantation suffered a terrible fire. The family in charge of the plantation needs a hand to recover from their tragedy.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4625",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A powerful mage named Rurelion went missing in the Temple of the Mourning Springs. I agreed to help his apprentice Gathwen search the temple for signs of her master.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4966",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a wanted poster offering a reward for the head of an Orc called Sgolag.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4968",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nimriell, a kwama-tender and researcher, told me that she was driven out of her mine and lost her kwama flock as well as her research notes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4885",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Falinesti Winter Site, one of the legendary resting places of the Walking City of Falinesti, is buzzing with activity. It seems General Endare has begun an excavation.",["poiIndex"]="29",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4914",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The ruins of the ancient Wood Elf village of Gil-Var-Delle is under the corrupting influence of Molag Bal. The Worm Cult is active here, and my help is needed to put an end to their schemes.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4975",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a priest of Y'ffre who seeks to heal the scarred ruin of Gil-Var-Delle by mixing blessed water into the falls that feed into the river of the vale. She asked me to help her in her task.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4977",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Eminaire, a scholar studying dialects of the Ayleidoon language, asked me to travel west to the coast to look for fragments of a tablet that she believes may further her research.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4915",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A group of vampire hunters has come to this area to cleanse it of its infestation, including a powerful vampire lord. They've asked for my assistance.",["poiIndex"]="33",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4893",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="On approaching Redfur Trading Post, I came upon Cinder-Tail, a Khajiit in trouble with the local authorities.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4908",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Enthoras needs couriers to make deliveries around Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4387",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found an ancient letter in the Reliquary of Stars. It speaks of an ancient, forbidden love.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4385",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Mages Guild is investigating a strange Ayleid ruin, which has recently become much more active than in years past.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4386",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Laranalda uncovered information proving the Heart of Anumaril is definitely located within the Reliquary of Stars. She needs my help in recovering it.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4917",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Vinedusk Rangers want me to help quash the remnants of the Blacksap Rebellion, the Wood Elf civil war that ended with the Dominion's formation.",["poiIndex"]="31",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4895",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a strange glowing amulet on a corpse in the woods.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4854",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Culanwe, a priestess of Azura, has long suffered at the hands of Molag Bal. Her pain is so great it has torn a hole between Coldharbour and Laeloria, an Ayleid ruin in Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="23",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4815",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nature itself has turned against the Bosmer village of Karthdar and its citizens are desperate to restore peace.",["poiIndex"]="30",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4939",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mizahabi has lost track of her husband and her dog. I've offered to help her look for both of them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4842",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dead Mages Guild acolyte in the Ossuary of Telacar. However he died, it was sudden and unpleasant. The acolyte came from the Mages Guild base camp near the old Ayleid ruins.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4395",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found bandit orders detailing a plan to attack Barkbite Stronghold in Reman's Bluff. I should do what I can to stop the bandit attacks.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4397",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've helped track down the source of the poison in Barkbite Stronghold, but the poisoner still remains to be found. I should work with Moramat to bring the culprit to justice.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4398",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Moramat has asked me to find and deal with Gargak, the real force behind the attacks on Barkbite Stronghold.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4950",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dead Orc in Vinedeath Cave. A well-crafted bow and a note were beside him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4951",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Queen Ayrenn must complete the ratification ceremony if her allies are to accept her as leader of the Aldmeri Dominion. At the heart of the ceremony is the Orrery, an ancient Ayleid artifact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4922",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="If Queen Ayrenn is to prove herself worthy of leading the Aldmeri Dominion to glory, she must complete the ratification ceremony in the Orrery of Elden Root. Legends say it can reveal those worthy of becoming emperor â€¦ or empress.",["poiIndex"]="24",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4735",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Queen Ayrenn must deal with the aftermath of her brother's betrayal and settle matters in Grahtwood. In the meantime, she asked me to travel to Marbruk, in Greenshade, and secure the Staff of Magnus from its vault.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4791",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An undercover agent named Cinnar asked for my help tracking down a notorious thief called the Artisan. He gave me a list of people to question around Marbruk.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4573",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Wood Elves in this part of the Valenwood are opposed to the Dominion. I agreed to negotiate and attempt to convince them to swear allegiance to Queen Ayrenn.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4593",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="To learn why the Wood Elves in this part of the Valenwood are opposed to the Dominion and to convince them to change their mind, I must negotiate with the Wilderking.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4596",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Wood Elf named Benduin wants to show me how to build a guardian with special powers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4824",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Bosmer named Adamir, and his associate Timiwe, are attempting to animate an assemblage of rodent parts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4657",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Though Aranias was sent by the Veiled Heritance to kill him, the Wilderking believes she has actually come for another reason, and that our destinies are intertwined.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4586",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Veiled Heritants plan to harm the Wilderking. If I enter Aranias' past through Maruin's story, I can change her future.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4699",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A merchant in the Shrouded Vale reports seeing a village that has mysteriously and suddenly appeared in a nearby cave.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4792",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A stone being named Sumiril carries a book that contains a story about how he came to be.",["poiIndex"]="57",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4750",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Aranias and Andur were sent by the Veiled Heritance to kill the Wilderking. They are now forcing their way through Greenheart towards the Wilderking's throne.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4848",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered the remains of a mage outside a cave in Shademist Moors. While there are no shortage of victims around here, the presence of the Mages Guild urges me to investigate what might have happened to the rest of them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4611",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Something strange is happening in Shademist Moors. The village of Longhaven needs someone who can uncover what might be behind it.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4615",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Destroying the cursed skull held by the Shademist vampires has cleared the moors of corruption, but Thorinor says his wife was among the missing and never returned.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4853",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Before losing Aranias' memories, the Wilderqueen told me that she knew about the Veiled Heritance plot to steal the Staff of Magnus. She suggested I go to the city of Woodhearth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4574",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After the death of Prince Naemon, Vicereeve Pelidil assumed leadership of the Veiled Heritance and stole the Staff of Magnus. Razum-dar has tracked him to somewhere in the area of Woodhearth.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4580",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Evidence suggests that Vicereeve Pelidil and the Veiled Heritance are planning to attack the city of Woodhearth.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4575",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I need to find out what's happening in Rootwater Grove and prevent it from spreading into Greenshade.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4681",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sea Elves have entered Serpent's Grotto, and one of the Maormer mages has broken the seals that bound a massive sea serpent here for centuries.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4744",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Pelidil's plans to lead the Maormer in attack against Valenwood have been exposed and Treethane Fariel suggests I go to Seaside Sanctuary to try to repel the Maormer invasion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4739",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicereeve Pelidil and his Maormer allies have attacked and seized control of Seaside Sanctuary.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4765",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Seaside Sanctuary is back in the control of the Aldmeri Dominion, but Vicereeve Pelidil has escaped aboard a Maormer vessel.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4821",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've been given a letter to deliver to Queen Ayrenn to bring her up to speed on the events that have occurred and inform her of our victory over Vicereeve Pelidil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5088",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="It seems that Prince Naemon has indeed returned from the dead and now leads an undead army that's pushed its way to the city gates of Marbruk.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4546",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="An undead army surges through Driladan Pass and assaults Marbruk on the command of the Shade of Prince Naemon.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4771",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Thonoras and his wife, Pariel, were captured and tortured by Wood Orcs. Pariel begged Hircine to save them, and Hircine \"changed her.\" After helping her husband escape, Pariel disappeared into a cave beneath the Falinesti Spring Site.",["poiIndex"]="46",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4826",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Narion, a member of a hunting order called the Hounds, asked for my help in hunting a timber mammoth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4787",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Laurosse, a lovelorn Altmer, who believes his Wood Elf bride-to-be has been kidnapped.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4608",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Most of the Bosmer entering Verrant Morass are being corrupted by a blight that turns them into feral beasts. Indaenir believes the corruption comes from the Shade of Naemon.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4601",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Shade of Prince Naemon and the Veiled Heritance have somehow raised the infamous warriors of the Blackroot Clan from the dead.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5063",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Fleeing undead to the north, a clan of Bosmer refugees wants to settle in Shadows Crawl, but stone men, known as Hollow, rose from the ground and attacked.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4828",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Radreth, a new member of the hunting company the Hounds, asked for my help in hunting a giant wasp.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4794",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Khajiit trader was tricked by an Altmer merchant captain who gave her low quality fabric in place of the rare silks she traded for.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4850",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Shade of Prince Naemon is spreading corruption across Greenshade. I must help Indaenir cleanse the corruption.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4690",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Shade of Prince Naemon has seized control of Hectahame where he is corrupting the Heart of the Valenwood. I must assist Queen Ayrenn and Indaenir in defeating him.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5006",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="With Prince Naemon deadâ€”againâ€”and the new Silvenar revealed, Queen Ayrenn asked me to head to Velyn Harbor in Malabal Tor. The Aldmeri Dominion needs to prepare for the wedding between the Green Lady and the newly-discovered Silvenar.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4193",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Redguard invaders and Wood Orcs from the Drublog clan attacked Velyn Harbor. Lieutenant Ehran plans to create a militia to take back the city.",["poiIndex"]="26",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4194",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The battle for Velyn Harbor continues. With a little luck and a lot of effort, the Redguard invaders and Drublog Wood Orcs can be driven from the town.",["poiIndex"]="26",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4195",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Angardil isn't a resident of Velyn Harbor, but he's been caught up in their problems.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4119",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Maormer Sea Vipers invaded Ilayas Ruins, searching for a weather-controlling relic called the Sphere of Storms. I've been asked to help the stormwardens defend the sphere until reinforcements arrive.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4111",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Vicious raiders known as the Steel Shrikes attacked a troupe of traveling entertainers. They hold several performers captive at Fuller's Break.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4112",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Salgaer wants to take his own type of revenge against the Steel Shrikes who destroyed his troupe's ship and livelihood.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4378",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Glanir is a Proctor for the Aldmeri Dominion. He has tracked a bandit group known as the Crimson Raiders to their hideout. The Raiders have been causing trouble for the Dominion fleet.",["poiIndex"]="37",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4373",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Bosmer named Peras escaped from bandits hiding in the Crimson Cove. He claims his ship was boarded by the raiders, and he has friends still inside the cove.",["poiIndex"]="37",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4089",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Green Lady's sister, Lanwaen, may have been kidnapped from Deepwoods, a village famous for being the birthplace of several previous incarnations of the Green Lady as well.",["poiIndex"]="28",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4108",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Oraneth offered to tell me the story of the Green Lady and show me the most sacred sites of Deepwoods.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4291",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Falinesti Summer Site is a legendary seasonal location for the Wood Elves' Walking City. But the city hasn't been seen in Tamriel for centuries. Now, something is happening at the Summer Site.",["poiIndex"]="52",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4464",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After eating too many moon-sugar candies, Liane's Khajiit husband, Feluz, ran screaming into the forest.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4458",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Green Lady believes the Wood Orc clan of Dra'bul, the Drublog, would not have attacked Velyn Harbor under normal circumstances.\n\nShe needs to take some time to visit with local leaders in Velyn Harbor before going to Dra'bul.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4452",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Green Lady has come to Dra'bul to find out why the Drublog attacked Velyn Harbor.",["poiIndex"]="23",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4288",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A blind Redguard pirate is willing to share his treasure with anyone who can transport him to Anvil, even the Wood Elves harassing him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4129",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Maormer attacked an Aldmeri Dominion ship off the coast of Jode's Pocket and captured several members of its crew.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4130",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Though the Thalmor fleet manifest had been destroyed, the Maormer still hold Captain Seritenya captive at Jode's Pocket.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4285",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Drublog Orcs attacked the village of Tanglehaven. Treethane Dailithil said the survivors barely managed to fend them off. After the massacre, the surviving Tanglehaven militia chased the Drublog into the forestâ€”including Firwin, Treethane Dailithil's daughter.",["poiIndex"]="51",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4497",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While exploring the Tomb of the Apostates I came across a campsite with an inscribed vase. The inscription read as if it was given to someone, but I only found skeletons in the tomb.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4137",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Though most of the rotmeth was stolen, an unfinished batch remains. Alphrost needs some special ingredients to complete what's left of the brew.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4134",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Someone is stirring up chaos in Vulkwasten, and Peruin asked me to help put a stop to it.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4103",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a journal written by a priest of Z'en, which details part of Bloodtoil Valley's history. The local spinner may find this information valuable if I can find the rest of the journals.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4101",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A recent conflict between the Wood Elves and Drublog Orcs of Bloodtoil Valley threatens to end in bloodshed.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4155",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult ambushed and captured several Wood Elves in Abamath. The Cult may be preparing for a dark ritual.",["poiIndex"]="22",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4456",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Shaman Glazulg told me his clan had a hand in the Silvenar's alleged kidnapping by the Hound.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4124",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Drublog clan of Wood Orcs captured the Silvenar. I need to infiltrate Jathsogur and do whatever's necessary to free him.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4475",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While exploring along the river, I found an Argonian enveloped in lightning. I found a journal nearby his body. It contained instructions on how to help him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4085",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found the temple of the spinners of Malabal Tor, where their \"story\" has gotten away from them.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4161",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A spinner in Valeguard wants to finally transcribe a story into written word, but is having difficulties.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4092",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult is trying to enslave the spirits of Ouze.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4091",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult invaded Ouze and captured its primary protector, Spinner Indinael.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4477",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Silvenar assures me he will recover from his imprisonment in Jathsogur and I should not wait for him. He wants me to meet him in the city of Silvenar where he will marry the Green Lady.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4143",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Indaenir, the new Silvenar, traveled across Malabal Tor to marry the Green Lady and fulfill his role as the spiritual leader of the Wood Elves. But the Hound arrived first and is trying to usurp his position.",["poiIndex"]="20",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4144",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="People from across the Aldmeri Dominion gather to celebrate the handfast of the Silvenar and the Green Lady. The Hound, however, caused many of them trouble. Among these are a group of minstrels led by Laen the Doorwalker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4515",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Fists of Thalmor were attacked by strange creatures in Wilding Run. While many were slain, there may be survivors.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4503",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Daine and his brother, Dariel, came to the ruins in search of a plant which grows in the light of an Ayleid well. Its sap is rumored to cure any malady.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4142",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Finoriell needs to join her fellow spirits in Treehenge, but something prevents her.",["poiIndex"]="24",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4165",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Finoriell must take root in Treehenge before the Worm Cult can corrupt her soul.",["poiIndex"]="24",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4229",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Altmer doing research in Treehenge found some cultists poaching mammoths at the shrine.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4500",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While exploring Dead Man's Drop I came across a battered Nord shield.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4196",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Eraral-dro hired Gold Coast mercenaries from Colovia to protect his tradepost, but suspects they will turn on him.",["poiIndex"]="27",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4199",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Eraral-dro wants to neutralize the Gold Coast mercenaries in Malabal Tor so his people will be safe from reprisal.",["poiIndex"]="27",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4480",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Vinedusk Rangers are under siege by an invading Colovian force. They've offered me a chance to join the fight.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4486",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="With the Colovians removed from the village, Captain Odreth has planned a counterattack with his Rangers. We are to use a secret tunnel to gain access to the Colovian camp and take them out.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4544",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Mane, on his way to the Handfasting in Silvenar, suddenly attacked his entourage and fled. Lord Gharesh-ri, the Speaker of the Mane, asked me to find him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4460",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Mane has released Dro-m'athra spirits on Fort Grimwatch! Twins Khali and Shazah, Khajiit Champions, lead the fight against the creatures.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4461",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've worked with the Lunar Champion Shazah to seal up corruption wells inside of Fort Grimwatch. Now I've met up with her sister Khali to explore an unearthed Khajiiti temple.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4738",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered a Spinner named Melrethel imprisoned in the cellars of the Vile Manse. She claims to be from the Wood Elf village that Graccus razed and built his manor upon.",["poiIndex"]="23",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4501",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've come upon an active battlefield, as Colovian forces attempt to take an Ayleid ruin from Dominion soldiers.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4689",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I have been sent to the Moonlit Clearing to meet with a member of the lunar clergy. I'm supposed to find out if I am the Moon Hallowed.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4710",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to help the people of Arenthia. Apparently Mane Akkhuz-ri is somewhere amid the Colovian invaders of the city.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4652",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The town of Arenthia has been occupied by a Colovian force. I've been tapped to help retake the city alongside a Khajiiti resistance force.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4653",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="According to Centurion Gavo's confession, the Stonefire cult plans to summon a Dark Anchor within Arenthia.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4647",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Thizzrini Arena is host to numerous arena games in a sprawling complex outside of Dune. To compete in the games, I must speak with the three Division Champions and earn the proper credentials.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4649",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I am competing in the Sorcerer Division of Thizzrini Arena. I must fight through the ranks in order to fight Malarel, the Sorcerer Division Champion.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4650",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I am competing in the Swordmaster Division of Thizzrini Arena. I must rise through the ranks of contenders before I can battle Zara, the Swordmaster Division Champion.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4648",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I am competing in the Summoner Division of Thizzrini Arena. I need to work my way through the ranks in this division before I can challenge Tholbor, the Division Champion, in the main arena.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4651",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I have defeated the champions of the three major divisions in Thizzrini Arena. Now I am ready to face Ishalga and become the Grand Champion of Thizzrini Arena.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4717",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Within Fort Sphinxmoth I encountered one of the chapel guards. She believes more of her companions were still alive elsewhere in the complex.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4676",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bandits attacked a chapel just over the border from Reaper's March. A group of temple guards and their priestess tracked them to the ruins of Fort Sphinxmoth.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4578",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An associate of Cariel's stopped me outside of Arenthia to ask for help. She's lost some critical supplies and letters, and wants my help in retrieving them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4599",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="As I arrived at the town of Greenhill, a very drunk man ran out to me and began raving about evil strangers in town.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4665",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bowenas, the Treethane of Greenhill, is having trouble deciding what to do with Ezreba. The Khajiit helped the cultists to subvert the town, but she was forced to do so against her will.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4488",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Bosmer named Ongalion at the Falinesti Autumn site. He's a tree-steward, helping to tend the site while the city is away.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4487",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Telenger the Artificer, a reknowned sage, has come to the Falinesti Autumn Site in search of answers.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4749",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The mine called Kuna's Delve has been assaulted by a pack of bloodthirsty trolls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4697",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Clan Mother Kazirra told me to travel to the city of Rawl'kha, to bring word of the Mane's change of heart.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4712",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I traveled to the city of Rawl'kha, where I'm to help the Lunar Champions begin their spiritual journey.",["poiIndex"]="33",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4571",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found the body of a hunter in the wilds. Nearby was a notice he dropped detailing a bounty on senche-tiger fangs.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4440",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a strange old Wood Elf outside the ancient ruin known as Thormar. She's invited me to a party she calls \"the greatest in all the worlds.\"",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4499",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After our tricks at Thormar, Aniel has ushered me into Baan Dar's realm: The Five Finger Dance.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4457",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Daifa wants my help to prank her Subtle Knife rival, Aldeth, who has won their trickster duels for the last four years.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4536",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The lunar priests at the Do'Krin Monastery have been attacked by the Stonefire cult. The survivors fear the cultists mean to steal a sacred relic: The Golden Claw.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4537",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the body of a Khajiiti woman on the terrace of Do'Krin Monastery. She was still clutching a letter and a small offering to the Bright Moons.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4709",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lunar Priestess Kauzanabi-jo has indicated I should make for the temple of Moonmont. The Champions, the new candidates for the Mane, will join me there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4479",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After the ritual at Rawl'kha, I traveled to meet the Lunar Champions at the temple called Moonmont. Here I'm told the Dark Mane has holed up. After what it did to Mane Akkhuz-ri, we must destroy it.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4732",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've been asked by a moon priestess named Felari to help with a project that could help firm up relations between the Khajiit and Wood Elves. They are working to return home relics and bones from ancient battle sites.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4740",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Wood Elf brewing town of Willowgrove is trying to expand their beehives. They've hired help to clear the forest. This help appears to have suffered some difficulties.",["poiIndex"]="22",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4775",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I ran into a very hung-over mage in Rawl'kha. He had too much to drink, lost several magical relics, and now fears he'll never gain an apprenticeship to Telenger the Artificer.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4598",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Khajiit named Tand has disappeared at the notorious Hadran's Caravan. The people who love him are losing hope of seeing him again. They have turned to me for help.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4655",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hadran, the slave dealer who runs Hadran's Caravan, sent his thugs to kill me and failed. His business partner, Azum, has grown tired of his slave-trading operation and wants me to eliminate him.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4668",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I'm now partcipating in Lizard Racing, where I place bets on which lizard finishes the race first.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4481",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Clan Mother Shuzura has apparently been very hard on her assistants. There are problems in the little town of S'ren-ja. Perhaps I can help out.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4482",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Milk Eyes has been having problems with rats down his well.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4483",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Word around town is that the farmer Ezzag is having trouble in his fields.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4484",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The rumor around town is that Kalari's new house is haunted.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4485",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I helped the people of S'ren-ja with their many and varied problems.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4711",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After a vicious fight with the Dark Mane at Moonmont, we left Khali behind to hold his essence in place. Shazah has asked me to meet her at Dune, where we'll prepare to walk the Two Moons Path.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4808",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a journal that belonged to a monk of the Lunar faith named Yenadar. The journal mentions that he has a sister named Kala in S'ren-ja. I should return the journal to her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4550",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've arrived at the city of Dune to find it under siege by Daedra and the forces of Javad Tharn.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4719",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I saved Dune from the plots of Javad Tharn. Now I must aid the Lunar Champion as she walks the Two Moons Path, a mystical Khajiit ritual used to annoint a new Mane.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4720",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I have completed the first part of the Two Moons Path with the Lunar Champion. Now we must venture into the Den of Lorkhaj and complete the mystical journey.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4687",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a suspicious bottle near the town of Pa'alat. There appears to be something inside it.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4492",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In the wake of a Dro-m'Athra attack, a lunar priest has asked me to save a priceless relic from the vault behind Moonmont.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5318",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Orsimer army needs to get into Frostbreak Fortress to find and destroy the source of the briarheart warriors, but the Winterborn's defense are too strong. Between the briarhearts and the harpies, they can't breach the walls.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5462",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lozruth and Sharela discovered a lost tomb, but they disagree on who rests within.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5317",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a letter from High-King Emeric offering amnesty to the bandits who reside in the ruins of Watcher's Hold. The royal messenger also brought a chest of gold as a sign of the king's good faith.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5329",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Kurog of Orsinium struggles to defeat the Winterborn threat. His mother, Forge-Mother Alga, asked me to go to Frostbreak Fortress to aid the king.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5485",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dagarha, one of the Malacath faithful, learned Winterborn raiders seek the Vengeful Eye, an old relic of Malacath. She wants me to recover it before they can.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5474",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I spoke with Zabani who is being held for stealing something from the king. She swears a Wood Elf named Agolas framed her for the crime. She asked me to help her prove it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5447",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="One of the guards from the caravan brought me a message. It seems that King Kurog has requested my presence at his cornerclub in Orsinium.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5326",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Forge-Wife Kharza is worried about Graystone Quarry. After she hired an Elf to help improve efficiency, strange things began to occur. Fog rolled out of the quarry and screams were heard. Then â€¦ nothing.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5464",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A group of Orc artisans was heading to the new city of Orsinium when they were attacked by members of the Trinimac cult known as the Vosh Rakh and taken prisoner in the ruins of Paragon's Remembrance.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5439",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Draugr from a nearby barrow harass the Orcs of Gloorot's clan. A legendary hero named Narsis Dren agreed to help them, but he has yet to return from the ancient barrow.",["poiIndex"]="28",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5452",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Brulak built a cairn for his grandfather Corgrak, but couldn't retrieve Corgrak's helm from Morkul Descent.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5441",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="All is not right in Morkul Stronghold. Ashaka, the chief's eldest daughter, ran off to Morkul Descent without explanation.",["poiIndex"]="26",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4401",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've discovered the Ember-Eye's plans for an assault on Koeglin Lighthouse. I should bring these to Koeglin Village.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5646",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rumors are floating around that the Thieves Guild isn't a threat anymore. The Thieves Guild wants to quash the rumors with a series of conspicuous thefts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5865",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Missir-Dadalit Egg Mine has been overrun with kwama. I've been hired to clear out the infestation to help re-balance the colony. I'm also required to defeat a large kwama warrior who guards the queen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5273",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the cavern called Spindleclutch beneath Glenumbra.",["poiIndex"]="66",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5291",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the frosty ruin of Direfrost Keep, which lies flush against the mountains of Eastmarch.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6351",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I met a couple of Wood Elves who want to enlist a mage's and a nature spirit's help to kill a Dragon that threatens Elden Root.",["poiIndex"]="62",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6353",["level"]="50",["type"]="6",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="Word has spread that the Divine Alkosh has descended to his mountain temple of Sunspire to be the Khajiits' savior in these troubled times.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6214",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture any three keeps for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6415",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted challenged me to explore Icereach.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode.",["poiIndex"]="59",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4641",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I met a mage named Shatasha in Darkshade Caverns. She has asked for help investigating the Dwemer ruins beneath the mines.",["poiIndex"]="60",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6090",["level"]="50",["type"]="6",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="Three Dark Elf Saints were granted the gift of immortality, in the form of ageless mechanical bodies created by the god Sotha Sil, at the price of their sanity. Now their madness poses a significant threat to the Clockwork City.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6449",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a lumpy sack abandoned in the wilderness. Its contents seem to be alive.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2538",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After escaping from the mirror, the countess is asking me to help her uncover which of her suitors actually gave her a gift that turned out to be a trap.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1384",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The owners of the Dro-Dara Plantation have lost everything. First ogres attacked, and now bandits. The plantation was owned by a group of retired adventurers. The thief, Janne, asked me to rescue the others.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2536",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dro-Dara asked me to talk to the warrior Knarstygg about abandoning the plantation.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1339",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Knarstygg and Dro-Dara have decided it would be wise to go to Wayrest until the bandits clear out of the plantation. Knarstygg is concerned that Murk-Watcher might not want to leave.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1639",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After I returned the Dream Shard to Pariah Abbey, Abbot Durak told me of concerns that Vaermina also works to destabilize the eastern region of Gavaudon. I'm to warn High King Emeric and then meet Durak at Shinjis's Scarp.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1437",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Clan Murtag Orcs are fighting the Ironhand ogres in Shinji's Scarp. They've asked for my help.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1341",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A glory-seeking Orc warrior asked me to help him gather ogre teeth for a trophy necklace from the battle. Why not?",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1346",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="General Godrun is counting on me to finish this battle with the Ironhand Ogres. If I can collapse the cavern they're using to get through the mountain, that should solve the ogre problem for good.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3637",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Omen of Betrayal failed to manipulate General Godrun into attacking Wayrest, but has now trapped General Godrun within his dream. Abbot Durak has asked me to enter the dream and kill the Omen to save Godrun.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4041",["level"]="28",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I returned to Dhalmora. All of the Bleakrock villagers are gone. Aera informed me of a large Covenant attack on Bal Foyen. Darj has lead some of the non-combatants to Fort Zeren. Captain Rana is leading a defense of the docks.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4028",["level"]="29",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Daggerfall Covenant has siezed control of Foyen Docks. An injured Argonian fisherman saw Rana fighting through their ranks.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4067",["level"]="29",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Argonian named Bishalus is afraid that nix-hounds have devoured her friend, Gena. She claimed to have made a flute that could tame the beasts, but she has yet to return.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4153",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've arrived in Nimalten to find the city under threat. Thane Fjora was attacked by her houscarl. Aera Earth-Turner, my old friend from Bleakrock Isle, is leading an investigation.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5524",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Riekrs have been raiding caravans throughout Wrothgar, plundering cargo and taking travelers prisoners. The Riekrs, led by King-Chief Edu, must be dealt with.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6289",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Several offerings collected by the Root-Whisper Tribe have been stolen by the Blackguards. If these offerings aren't recovered, the other tribes will become deeply offended.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3612",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a confused Nord named Norgred on the road outside of Quarantine Serk. He said he was escorting a witch. Apparently, she turned on him and stole a valuable axe. He's anxious to get it back.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3100",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Bloodmayne for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3137",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Black Boot Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2886",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Brindle Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3662",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Covenant landed west of Ebonheart, but a band of Nord sawyers have refused to join the general defense. They sneeringly refer to the town's Dark Elves as \"fancy lads.\"",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3863",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Naril Heleran turned up again in Ebonheart looking to collaborate on another \"business venture.\" He wants me to procure a bottle of White-Gold Tower from an innkeeper.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4380",["level"]="6",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I stumbled onto the ruins of a campsite by the beach. Sea Drakes attacked and kidnapped two people last night.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6390",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Necromancers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3841",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered a battered Dwarven construct that seems to have killed its Imperial caretaker. The Imperial's notes imply that they are searching for something within the Dwemer ruin at Razak's Wheel.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1294",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The wizard Valdam Andoren in Davon's Watch told me his apprentice has stolen his spellbook. I offered to help find him, but there's a problem. To punish him for a previous theft, the wizard changed the warding rune on the book.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5501",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Brihana has taken to hunting Daedra for sport and profit. She's asked for my help in exchange for a cut of the earnings.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3520",["level"]="41",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sorcerer Vunal at the Brothers of Strife monument says he can teach me about the past. The Brothers were apparently once mortal leaders of the citizens of Stonefalls. The past may hold clues about these powerful creatures.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4054",["level"]="41",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Praxin and his comrades from the Fighters Guild explained that spiders infest the Spindleclutch caves. And maybe something else. It whispers in the darkness.",["poiIndex"]="42",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3622",["level"]="41",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sorcerer Vunal sent me into a deep vision with the help of an ancient ritual site. In this vision of the past, I should be able to interact with Balreth and Sadal. Then I can learn how the Brothers of Strife were born.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6260",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cyrodilic Collections' operation in Murkmire is growing, and more explorers mean more mouths to feed. With my help, Jee-Lar plans to send cured meats to Black Marsh.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6400",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A good-hearted scoundrel named Daini wants to rob local bandits of their ill-gotten goods. She means to use their wealth to leave Elsweyr with her brother, but seems intent on settling scores before she departs.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6441",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A traveler from Skyrim named Vigwenn Owl-Watcher claims to have the recipe for a secret concoction that allows the imbiber to see the invisible sand-whales of Elsweyr and hear their haunting song.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6448",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An herbalist hired me to deliver his product, an herbal remedy, to multiple customers in Senchal. He's being somewhat cryptic, but he offered to pay well if I hurry.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3530",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Defeating the Dark Witnesses can only be accomplished by killing the Hagraven, Uela. Some of the Wyrd Sisters up near Jackdaw Cove have been searching for where Uela is hiding, but they need help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5077",["level"]="5",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Hall Steward Basile has asked I speak with him about the Fighters Guild in the Daggefall Guildhall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5076",["level"]="5",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Magister Nemarc has asked I speak with her about the Mages Guild in the Daggerfall Guildhall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1834",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The only way to ensure Evermore's security and drive the Reachmen from northern Bangkorai is to defeat their leader, the Hagraven Uela. I have agreed to help the Wyresses in Jackdaw Cove toward this end.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6014",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="3",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note about a celebration taking place in my alliance's gate garrison in Cyrodiil and at battleground camps throughout Tamriel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4891",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Reachmen threat has been averted, but Evermore is still in danger, and Queen Arzhela needs my help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4988",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="High King Emeric has arrived with the Lion Guard to help retake Bangkorai Garrison from the Imperial forces.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4912",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Imperial forces have taken control of Bangkorai Garrison, the strategic keep that divides northern and southern Bangkorai. King Emeric and the Lion Guard have come to aid Queen Arzhela and the Knights of Saint Pelin in reconquering the garrison.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2853",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Castle Faregyl for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2700",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2746",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Dragonclaw Lumbermill  for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4079",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Flame atronachs are plaguing the Ayleid ruins at Ceyatatar.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4349",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a bonus for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy combatants.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5220",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5232",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2504",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Supernal Dreamers attacked Azura's shrine at Weeping Giant, killed the Spirit Wardens, and stole many relics. The young novice, Sister Tabakah, asked me to help her recover them and look for a captured warden.",["poiIndex"]="60",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="521",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vaermina has taken control of King Emeric's dreams and Abbot Durak says we need Azura's guidance.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="575",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vaermina's ultimate plan has been revealed. Her consort, the Night Terror, has seized High King Emeric's mind and trapped him in a nightmare. I must face the Night Terror and save the king.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1615",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a letter on a dead man in Bearclaw Mine.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2677",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Dragonclaw for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2919",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Aleswell for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5512",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6226",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cyrodilic Collections, a society dedicated to locating and restoring Argonian antiquities, seeks help in its mission. They want to stay ahead of their competition and preserve every piece of Argonian culture they can.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5495",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sister J'Reeza is looking for aid to protect the valuable artifacts scattered and defenseless across the Temple District.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5483",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I met a scout who serves an Imperial resistance fighter named Captain Caudex. The captain, and a small group of legionary loyalists, have held a garrison at the heart of the Nobles District for nearly two months.",["poiIndex"]="29",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5492",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Valga Atrius, an Imperial freedom fighter, has asked for my help in rescuing Imperial citizens held captive by the Daedra in the Arena District.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2858",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Warden Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6010",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Wardens.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5229",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5226",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3632",["level"]="45",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Covenant has seized Fort Virak. They're serving under the command of General Serien. The Pact's armyâ€”led by the Indorils, Holgunn, and Walks-in-Ashâ€”has besieged the fort in an attempt to retake it.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5498",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A concerned clerk named Loncano believes there is a grave threat to the well-being of future generations if the Imperial recordkeeping falls to war.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
