{["internalId"]="6136",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Relicmaster Glenadir of the Psijic Order has tasked me with recovering stolen relics, taken from the Vault of Moawita.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5337",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A mortal wound to Chief Ogzor has thrown Shatul clan into crisis.",["poiIndex"]="27",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5469",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rogzesh, the hearth-wife to Chief Ogzor, believes he was murdered. She suspects Glagosh, Chief Ogzor's hunt-wife, conspired to kill him. Rogzesh is convinced Glagosh secretly worships Boethiah, the Daedric Prince of Treachery.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5445",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found some ancient Nord relics. I'm sure someone will want to examine these. I'll take them with me and try to locate an interested party.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5497",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Doranar, an artist, believes the ogres of Wrothgar possess a misunderstood artistic genius. He wishes to create a replica of ogre artwork for the House of Orsimer Glories.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5458",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I received another message from King Kurog. He requested that I come to the throne room at Scarp Keep. Apparently, he has a new mission he needs me to deal with.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5348",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="High Priestess Solgra sent Eveli to recruit me for some sort of secret mission. It appears to involve a rescue, but she wants to give me the details in person.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5484",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="One of the survivors of the frozen fleet asked me to keep an eye open for a gold pendant he lost. It was meant to be a gift for his betrothed when they are finally reunited.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5446",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lady Sovelle, an ambassador from Daggerfall, was sent to negotiate a trade agreement with the Orcs. But the fleet was blown off course and wrecked on the ice, and now Lady Sovelle is missing.",["poiIndex"]="30",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5340",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Vosh Rakh attacked Fharun Stronghold, killing people in Trinimac's name. A dying archivist claimed they sought a secret sanctuary and the sacred words of Malacath that are hidden within.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5468",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Kurog seems to be in a foul mood, which has affected everyone in the royal court. His shield-wife indicates that tensions at the keep are on the verge of boiling over. I wonder what happened to darken the king's usually boisterous spirits?",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5444",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lady Laurent and Stibbons have been hired by the House of Orsimer Glories to locate the shrine of Torug gro-Igron, which supposedly sits at the top of the mountain named Sorrow.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5349",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="At Paragon's Remembrance, I learned that the Vosh Rakh plan to harm Chief Bazrag and High Priestess Solgra before they attack the chiefs at the king's moot in Orsinium. I need to find a way to stop them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5481",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="All of the paths into the moot have been sealed except the one through the temple in Orsinium. Chief Bazrag wants me to get to the temple, help High Priestess Solgra, and then reach the moot before Kurog assassinates the clan chiefs.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5494",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Chief Bazrag wants to honor the memory of Kurog with a traditional Orc requiem for the dead. He believes such a ceremony will help heal the wounds Kurog inflicted on Orsinium and the clans.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5319",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="According to a note I discovered in Coldperch Cavern, a hagraven named Kraala uses a totem to transform people into birds.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6007",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a notice stating that adventurers looking for rewarding work should report to the Hall of Justice.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5803",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vivec of the Tribunal has noticed your exploits and requests an audience. Captain Jenassa's ship travels to Seyda Neen from such locations as Daggerfall, Davon's Watch, and Vulkhel Guard. When you arrive, find Canon Llevule outside the town.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5950",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Librarian Bradyn seeks the location of the lost Library of Andule, the secret repository of knowledge of the ancient Great Houses, by building a miniature reproduction of Vvardenfell.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5832",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Dark Elf businessman named Malur Rethan is convinced that his brother and partner, Benar, is hiding something in the Vassir-Didanat ebony mine. He asked me to investigate.",["poiIndex"]="47",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5903",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An elderly Dark Elf named Gilan Lerano contracted me to transport a memory stone to locations across Vvardenfell. He wishes to archive his memories for future generations.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5887",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A House Redoran Councilor seeks information regarding his missing daughter, Veya Releth. After exhausting House resources, he's turned to outside help in a concerted effort to find her.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5919",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Even though I confirmed that Veya is safe, Councilor Eris continues to press me to arrange a meeting between him and his daughter.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5948",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Veya thinks we should go and find Vatola Telem's squad that's scouting the old fort outside of Balmora. She said the fort's overrun with cultists and we need to reach the soldiers before anything happens to them.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5857",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The feared Camonna Tong crime syndicate attacked a group of people smugglers at Khartag Point. Khartag and a group of slaves retreated to a nearby cavern. They'll be killed if help doesn't arrive soon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5885",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Dark Elf named Drelyth Hleran requested my aid in finding his family's lost grave site. He believes the Ashlanders camped near Ald'ruhn might know more about the lost tomb, but the tribes only share their secrets with those who earn their respect.",["poiIndex"]="48",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5880",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lord Vivec fears that the mysterious affliction that drains his divine energy may be the result of an enemy's attack. He asked me to work with Archcanon Tarvus to determine the source of the attack by conducting investigations throughout Vvardenfell.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5877",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Buoyant Armiger warned me of pilgrims being attacked on the roads and directed me to speak to Captain Naros at Molag Mar if I wanted to know more.",["poiIndex"]="74",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6008",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Zainab tribe has encouraged other Ashlanders to seek a positive relationship with outlanders. Because I've shown respect for the Ashlander culture, I've been encouraged to help build that relationship.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5872",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Gnisis Egg Mine has been shuttered. Some kind of mysterious illness has taken hold there. Unfortunately, many workers remain trapped inside.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5883",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Another crisis looms in the Gnisis Egg Mine. Kwama workers, driven mad by the tonal magicks of the Dwarven resonator, killed their queen. Without the queen, the colony dies. If I do not act, the mining town of Gnisis will die along with it.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5864",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tilenra, a Telvanni healer and herbalist, has served the people of Suran for years. Unfortunately, a Mages Guild healer named Menaldinion has opened a shop of his own, and he's taken a keen interest in disrupting Tilenra's business.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5862",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="According to a masked vigilante known as the Scarlet Judge, a corrupt marshal named Hlaren is oppressing the citizens of Suran. I must aid the Judge in rooting out this corruption.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5893",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lord Vivec's condition continues to deteriorate as his energy drains away. Archcanon Tarvus believes that Chodala's staff holds the key to saving the Warrior-Poet. However, it also makes the Ashlander practically impervious to harm.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5902",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Daedric hound Barbas tricked us into depleting Lord Vivec's energy so he could determine the location of Clockwork City. Before we deal with Barbas, we need to restore enough energy to Vivec to keep the moonlet from plummeting out of the sky.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5905",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Archcanon Tarvus revealed himself to be Barbas, the hound of Clavicus Vile. In an effort to locate and take control of Clockwork City, he tricked me into helping him drain Lord Vivec's energy. I need to stop Barbas and recover Lord Vivec's energy.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6003",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lord Vivec wants to reward those who helped restore his power and save Vvardenfell from Barbas and Clavicus Vile. He asked me to help him accomplish that.",["poiIndex"]="75",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5882",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Elfbetta, personal assistant to the famed explorer Narsis Dren, informed me that the adventurer is investigating the ancestral tombs that dot the Vvardenfell landscape. They apparently uncovered an old scroll that hints at hidden treasure.",["poiIndex"]="64",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5886",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The scholar, Neramo, has a problem. One of his less savory competitors, Artisan Lenarmen, stole his Dwemer control rod, and seeks to use it to find an ancient artifact. I must stop Lenarmen before he discovers the secret of Nchulefthingth.",["poiIndex"]="34",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6135",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A prominent High Elf named Halimorion was murdered by a folkloric assassin called the Ghost of the Green. But there may be more to this case than meets the eye.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3152",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6118",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a High Elf bailiff outside the ruins of the Direnni Acropolis. He told me that an ancient curse lingers within its walls. I must find the source of this corruption and cleanse it.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6064",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="According to the Undaunted Trailblazer, Yisareh, the ruins of Fang Lair have been taken over by a cult of necromancers who are preparing for something big. She's enlisted my help in discovering and foiling their plans.",["poiIndex"]="64",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6121",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a keeper of the Royal Menagerie in Sil-Var-Woad. He warned me that dangerous animals have escaped into the park grounds, but he is searching for a tame indrik that may have escaped during the chaos.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6177",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Three descendants of Gjadil the Keel-Hauler have traveled to Summerset to collect her buried treasure. Unable to trust each other after a death of a party member, they've requested I find the chest and bring it back to them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4346",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I must discover what has happened to the missing nobles of Direfrost Keep.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5826",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Reaper's March.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6178",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A High Elf named Vinafwe is being plagued by a vandal who is ruining her carefully arranged botanical grounds with foreign flowers and even dangerous stranglers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6180",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a noblewoman along the beach who has lost her husband and her prized hound. I have agreed to help reunite them with her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5841",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mistress Dratha, having woken from a crippling illness, made it clear that she wants to beat death. Seven Daedric relics called the Stones of Cold Fire may be the key to achieving immortality.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5930",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Ashalmawia and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6111",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Sapiarchs of Lillandril imprisoned a member of the Mages Guild. The authorities are convinced this mage murdered one of Lillandril's sapiarchs, but the particulars seem murky. There may be more to this murder than meets the eye.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6115",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Students in the Illumination Academy have taken on bizarre personae and don't appear to know who or where they are. I must help them reclaim their lost identities.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6142",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Sea Sload altered the Ritemaster's memories and forced him to steal the Heart of Transparent Law and hide it away. While he works to unlock his memories, he wants Valsirenn and I to warn the keepers of the Crystal Tower, the Sapiarchs.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6137",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Seeks-the-Dark was hired to steal tokens from a cult within Eton Nir Grotto. Unexpectedly, the cult has been massacred by Daedra who now lurk within. I've been hired to collect the tokens and find Seek-the-Dark's assistant, Erilthel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6109",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Ritemaster used scrying magic to recall some of his missing memories. He took the Heart of Transparent Law into the Dreaming Cave beneath Ceporah Tower, but he still can't remember what happened after that. I need to help him remember.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3918",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Sheogorath's book is supposed to lead me to the next trial, \"the Circus of Cheerful Slaughter.\" Let's see what the Mad God has planned for me this time.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4426",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sylvian Herius asked me to deliver orders to a rebel spy in Imperial-held Cheydinhal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4422",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Vyctoria Girien asked me to taint Imperial food stores with a special spice.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4417",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Imperial archers are preventing rebel troops from crossing the river.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5534",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Zeira, the guildmaster of the Abah's Landing Thieves Guild, believes someone sold out the guild to the Iron Wheel. She needs my help to deal with the matter.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3953",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I've been tasked with finding another book for the Mages Guild. Once again I need to return to the Shivering Isles, to a place called the Chateau of the Ravenous Rodent.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3997",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Valaste and Shalidor have finished analysis of Sheogorath's books. Now I need to help them take possession of Eyevea, the Mages Guild Sanctuary.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4971",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After all we've been through together, Arch-Mage Shalidor wants to offer me a kind of memory boon, a way to recall every book I've ever read.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5831",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from the Rift.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4434",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sylvian Herius's troops have written petitions, asking the gods' intervention on the rebel side.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3850",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've encountered a Covenant scout named Damrina in Razak's Wheel. She was captured by Imperials and has asked for my aid.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3990",["level"]="3",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6127",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ulliceta, an apprentice studying under the Psijics, took a powerful seeing stone called the Eye of Remembrance to the forbidden Traitor's Vault. It may reveal the secrets hidden there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6144",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note by a dead Dominion soldier, written by Captain Telomure. It describes a betrayal by Justiciar Avanaire. She's now hiding within the ruins of Tor-Hame-Khard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4104",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Raynor and Kireth Vanos, self-proclaimed Dwemer experts, left Morrowind to look for long lost knowledge and lore within Skyrim's Dwarven ruins.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4105",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Kireth Vanos has been exploring the ruins of Mzulft, looking for a valuable piece of forgotten lore. Her brother Raynor and her plan to use their findings to get invited into either Shad Astula or the Mages Guild.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4722",["level"]="10",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've arrived in Cyrodiil, ready to help the Pact win the war.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5075",["level"]="11",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Hall Steward Hilan has asked I speak with him about the Fighters Guild in the Davon's Watch Guildhall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5074",["level"]="11",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Magister Rudrasa has asked I speak with her about the Mages Guild in the Davon's Watch guildhall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6113",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Ritemaster Iachesis remembers a woman's voice, whispering ancient words over and over. He thinks these words are tied to the place where he hid the Heart of Transparent Law. Before we breach the barrier, we need to determine what the words mean.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6117",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The garrison at Cey-Tarn Keep has been terrorized by a spate of unusual disappearances and deaths. A monster hunter named Silurie has enlisted my help to stop the killings.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6146",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A group of outcasts living in the seclusion of the Corgrad Wastes has seen their number dwindle after a string of disappearances. They believe the source of the trouble lies in the old buried ruins exposed by the recent sinkholes plaguing the region.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6125",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="With the Ritemaster dead and the Heart of Transparent Law in Nocturnal's hands, events have taken a grim turn. I need to help the Psijic sages figure out a way to enter the Crystal Tower and stop Nocturnal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6126",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I negotiated an alliance of sorts with Clavicus Vile and Mephala. They agreed to help us get into the Crystal Towerâ€”mostly. Once inside, I need to find a way to stop Nocturnal before she uses the tower to remake reality.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6153",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="With the Crystal Tower saved, Valsirenn wishes to call a meeting of Summerset's most influential leaders to ensure its future protection.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4478",["level"]="11",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Laganakh senses evil spreading on Betnikh. We need to know what we're facing before we can fight it. A totem may grant me visions that will help us.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4547",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Garnikh bet his axe that I can't best the Seamount hunters in duels.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4468",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Bloodthorn Cult has invaded an ancient Breton graveyard in order to raise zombies. The Seamount Orcs are concerned but await reinforcements.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4525",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Orc spirits have risen around Moriseli. I've been asked to investigate the source of this disturbance.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4964",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I was bitten by a vampire. I have the option of embracing the disease or receiving the cure.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3263",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5227",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2983",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4277",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered a statue outside the small town of Shattered Grove. The statue is remarkably lifelike and warm to the touch.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4278",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Merormo senses that a powerful Daedra has wrested control of the animals. As long as the Daedra remains, Merormo won't free the villagers.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4107",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Banished Cells have been overrun by Daedra. They have set free the immortal High Kinlord Rilis, an evil being of great magical power. I have agreed to help Keeper Cirion, the warden of the Banished Cells, deal with this crisis.",["poiIndex"]="41",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3688",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Doubts-the-Moon says some mercenaries in Stormhold are stirring up trouble between the Dark Elves and Argonians.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3645",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zasha-Ja fears for the survival of the Hist Tree the Argonians transplated from Black Marsh to Ebonheart. He thinks the Dark Elves of House Dres poisoned it, so he wants to fertilize it to encourage its growth.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3667",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dunmer of Ebonheart have turned to Disciple Sildras for comfort in the face of an expected assault by Covenant forces. Disciple Sildras, however, believes the Tribunal has rejected the town. His gloom is affecting the citizens' morale.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3639",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A strong Covenant raiding force landed west of Ebonheart. The citizens are too busy with their own internal squabbles to unite against invaders. Drathus Othral fears the town may fall to Alexandra Conele's forces.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3690",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicecanon Hrondar suspects the Dominion skin-stealers are based out of Ten-Maur-Wolk.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4587",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The vicecanons of Shadowfen tracked the Dominion's forces to the ancient Daedric ruin of Ten-Maur-Wolk.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4590",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicecanon Hrondar was replaced by a Dominion skin-stealer. I need to find the imposter and stop the remaining skin-stealers in Ten-Maur-Wolk.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5499",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered a merchant's permit lying unattended. The permit mentions three trading partners from Daggerfall seeking to establish a shop in Orsinium.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5320",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a whistle in a backpack in a cave full of durzog. I should try to use the whistle on the durzogs and then see if anyone in Orsinium is interested in the thing.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4259",["level"]="34",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Spies from the Aldmeri Dominion have infiltrated Sanguine's celebration. Seducer Trilvath gave me Sanguine's goblet and wants me to find the spies.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4237",["level"]="34",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sings-with-Drink has been trapped in Sanguine's celebration for four years. He's convinced he can only escape if the other party goers are distracted by an entertainment troupe from Morrowind.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4607",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I must find a way into the Castle of the Worm. There will be many dangers ahead, so I must make sure I am prepared.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4836",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Varen Aquilarios and Abnur Tharn have found the location of Sai Sahan within the Halls of Torment. I need to venture into these halls and save the final, missing companion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4837",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Varen Aquilarios asked me to accompany Sai Sahan on a trip back to his ancestral home. An old friend, Kasura, may have knowledge of how to sneak into Sancre Tor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5836",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Llonas Givyn desires to marry his love, Tirwin. Unfortunately, Tirwin is a slave belonging to Llonas's mother, Faras, who disapproves of the pairing.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6131",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A massive storm is brewing over the fortress of Sea Keep that is the work of a Maormer Sea Mage. It will devastate the entire coast unless the Sea Mage's spell is stopped.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5443",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a pair of adventurers outside a ruin who offered me a share of their gold if I help them complete a job. They've been hired to find a missing young Orc inside the ruins known as Thukhozod's Sanctum.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4548",["level"]="11",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Orc named Magula has seen visions at three shrines around the island. I should visit these shrines and see the visions.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4559",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The hunt-wife of the Seamount clan thinks the chief's daughter is not mindful of her duties to the clan. She believes I could help sort things out.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5538",["level"]="8",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Rumors abound that the Dark Brotherhood, assassins of legend, are on the lookout for members worthy to wield their killing blade. This might be why so many innocents have been murdered of late.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3914",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tah-Tehat asked me to find his son who hasn't returned to the village.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3608",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Healer Ravel asked me to collect Saint Veloth medallions. As long as the monks are allowed to pray in peace, the medallions allow the power of the Tear of Saint Veloth to keep the Llodos plague in check on whoever wears one.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3611",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Relnus Andalen and his brothers want to take revenge on the Vereansu for killing their father, who was afflicted with the Llodos plague and was being cared for by the monks of Muth Gnaar.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3605",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a tormented Dark Elf spirit in the Orc camp at Malak's Maw. She asked for aid in easing her torment.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3600",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a Dunmer lurking in a cave near Malak's Maw. He informed me that a Nord woman named Svanhildr was captured by Orcs. I offered to rescue her in his stead.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3604",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Svanhildr wants to break the Oathbound offensive once and for all.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3593",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dark Elves have been disappearing along the road to Narsis, near the western mountains. An incursion of Orcs may be responsible. I offered a Dark Elf scout my assistance.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4455",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Merchants from House Hlaalu are worried about their leader, Raston Vendil. He went to negotiate a trade agreement with the isolated Mabrigash tribe in the Vale of the Ghost Snake. He never returned.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3651",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Farseer Bodani has placed the fate of Raston Vendil in my hands. I agreed to undertake a trial and see if the Ghost Snake will counsel me on this matter.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4424",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sylvian Herius wants an Imperial lieutentant killed, to hurt their army's morale and readiness.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4530",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I agreed to help Aemilia Hadrianus kill a Goblin that Chef Amadour has been feeding.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4674",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Someone named Jena is being threatened. She apparently lives in Cheydinhal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4691",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a letter from someone named Iocundus in Cheydinhal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3820",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Some terrible catastrophe has befallen Selfora, and now hostile spirits overrun the place.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3904",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Aamela Rethandus needs healing supplies to treat Selfora's wounded.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3852",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Forlorn One asked me to use the decanter of holy water to rescue two people trapped by the fires.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3620",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered Vara-Zeen, the leader of the Argonian village of Silent Mire. The settlement is under attack by Khajiiti pirates and I have offered my assistance.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3650",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An extremely angry Argonian named Azeenus has asked me to seek vengeance against the Khajiiti pirates in his name.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3624",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Leel-Vata asked me to rescue the captured Argonian villagers from the Khajiiti pirates.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3715",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Churasu has a way to turn the giant wasps into an army to use against the Khajiiti pirates. She needs my help to make an alchemical concoction.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3728",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a battered journal while walking the Coiled Path. A young woman named Risa did not survive this place. She lost her amulet fighting one of the snakes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3684",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="It appears that soldiers known as Sentinels are terrorizing the fortress.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3666",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="General Gavryn Redoran is acting erratically and completely out of character. Something has changed. I get the impression that Tal'Deic Fortress is in some kind of trouble.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3702",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a captive Dark Elf soldier named Saryvn in the ruins beneath Tal'Deic Fortress. He was captured by the Maulborn while he was avoiding his duties.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3683",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I volunteered to enter the ruined crypts beneath the fort to look for the retainer, Durel Gilveni, and the mysterious others mentioned in the General's dispatch. The entrance is by the river.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4867",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Sai Sahan has recovered from his experiences in the Halls of Torment and is ready to guide me to the Amulet of Kings. He hid the artifact in Sancre Tor, an ancient Imperial catacomb.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3749",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Blessed by Veloth, I've come to Eidolon's Hollow to confront Magistrix Vox. It's time to end her threat once and for all.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3810",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="With Vox's wards shattered, the path to her lair is open. Aspera the Forgotten suggests this creates an opportunity to defeat Vox, but I'm not sure I can trust this strange projection.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3831",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The time to confront Vox has arrivedâ€”but it seems that to defeat her, I need to die by her hammer. The Blessing of Veloth should protect me, but can I return from the dead?",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3893",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Deshaan's Academy of Magic, Shad Astula, trains only the most promising mages to become leaders of the Ebonheart Pact. However, the Academy only accepts those who've received a special invitation.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6399",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sai Sahan wants me to infiltrate the Dragon cult and learn more about them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4565",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found a scared bandit trying to hide in Portdun Watch. He wants me to take a token to his brother, though he was too frightened to tell me much more.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4519",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A mortally wounded man in Norvulk Ruins asked me to take word of his death to his wife.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1637",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Slavers are using Steelheart Moorings as their base of operations and they're holding some sailors who they recently captured. The first mate has asked me to help free the sailors from the slavers' clutches.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4589",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Shifty Tom, one of Captain Blackheart's underlings, wants to give up the pirate's life. He plans to leave Blackheart Haven, the Captain's island fortress, but wants me to help him steal two magical relics from the Captain, first.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3815",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicecanon Servyna wants to find out more about the Mnemic Egg. Until the vicecanons understand its danger, they can't root out the Dominion in Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4606",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicecanon Servyna asked me to help Keeper Uxith-Ei in the Hatching Pools. Dominion forces overran the area.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4646",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Dominion took the Mnemic Egg to the Ayleid ruin of Loriasel. There they used its power to sever the Argonian connection with the Hist. As long as it remains in their possession, no Argonian eggs can hatch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3911",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Maahi is one of the few surviving prisoners from the Dominion's march into Loriasel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3912",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After picking up an ancient sword in Loriasel, I learned an Ayleid knight's spirit haunts the ruins.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3909",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicecanon Heita-Meen tracked the Dominion's movement to Loriasel, where she hopes to end the Dominion invasion of Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3910",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vicecanon Heita-Meen asked me to retreive the Mnemic Egg from Ruuvitar, the architect of the Dominion invasion in Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3674",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Some pirates in Alten Corimont captured one of the vicecanons' assistants from Stormhold.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3675",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="One-Eye wants to get rid of Tsanji, the Khajiit in Alten Corimont. Since the Khajiit is running Dominion supply lines, her sudden demise would benefit both One-Eye and the rest of Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3676",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="S'jash has a plan to steal treasure from Dominion troops before they find out what happened to Tsanji, their contact in Alten Corimont.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4474",["level"]="12",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Prophet has contacted me across great distance for some important purpose.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4552",["level"]="13",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Prophet and I are seeking a way to rescue Sai Sahan, the Redguard who hid away the Amulet of Kings.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6119",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I agreed to escort the scholar Andewen as she investigates an ancient temple, hidden within the mysterious forest of Ebon Stadmont.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2759",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a bonus for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy combatants.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3724",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Luteema went to the Percolating Mire. He has yet to reply to Rabeen-Ei's correspondence.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3900",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dominion troops invaded Feyne Vildan's village, trapping her husband and the other villagers. Whatever the soldiers are doing in Percolating Mire, they must be stopped.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3905",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Feyne Vildan's husband Ja-Reet won't speak since his ordeal with the Dominion. I must find a way to heal him.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3888",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Researchers seeking ancient relics around the xanmeers found Renrijra pirates camped in the Argonian ruins they were planning to search.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3889",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The artifacts buried beneath Sunscale Strand are dangerous. Looks-Under-Rocks warns that we may have trouble with them. I need to be careful when searching the ruins.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3890",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I left the ancient Argonian ruins with a single Fang of Sithis. According to Looks-Under-Rocks, the Renrijra pirates are in an uproar. They may be feeling the effects of the other Fang in their midst.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3730",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Deep Graves is plagued by wisps. They're stealing away travelers at the gravesite. No one is sure what caused their sudden aggression.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3729",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Xijai-Teel welcomed a traveling High Elf to Deep Graves, but she believes he has something to do with the wisps' recent aggression.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3731",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="To rid the area of her corrupting influence, Xijai-Teel and I cleansed the ancient vessel. We need it capture the wispmother in Deep Graves.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3799",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dominion established a foothold in the small town of Murkwater. The Argonian Shadowscales intend to take back the town by force.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4831",["level"]="4",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Prophet contacted me through a magical projection. He asked me to seek out a place called the Harborage, where he has taken refuge. I should go to him and ensure that he is safe.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3590",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The remnants of a broken siege lie outside Davon's Watch, broken by the appearance of an army of ghosts. A sergeant at the front, a Nord named Rhorlak, has asked me to decide how best to deal with the spirits.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3594",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Even though they're dead, Ix-Utha's Argonian brethren still act as slaves to the risen Chimer. They've returned to serve their cruel spectral masters.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6165",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Battlereeve sent a group of adventurers and a squad of marines to determine the extent of the Sea Sload's incursion into Summerset. After an initial report, the Battlereeve lost contact with the group. She asked me to investigate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3804",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Argonians in Xal Ithix have been picking through trash piles. Now normally docile creatures from the swamp are attacking them.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3795",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Something caused the creatures in Xal Ithix's swamps to become aggressive and attack the villagers.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3845",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The vicecanons tracked an ancient keystone to White Rose Prison. This artifact would be a major boon to Pact forces in Shadowfen. However, the prisoners seem unwilling to negotiate directly with the vicecanons.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3847",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Erranza, a former prisoner of White Rose Prison, is dead, but her grieving spirit lingers on.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3846",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The keystone is located within the White Rose Prison Dungeon. I've agreed to find it and use it to free the prisoners here.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4532",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Deep inside a dungeon called Mehrunes' Spite, I found a scamp with a labeled choker. It apparently belongs to a mage in Skywatch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2860",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Glademist Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6381",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="According to Ri'hirr, a pair of Khajiiti criminals named Akumjhargo and Zav'i bleed Northern Elsweyr dry through a combination of theft, murder, and extortion. Honest trade cannot flourish as long as these lawbreakers remain alive.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5037",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Covenant soldiers are massing within Softloam Cavern. It won't be long before they have the numbers to launch an attack on Kragenmoor and the rest of Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4435",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="My first trial in Sheogorath's realm awaits. Valaste and Shalidor have uncovered what they need to get me where I need to go.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6094",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found an inactive brassilisk in the Radius of the Clockwork City with the name \"Frynga\" carved into its jaw. If I find Frynga and return her mechanical pet, perhaps she will reward me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6076",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've accepted a contract to defeat Sotha Sil's creation, the Imperfect, in order to test its capabilities. I've also been asked to gather its lost sequence plaques.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6060",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Brengolin, the cook in Slag Town, needs some assistance in creating some unconventional cuisine. This time he's asked me to procure him some Bosmer Root Liqueur.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6061",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Brengolin, the cook in Slag Town, needs some assistance in creating some unconventional cuisine. His meat stores are presently empty, so I agreed to assist him with restocking.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6074",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The people of Slag Town apparently seek predictions about the future from a factotum known as the Grand Prognosticator. Kamid, whose mother died during the last pilgrimage, plans to prove that the oracle is a fraud.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6093",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the journal of Orinol, a dead mage from the city of Cormount, in Grahtwood. He arrived in Clockwork City by accident and died in the Radius sometime later. His dying wish was that someone would care for his dog, Jona.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3865",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The wilderness of Stonefalls is filled with predators and hostile creatures. The citizens of the region would sleep better knowing the worst ones are dead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3916",["level"]="6",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="A high-ranking member of the Mages Guild, Valaste wants me to perform a task for her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3587",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Tanval Indoril asked me to help slow the Covenant's siege of Davon's Watch.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3588",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Covenant forces have scaled the walls of Davon's Watch. Now they're threatening to take the city from within its walls. Tanval's ritual may be our only hope to end the assault.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6299",["level"]="6",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Imperial battlemage and former Grand Chancellor of the Empire, Abnur Tharn, requested my assistance with an important matter that could lead to the end of the Three Banners War.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6395",["level"]="6",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Blademaster Kasura has agreed to search a nearby Dragonguard tomb for a former student interested in finding some way to fight back against the Dragons in Elsweyr. I agreed to help her in this endeavor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6097",["level"]="6",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Vanus Galerion in the Mages Guild. Turns out, he had a message for me from an Oracle. It must be important for the Great Mage to deliver it personally.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3592",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A volcanic eruption and an infestation of shalks have devastated the town of Senie. The townsfolk are wounded, but distrust between Dark Elves and Argonians delay efforts to heal them.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3602",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Drelden Orn lost most of his kwama in a mine collapse. He asked me to help round up the survivors and convince them to return home.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3589",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="With the Covenant driven from Davon's Watch, Tanval Indoril has asked me to return the living weapon known as Balreth to its cell.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3855",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Garyn Indoril believes the spirit of a long-dead mage may know the secret to imprisoning Balreth again. An Argonian scout named Onuja has already left for Othrenis.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3615",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="An Argonian named Onuja has come to Othrenis. He wants to know how to rebind the Brother of Strife. He's hoping to contact the spirit of Mavos Siloreth, an ancient Dunmer scribe buried in the area.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3616",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I awakened the spirit of an ancient Dark Elf scribe named Mavos Siloreth. Mavos's spirit can't remember how he bound Balreth in the original ceremony. To help me, he's going to perform a ritual and show me a vision of the past.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6227",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards, an agreement to deliver Jewelry to an interested organization.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5876",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A mad breedsman named Drovos Nelvayn has created a dangerous new genus of kwama. These insects attack without provocation and resist any attempts at domestication. If the creatures escape, native kwama and the miners that tend them will suffer.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3617",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bala, an Ashlander, is searching for her deceased lover, Eanen Varam. In life, he was part of House Dunmer, so their status kept them apart. They promised each other to unite in death, but now, she can't find his tomb.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3618",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've learned all I can at Othrenis. Onuja says that Balreth is somewhere near Ash Mountain. Garyn Indoril has led many Pact soldiers there with hopes of containing the Brother of Strife.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3736",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Scamps are boiling up out of the ground, no doubt excited by the freeing of Balreth. Sergeant Jagyr asked for my help dealing with them. Collapsing the entrances to caves in Ash Mountain should do the job.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3734",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Garyn Indoril led a force of Pact soldiers to Ash Mountain. They were following the Brother of Strife, Balreth. Using the information I learned from Mavos at Othrenis, we're going to imprison the Brother of Strife again.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3735",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've defeated Ash Mountain's guardians. Now I must enter Ash Mountain's caldera, defeat Balreth, and imprison him again.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3670",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rogue Dark Elves flaunting the Pact are enslaving Argonians at a mine near Ash Mountain. A powerful Daedra rebelled against the mine's master. Then the Daedra took most of the people at the mine into Oblivion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6070",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Bursar of Tributes seeks items of flesh to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3717",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dominion is searching for a keystone in Zuuk. I need to find it before they do.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3718",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After Drillk's memory returned, he told me how to obtain the keystone. It's locked away in the Temple of Sul.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3719",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found a book about Ayleid 'Alasil pilasters' within the Temple of Sul. Beside it was a small Ayleid relic that may be able to awaken the pilasters.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3681",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A group of pilgrims failed to arrive in Hissmir as scheduled. Kiameed fears something has happened to them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6036",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Proctor Sovor Saryoni, a ranking Clockwork Apostle, is dying and has asked me to help save his life. He believes his only hope to continue his existence lies in an experiment conducted by a former apostle, but she was exiled long ago because of it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2799",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5904",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've been hired to defeat the spirits which haunt Salothan Tomb.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5934",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I have been asked to retrieve taxes and records stolen by bandits.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5956",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Sunken Vaults of Ashalmawia are infested with Worm Cultists performing unclean rites to summon Daedra.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5866",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've been hired to defeat a nix-ox that has been eating mushrooms the wizard Bravosi Felder is attempting to research. I'm also required to collect samples of the mushrooms while in the area.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4309",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Arfanel, a member of the Eyes of the Queen at North Beacon. He's tracking an elite Covenant soldier and wants my assistance supporting the troops in the field.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3227",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Brindle for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4295",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Covenant officer and her husband attempted to defect to the Aldmeri Dominion. Covenant troops pursued the Orc couple all the way to Auridon, and they've taken North Beacon in an attempt to capture the Orcs.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4361",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Elanwe's son, Sorondil, is the illegitimate son of the deceased High Kinsman Rilis XII. Sorondil has come to these ruins to retrieve a great treasure and his inheritance.",["poiIndex"]="35",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6166",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Battlereeve Tanerline charged me with finding allies to attack the abyssal geysers and destroy the pearls that power them before the Sea Sload cabal's plan to sink Summerset comes to fruition.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6073",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Clockwork Apostles have sent explorers into the Shadow Cleft to find out more about the mysterious realm and the reason it's connected to Clockwork City. One explorer hasn't returned, and I agreed to try to find him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6240",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dradeiva, a local Argonian, seeks to prove that the Imperial Ninth Legion disappeared in the Tsofeer Caverns. She hopes to show that her ancestor didn't betray Murkmire. Unfortunately, the caves may also be home to the monstrous voriplasm, Wuju-Ka.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3583",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Covenant troops are massing to the north of Fort Arand. They don't have the numbers for a frontal assault, but Fort Captain Hjolm believes they may be coordinating an attack with a second flank.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2920",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Dragonclaw for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2673",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Rayles for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6239",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Teeth of Sithis, a pair of ancient xanmeer temples, has been overtaken by the servants of its heretical, former high priestess, Shuxaltsei. She has taken the custodians of the Teeth captive and is sacrificing them in some profane blood rite.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3591",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Covenant troops have killed Captain Hjolm of Fort Arand, and they're threatening the safety of the recruits within the fort. Captain Llaari hatched a plan to respond to the threat.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3627",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Gar has been taken captive by the Goblins, and Fafnyr was wounded in the fighting. The Nord warrior seeks revenge against the hated Goblins and their spider allies.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4844",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a strange sapling that spoke to me, confused about its own ability to think and feel. It has vague memories of walking and a nearby cave. I agreed to help the sapling get some answers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4135",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The people of Riften have been brought inside their shattered walls. While Sinmur is gone, however, Riften's people may face other threats.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4304",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Gorgath Deadeye is after a Redguard called Varnedo. Rumor has Varnedo in Ivarstead and Gorgath will give me a reward for tracking him down.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6129",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tindoria, a High Elf artist, has hired me to acquire a list of rare art supplies for her next masterpiece.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4638",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found a letter indicating a man named Fadeel is tricking people into traveling to Sandblown Mine to provide \"fresh meat\" for the snake, Huzal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3903",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Arch-Mage Valeyn believes I'm here to help protect the Academy against some unnamed threat. While he determines what this threat is, he asked me to help him with another matter.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3908",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Arch-Mage Valeyn thinks his visions are somehow connected to the evil Magistrix Vox. Unfortunately, before he could learn more, something blocked his magic.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4493",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A note posted at the entrance to Knife Ear Grotto by a scholar warns of danger inside.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3809",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rigurt the Brash, leader of the Expedition for Nord Cultural Exchange, has asked for my assistance. I've agreed to trade a Nord book, clothes, and relic for similar Dark Elf items.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4163",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ganthis, an agent of Shadowfen's leadership, asked me to help Vicecanon Hrondar investigate a number of murders in Stormhold.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3840",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Shadowfen's Vicecanon Hrondar sent Saervild Steel-Wind to Bogmother's ruins to collect Argonian relics.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3828",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dominion slaughtered the Argonians living in a small hamlet in Shadowfen. Only one remains alive to take his vengeance.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3827",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mystery surrounds Forsaken Hamlet. An Argonian tree-minder lies murdered at the edge of her village.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4553",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Erranenen lost his lute in a riddle game with Akishan.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3585",["level"]="7",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A Nord commander named Holgunn asked me to help defend Davon's Watch.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6403",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Order of the New Moon plans to attack Pridehome, a reclusive temple dedicated to the worship of Alkosh. The Dragonguard is determined to stop the cult's assault and uncover the motives behind the attack.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6436",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Senchal job broker, Guybert Flaubert, has a client who wants some lilies planted in Moonlit Cove as a tribute to her late grandmother.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6423",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A territorial guardian watches over a temple of Meridia in Southern Elsweyr. I agreed to help kill the guardian and gather some temple dust.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6186",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Adonatus Varian, member of the Silver Dawn, has tasked me with taking down the werewolf pack within Moon Hunter Keep. I'll need to work my way through the keep in order to reach the pack's leader, Vykosa.",["poiIndex"]="62",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6187",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Moon Hunter Keep.",["poiIndex"]="62",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4597",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Ancient Keepers, sworn to imprison the spirit of High Kinlord Rilis, have taken to forming Daedric pacts. Keeper Cirion has asked for help in defeating the corrupting force of Rilis, but will require fighting the Keepers directly.",["poiIndex"]="61",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5014",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Ring of Daggers has tracked down a war criminal named Gerard Althen, who once served as King Ranser's spymaster. He's hiding somewhere in Sanguine Barrows and I've agreed to find him and bring him out.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4955",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a journal that belonged to a thief called Nedras the Sly. He apparently turned to crime in order to support his ailing sister in Northpoint.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4524",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the journal of a young man named Vareldur in the mine called Del's Claim. He died trying to stop the Heritance from killing the miners there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3085",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Glademist for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3856",["level"]="8",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Guildmaster of the Fighters Guild wants me to perform a task for her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3737",["level"]="11",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Walks-in-Ash told me of an assault force landing in the Ashlands west of Ebonheart. She's asked me to make for the land coral maze known as Vivec's Antlers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3927",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The city of Riften has been devastated by Sinmur's assault. The town guard is overwhelmed trying to help all the refugees. They're asking everyone to help with the recovery effort.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4267",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Rothalens have fallen on hard times. Sarisa has designs on Bar-Neeus's stall in the central market.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5038",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a soldier outside a spider cave in Stonefalls. She's suffering from a spider bite she received while trying to search the Hollow.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3671",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Covenant has taken Fort Virak, a vital strategic chokepoint.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3633",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've infiltrated the ruins beneath Fort Virak. Walks-in-Ash asked me to help secure our foothold within the fort's main courtyard.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3634",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Fort Virak is ours. All that remains is to kill General Serien, the leader of the Covenant forces in Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3635",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Holgunn warned me that Tanval will likely try to release the second Brother of Strife from Tormented Spire. To ascend the spire I'll need to speak to the grandmaster of House Dres in Kragenmoor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3695",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Tanval Indoril has fled towards the Tormented Spire with the Coral Heart in hand. He wants to unleash Sadal, the Brother of Strife, from his imprisonment. Kragenmoor's Grandmaster Omin Dres is the only one who can allow me access to the mountain.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3789",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Laughs-at-All is struggling to understand humor. He heard a rumor about a sacred Dark Elf performance from the distant past.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3696",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've discovered where Grandmaster Omin Dres' son is being held captive. The Vanguard is holding his son, Sen, in the tombs west of Kragenmoor.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3788",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The grandmaster of House Dres wants revenge against the Vanguard troops outside Kragenmoor. He's commanded me to slay their leader.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6414",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Skald-King dispatched a party of sword-thanes to investigate unnatural storms swirling around Icereach. Alas, a coven of witches killed most of the warriors. I must venture into the aged keep, kill the witches within, and search for survivors.",["poiIndex"]="59",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3698",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The grandmaster of House Dres has given me a key that should see me past the wards at Tormented Spire. Now all that remains is to make my way there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3826",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Tanval Indoril is inside the Tormented Spire working to unleash the Brother of Strife. Tanval's Vanguard holds the approach. If we don't stop Tanval, he'll unleash Sadal and destroy Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3837",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="With Tanval's help, we've lowered the final ward guarding the prison of Sadal, the Brother of Strife. The mages who originally imprisoned Sadal linger on the Tormented Spire as spirits, angered by Tanval's ritual.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5504",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dragonstar Caravan Company's job broker, Guruzug, has tasked me with traveling to Argent Mine to slay werewolves. A wealthy client will pay handsomely for their skins.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5518",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The laborers helping to rebuild Orsinium need supplies, specifically fresh meat. The hills and valleys of Wrothgar are typically filled with beasts to hunt, but their numbers are dwindling due to poaching. I must help feed the city's workers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3868",["level"]="14",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've accomplished great deeds with Tanval Indoril, Holgunn, and Walks-in-Ash. We've returned Tanval's Vanguard to the Ebonheart Pact, and convinced the spirits of Tormented Spire to open Sadal's prison.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5035",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lieutenant Slonn led a team of scholars to Pinepeak Caverns to awaken the spirit of Hakra, one of the five hundred companions, but the team hasn't returned.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4508",["level"]="5",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A drunk named Shazeem seems to have lost his memory. He offered to sell me a trained monkey, claiming it can find buried treasure.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4466",["level"]="4",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4344",["level"]="7",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Captain Kaleen wants me to locate Crafty Lerisa and convince her to join in on the heist.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4514",["level"]="7",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Captain Kaleen's cabin girl, Nicolene, informed me that Kaleen's crew is ready to start the heist as soon as I'm done recruiting.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3980",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A researcher named Nila feels terrible about her colleague's capture. The Worm Cult was torturing him at the far end of the cavern.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3978",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Netapatuu and his colleagues came to Pinepeak Caverns to consult with the spirit of Hakra, one of Ysgramor's Companions. Worm Cultists attacked and drove them out. The cultists cannot be allowed to gain control of Hakra's spirit.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3981",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Netapatuu fears the Worm Cult may try to enslave Valdur's spirit, much as they tried with Hakra's.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4631",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note of debt in Coldrock Diggings.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6276",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Overseer Shiralas asked if I could head into the swamp and look for her missing wife, Varona, and their pet Drooler.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6282",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a grave-stake lying next to a note indicating that it was stolen. I should find out who to return the grave-stake to.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6281",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An eccentric Argonian by the name of Listens-By-Smell asked me to help her fulfill a dream of hers, somehow involving creatures called swamp jellies.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5051",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I ran into Blademaster Qariar in Northpoint's back alleys. He's hunting down the remaining vampires that were working with Lady Lleraya Montclair.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4551",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While wading through the swamp, I stumbled into a cloud of roaming poison gas and passed out. Two Imperials rescued me and asked me to help them clean it up.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5788",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5822",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Glenumbra.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4556",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In the depths of Atanaz Ruins I came across the corpse of Gordag, cooked in his armor by a beast that dwells there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4560",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zahra, a Khajiit investigating Gandranen Ruins, has asked for my assistance.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4554",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The drunken cook, Angwe, is in trouble. She bet her hunter friend that she'd collect ingredients from beasts all over Shadowfen and cook him a feast in Hissmir. Now sober, she is afraid to venture out into the fen, for fear of these same creatures.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3678",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Due to archaic rules, Captain Henaamo of the Aldmeri Dominion is allowed to undergo sacred Argonian trials at Hissmir. Success will allow him to commune with the Hist. To determine his true plans, I must pass the trials myself.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3680",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Someone stole several relics from a cart in Hissmir. I offered to help Wareem find the culprit.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3679",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I completed the Trials of the Burnished Scales at Hissmir, which allows me to commune with the Hist. Doing so will give me insight why Captain Henaamo, a Dominion soldier, would undertake the trials.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4388",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Breton in the middle of the swamps of Shadowfen. She seems to be lost.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4557",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In the depths of Broken Tusk, I found a Daedric Urn surrounded by bodies. One of them stirred when I took the urn.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3732",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Aldmeri Dominion has set up a staging area south of Hissmir in a fishing village called Murkwater.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3849",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bezeer believes his mother's remains lie in White Rose Prison, away from the swamp waters. Her spirit is unable to return to the Hist.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3822",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Argonian outside Mud Tree Village asked me to find his brother, Miharil. He was in the nearby mine when Goblins overran it.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3824",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While in the Goblin camp, I found a Nord corpse clutching a runestone that bears the name \"Hodmar Iron-Kettle.\"",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4390",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Teegya, a traveling Argonian merchant, lost her guar and a valuable ruby to crocodiles in the swamp. She's too hurt to round them up, so she asked me to search for the ruby and her favorite guar, Wades-In-Muck.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3712",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A traveling merchant named Daeril fell prey to Worm Cult necromancers camped below Stillrise Village. His guards were killed, and their souls are now trapped in animus geodes throughout the cultists' camp.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3685",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Kothringi from Stillrise Village who told me Worm Cult necromancers plague their village.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3709",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After returning the soul gem array, Chieftain Suhlak made me the arbiter over the fate of Stillrise Village. Destroying the soul gem array will allow the villagers to die, but preserving it will trap them in their lifeless state.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4391",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A researcher and his apprentice are experimenting with an amulet that protects the wearer from wamasu lightning.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6269",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Erilthel has requested that I help save her boss Seeks-the-Dark by completing a gauntlet held by the Blackguards. I'll have to make my way through the many foes of Blackrose Prison and emerge victorious.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4726",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've reached the siege range. Bugbesh told me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Marc and Jaleel to learn more about the weapons.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4727",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Aurorelle Varin says there is much more for me to learn about the war in Cyrodiil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4152",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After events in Shadowfen, Vicecanon Heita-Meen and I must travel to Eastmarch, in Skyrim.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5479",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accomplished much since coming to Wrothgar. Now, it seems Curator Umutha has one final request from the House of Orsimer Glories.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5466",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="It seems that Raynor Vanos used the Dwarven power core I acquired for him in Zthenganaz to rebuild and modify a Dwarven Sphere. The construct went crazy and knocked out Kireth, and when she woke up both it and her brother were missing.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4316",["level"]="34",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Three friends have drunkenly wandered into the catacombs beneath Windhelm after having a good time at the Konunleikar. They won't leave the catacombs until they're reunited, but it's not safe for them to search the tunnels alone.",["poiIndex"]="37",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4322",["level"]="35",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In the Hall of the Dead beneath Windhelm I met Malana. She plans to gain favor in King Jorunn's court by eliminating Lodorr, an ancient necromancer entombed in the Merethic Era.",["poiIndex"]="37",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2871",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Faregyl Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3101",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5221",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6160",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dangerous Worm Cult tomes are circulating throughout Summerset. The Office of Divine Prosecution wants some of these forbidden books recovered and disposed of.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6087",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Office of Divine Prosecution tasked me with killing Keelsplitterâ€”a massive sea adder bred by the Sea Elves to hunt down High Elf ships. They also need me to recover intelligence logs from the ships Keelsplitter destroyed.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6202",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Battlereeve Tanerline charged me with finding allies to attack the abyssal geysers and destroy the pearls that power them before the Sea Sload cabal's plan to sink Summerset comes to fruition.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2638",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene asked for warriors to help capture the Elder Scroll of Mnem.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6085",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Divine Prosecution has requested I defeat the gryphons Haeliata and Nagravia. I'll also need to collect their feathers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6086",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Office of Divine Prosecution suffered a number of casualties to a creature called Graveld in Sil-Var-Woad.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6158",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Divine Prosecution has tasked me to recover several stolen relics from a group known as the Sagacians. In addition, I'll need to collect any plans I find outlining the group's movements.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6082",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Divine Prosecution has tasked me with taking coral crab eggs from the reef between Lillandril and the Corgrad Wastes for the Sapiarchs to inspect for signs of corruption.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3097",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Roebeck for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3134",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6152",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Justiciar Tanorian wants me to recover articles of faith on behalf of the cult of Phynaster.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4723",["level"]="38",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've reached the siege range. Adalmor advised me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Looks-Forward and Lirtis to learn more about the weapons.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4724",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Galsi Mavani says I have more to learn about the conflict in Cyrodiil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4420",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In the confusion of battle, Sylvian Herius left a family heirloom in the Imperial-held cathedral across the river.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2875",["level"]="39",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Bloodmayne Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4255",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I arrived in the city of Vulkhel Guard, gateway to Auridon. Security is tight as Queen Ayrenn, the new leader of the Aldmeri Dominion, prepares to make a public appearance.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4256",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="At the request of the captain of the Vulkhel Watch, I've been running errands all over Auridon's port city. I even helped deal with a criminal named Fasion who claimed that Captain Astanya is working with a group called the Veiled Heritance.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4211",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Queen Ayrenn asked me to join her at the ancient site Tanzelwil where she must commune with the dead. She's worried there may be â€¦ complications.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4217",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Queen Ayrenn seeks to perform rituals honoring her ancestors. When she arrived at Tanzelwil, however, she found the spirits angered and violent.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4222",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Queen Ayrenn must perform the final ritual at Tanzelwil in the ancestral crypts. Malicious spirits plague this holy shrine and the traitorous Norion lurks somewhere in the shadows.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4997",["level"]="45",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Kailstig the Axe has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5928",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Ebernanit and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5911",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the dire ash beetle called Ash-Eater.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6040",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Razgurug requested I gather gather the husks of Clockwork trees for an adhesive. I'll also need to collect artificial coal to help keep the sap warm.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4786",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nellor, an innkeeper in Redfur Trading Post, informed me of bandits who kidnapped his daughter Larasel. He asked me to bring her home safely.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4954",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met an old scholar near the Ayleid ruins who came to power a crystal for his research, but found the ruins swarming with Worm Cultists.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4857",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Verandis completed his research and discovered that his missing memories lead to an ancient ruin in the Lorkrata Hills. He needs my help to discover the secret hidden within the ruins.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4058",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I arrived in Eastmarch, in the Nord city of Windhelm. The place bustles with revelers as a celebration honoring the Skald-King is underway.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4059",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Thane Mera has named me the Champion of Windhelm and wants me to enter the Footrace of the Nine Holds.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4060",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Thane Mera, enraged by the death of the racer Hadring, demands that the assassins pay for this crime. She wants me, Windhelm's Champion, to deal with thisâ€”personally.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4061",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Fildgor, King Jorunn's exiled brother, has returned to Skyrim. Nords from the Stormfist clan, loyal to Fildgor, have infiltrated the Konunleikar to get close to King Jorunn.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4018",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Giants have attacked the village of Lower Yorgrim, destroying everything in their path.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4043",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After giants and wolves overran the village of Lower Yorgrim, the survivors found shelter in a tiny fishing camp outside the village walls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4037",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Yraldar Snowpeak was wounded trying to drive the Stormfist soldiers away from the meadery. He wants their leader, an Orc named Kazok, dead and his head on a pike. He asked for my help.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4034",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Stormfist soldiers ransacked Voljar's Meadery and slaughtered the familyâ€”all because they wanted free mead. Haraldar's wife was one of the Voljars killed in the attack. He wants to reopen the meadery, and he recruited his four brothers to help.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4149",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rigurt the Brash has been named Master of Ceremonies for the celebration of King Jorunn's anniversary. Rigurt has many organizational duties to attend to and needs a little help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4197",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A runner arrived from Fort Morvunskar, an installation to the west. Thane Mera believes Fildgor's forces have launched an attack against the fort.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4062",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A renegade clan of Nords known as the Stormfists launched a surprise attack against Fort Morvunskar.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4071",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The orders from Fildgor Orcthane suggest that the Stormfists are after something precious in the royal tomb. The spirit of Queen Nurnhilde and Lieutenant Koruni both asked me to return the relics. While I'm at it, I'll see what else is going on.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4118",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Draugr have spilled from the barrow beneath Bonestrewn Crest. Now they roam the area, attacking the living.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4177",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lieutenant Koruni asked me to deliver a dispatch detailing Fort Morvunskar's status to Thane Oda Wolf-Sister at Fort Amol.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4158",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Stormfist spies have used Daedric alchemy to infiltrate Fort Amol. The King and the Pact delegates are in danger. I need to convince someone that the threat is real before it's too late.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4166",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Thane Harvald want Lord Vurlop and I to go into the keep and check on King Jorunn. We need to make sure that the King and his war council are safe.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4205",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Trolls overran the town of Darkwater Crossing and now the Argonians who lived there have taken refuge in a nearby cave.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4075",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I met a frightened young woman. Her and her friend were attacked by monsters on their way back to Windhelm.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4106",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Valeric believes vampires don't have to be monsters. He wants my help to stop his father, Majorn, who plans to create an army of bloodfiends.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4203",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Thane Oda Wolf-Sister believes that the Ternion monks might be able to heal King Jorunn. But their complex rituals require special components.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4115",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Jorunn the Skald-King has been poisoned. Now he lies in an eternal slumber. The Ternion monks, who revere the Three Old Gods, attempt to cure him. But time is running out.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4123",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Dreamwalker is lost in King Jorunn's nightmares. I must enter the Dreamstride and try to rescue both of them before the Daedric poison kills the King.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3086",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Ash for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2841",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Rayles for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5925",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Assarnatamat and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5918",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've been hired by researchers to defeat a Hunger that's protecting a ruin they wish to study. I'm also required to gather relics scattered around the ruin.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5961",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A faction of bandits in a cavern called Zainsipilu are attempting to grow moon-sugar grass. I've been asked to re-direct their methods through misinformation.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2893",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2934",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Rayles Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6216",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture the towns of Vlastarus, Cropsford, and Bruma for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3216",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help regain Fort Aleswell for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3226",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Roebeck for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2780",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Castle Faregyl for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3083",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Warden for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5962",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Through unknown breeding and feeding practices, the kwama miners of Matus-Akin have been developing a new, more aggressive breed of kwama. Though this breed needs to be contained, the Temple also wishes to learn more about their breeding methods.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5916",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dubdil Alar's apprentice has hired me to stop one of her former master's experiments. I'm also required to gather his research notes for further study.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5113",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Nerien'eth the lich has returned to the Crypt of Hearts to find the ghosts he imprisoned there arrayed against him.",["poiIndex"]="58",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4526",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found a strange glowing artifact from the age of the Altmeri deep within the ruins of Bewan.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6141",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rigurt the Brash, an ambassador from the Nord Cultural Exchange, came to Summerset to broker peace. Unfortunately, he can't get an audience with the Proxy Queen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5923",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The miniature model of Vvardenfell is nearly complete. One section remains missing, which Librarian Bradyn believes is the key to finding the lost Library of Andule.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5907",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the deadly nix-ox called Great Zexxin.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5924",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Yasammidan and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4958",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Lleraya Montclair and her forces have taken control of Northpoint. They've sealed the gates and locked out the legitimate city guards. But Baron Dorell has a plan to liberate Northpoint. It just requires a small group willing to infiltrate the city.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4972",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="We found a way to sneak into the sealed city of Northpointâ€”a tunnel used by smugglers and black marketeers. Now we need to head inside and find a way to free the city from Lleraya Montclair's grasp.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4839",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While exploring Hildune's Secret Refuge, I found a journal written by Nadafa. It tells the story of how she was seduced by a vampire. The journal mentions that her husband, Giran, works in Northpoint at the cemetery and lives in the fishing village.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5024",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="We put an end to Reezal-Jul and Lleraya. Now we need to deal with Baron Montclair. But to reach Montclair in his citadel atop the Doomcrag, we first need to find a way through the Shrouded Pass.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4884",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="We've taken control of the Shrouded Pass and the way to the Doomcrag is open. The time has come to make our final assault and reach Montclair and  the cursed relic known as the Lightless Remnant.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4840",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Mages Guild novice named Anenya just inside the Erokii Ruins. She was sent here on an assignment to recover a relic called the Tear of Anurraame, but she can't carry it out. I agreed to recover the relic and bring it back to Shornhelm.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4936",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Now that the threat to Rivenspire has been dealt with, there's still the matter of crowning a true ruler for the region.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4822",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Gasteau Chamrond knows how to escape the structure I've fallen into. He'll help me get out if I lend him my strength.",["poiIndex"]="39",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2730",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6175",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alamar has lost several bottles of wine while on a winery tour. He hired me to find and collect them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5522",["level"]="23",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult has established a foothold in Wrothgar and seeks to summon a beast called Zandadunoz the Reborn. The king's servant, Arzorag, demands that I disrupt their scheme.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5515",["level"]="23",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The vile sorcerer, Gorlar the Dark, continues to terrorize the people of Wrothgar. He has raised countless Orcs as undead thralls and trapped their spirits in Mundus. I must set their spirits free and put this necromancer to the sword.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3333",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Sentinel Docks have been overrun with undead and the guards don't appear to be doing anything in response. I told Captain Marck I would try to find out what's going on.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2130",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="An army of undead swarmed from the sea and attacked the Sentinel Docks. Watch Captain Zafira has asked me to inform King Fahara'jad.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2915",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to capture Fort Warden for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2959",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Chalman Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2958",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Dragonclaw Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5007",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Something strange is happening inside Shroud Hearth Barrow that is frightening the villagers of Ivarstead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5747",["level"]="10",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A Herald has come with tales of a dire threat in the distant land of Craglorn.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2748",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Lumbermill  for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2697",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2726",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2702",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2917",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Glademist for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2935",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2728",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Chalman Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5756",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="A giant object fell from the heavens when the Mage constellation disappeared. Sara Benele is examining the object, which she calls the \"Mage's Staff.\" She believes the staff is unstable and needs my help to fix it.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5342",["level"]="46",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Daedra have occupied the White-Gold Tower, and I have agreed to help Moth Priest Terran Arminus retrieve an Elder Scroll left inside the Tower Library.",["poiIndex"]="105",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5523",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Khajiit named Birkhu the Bold has stumbled upon a number of dangerous Dwarven mechanisms, including the massive Dwarven Centurion, Nyzchaleft. These machines pose a threat to Wrothgar and must be dealt with.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6037",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Razgurug requested I gather oil from the water within Clockwork City. I'll also need to gather supplies to create more tools for future collecting.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6039",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Razgurug requested I gather the metal strands weaved within cloths in Clockwork City. I also need to collect components for an artificial lodestone that is used in harvesting the metal strands.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2639",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Covenant soldiers are seeking the Elder Scroll of Ghartok.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5230",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6038",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Razgurug requested I gather a strange material called flash stone which can be turned into a useful powder. I'll also need to collect metal pellets that help in the grinding process.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4533",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a message within Cryptwatch Fort indicating that the Red Rooks are worried the Bloodthorn cult will turn against them. The note also contains recipes for salves and potions to combat the Bloodthorns' festering magic.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4531",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a journal within the Mines of Khuras. It contained a message addressed to Odette Vinielle.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4529",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A note in Ilessan Tower has informed me that the Red Rooks are amassing resources for their allies. It also mentioned an attack on a manor north of Deleyn's Mill.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4834",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While exploring the Tribulation Crypt, I encountered a ghost that beckoned me deeper into the tomb. The ghost led me to an ancient sword engraved with the following message: \"Marcelle Stenric of Shornhelm.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4967",["level"]="31",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="The Khajiit, Turuk Redclaws, has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4692",["level"]="5",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Awash in a sea of rats, Laughing Moons Plantation is in dire need of assistance. Juranda-ra asked me to help deal with the infestation.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2146",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Prince Azah says the necromancers of the Withered Hand are tunneling into the Impervious Vault to steal powerful relics known as the Ansei Wards. We must try to stop them.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2408",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Withered Hand stole the Ansei Wards, ancient swords that protect Alik'r from necromancy. King Fahara'jad has asked me to enlist the aid of the Ash'abah, a tribe of dishonored warriors who fight the undead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4672",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The chief of the Ash'abah and many of the tribe's warriors have been poisoned, most likely by the Withered Hand. I agreed to help Talia at-Marimah gather ingredients for an antidote.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4686",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="On his deathbed, the chief of the Ash'abah says he has foreseen that I must join the tribe and defeat the Withered Hand. I must participate in an initiation ritual to become an Ash'abah.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5392",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards, an agreement to deliver Blacksmith goods to an interested organization.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4366",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Battlereeve Urcelmo has asked that I meet with Razum-dar near the town of Mathiisen. Raz is apparently investigating more threads in the Veiled Heritance plot.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4293",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I'm working with Razum-dar, at the town of Mathiisen. He's looking into reports of the Veiled Heritance in the area for Queen Ayrenn.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4294",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I uncovered evidence linking important community members in Mathiisen to the Veiled Heritance. Now Raz has asked me to take the fight to them directly.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4368",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I have purged the Veiled Heritance from Mathiisen. Now I should meet up with Razum-dar in Skywatch to learn what other plans the Veiled Heritance has.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4409",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Firtoril has offered me a chance to enter the frog race. If my frog wins, we'll split the prize.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4330",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I arrived in Skywatch to find a festival in honor of the High Kinlady Estre in full swing.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4331",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've been taken to the secret island stronghold of the Veiled Heritance. If I can pass their trials, I may be able to discover the true leader behind the Veil.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4345",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I'm now a full member of the Veiled Heritance. I've been told of a grand hall where their leadership council meets. And they are meeting with the Veiled Queen herself!",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6193",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="I met a commoner named Vandoril in Alinor who's had troubling dreams about the city of Cloudrest. He's requested I seek out his mother Belarin and ensure her safety.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6382",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Senche-raht necromancer named Thannar the Graveprowler stalks the ruins southwest of Rimmen, urging the corpses buried there to rise from their graves. Left unchecked, his ranks of undead followers could swell.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3138",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6404",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="With Ra'khajin defeated and the Mask of Alkosh in our possession, Sai Sahan is determined to defeat Laatvulon once and for all. It's time to make our final stand against the Order of the New Moon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3098",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Brindle for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4673",["level"]="7",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="There's a crisis at Windcatcher Plantation. Something is wrong with their Great Tree, and the locals believe it has something to do with the tree's roots, which can be accessed from a cave below it.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3104",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3103",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3139",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5770",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="A devout knight of the Divines discovered that the dead have awakened in the depths of Skyreach Catacombs. If the legend of Virmaril is true, then a powerful Elven necromancer could be the source of the trouble.",["poiIndex"]="35",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3154",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4664",["level"]="6",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note in a smuggler camp. A young Khajiit was captured and taken to Hazak's Hollow by the Crosstree Bandits.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4621",["level"]="5",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Maormer seek to prevent the Dominion from establishing themselves on Khenarthi's Roost. They've launched a full-scale attack on Cat's Eye Quay.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4818",["level"]="11",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After defeating the Maormer assault on Khenarthi's Roost, Razum-dar has asked me to report to Watch Captain Astanya in the Auridon city of Vulkhel Guard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2980",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4630",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note on the body of an Ebonheart Pact soldier. It mentions an egg brother named Bosekus in the town of Cropsford.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5605",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a bounty to investigate unnatural phenomena preventing the excavation of Tribune's Folly.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5661",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5791",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Eastmarch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5825",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Malabal Tor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5654",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5609",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bards and entertainers are failing to pay their dues and badmouthing the guild's members. The Thieves Guild wants to remind them why they pay protection. I should look for games, musical instruments, or children's toys, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5718",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I received a contract from the Speaker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5669",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5784",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5816",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Auridon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5726",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I received a contract from the Speaker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5625",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4930",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Teeba-Ja was a member of the Bitterhand Bandits, but when they became more violent, she decided to leave. She wants to start a new life in Shornhelm.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3228",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Black Boot for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5958",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Camonna Tong are thought to be active in the illegal slave trade at Khartag Point. Their efforts need to be disrupted.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4916",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Short-Tail is distraught. Her adorable pet, Puddles, ran away, and she's afraid that the little creature is lost.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6151",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Roguzog, an Orcish visitor to Summerset, wants to settle a grievance with a High Elf named Lirendel. We'll have to learn all the rules and customs of High Elf dueling before Roguzog can get bloody satisfaction.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6114",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rinyde has asked me to find her brother Larydel and stop him from joining the House of Reveries. I must audition as well in order to figure out who he is.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6139",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tableau is an artist fascinated by the outcasts known as hulkynd, and wishes to meet one. She's requested I help arrange a meeting with one who was seen outside of Rellenthil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5749",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="I met Ibrula, a friend of the Star-Gazers who is trying to get into a ruined temple called the Seeker's Archive. She hopes to discover information inside that will help defeat the Celestials.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5766",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met an Iron Orc shaman who had been banished by a younger rival. What's more, this rival, named Agganor, seems to be responsible for the Iron Orc and Scaled Court alliance. The old shaman wants me to avenge him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5765",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Iron Orcs, who usually don't take prisoners, have started abducting travelers near the Valley of Scars. I encountered a caravan master who survived an attack, though a number of his guards were dragged off by the Orcs.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5767",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="The scholar Nendirume warned me that the Scaled Court has taken over the ruined city of Skyreach. She believes they're searching Skyreach Hold for more of the nirncrux element, which they refer to as \"the blood of Nirn.\"",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5772",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="Outside the ancient ruins of Skyreach Pinnacle, I met a member of the Scaled Court. He told me that the Court accidentally released creatures from magical wards the Nedes set up long ago. He plans to reestablish the wards, but he needs help.",["poiIndex"]="34",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5136",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I have agreed to help a Daedra called Lyranth attack the Imperial City Prison, which has been overrun by others of her kind. I can free the mortal prisoners held within, but my goal is to eliminate the Daedric invaders.",["poiIndex"]="104",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5531",["level"]="14",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A thief named Quen needs a partner for a difficult job. I took her up on the offer.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3225",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Faregyl for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2637",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Grand Warlord Dortene wants the Elder Scroll of Altadoon captured and brought into Covenant hands.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2640",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Covenant forces are gathering to capture the Elder Scroll of Chim.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2782",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Castle Brindle for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5540",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="To prove myself to the Dark Brotherhood, Speaker Terenus wants me to murder the Imperial noble named Quintus Jarol.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5542",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I gained access to the Dark Brotherhood Sanctuary and met the Matron of this chapter, Astara Caerellius. She welcomed me into the family and suggested I meet the rest of my brothers and sisters in the guild.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5708",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I agreed to be initiated into the ways of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5595",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Recent lectures in Kvatch by the Grand Sermonizer of Akatosh and her priests paint the Dark Brotherhood as powerless pretenders not to be feared. Astara wants the Grand Sermonizer dealt withâ€”permanently.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5725",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I received a contract from the Speaker.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5634",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Listener sent a mysterious Dark Elf to the Sanctuary to deliver a strange tome by the statue of the Night Mother. She mentioned that it was meant for the killer who tasted death.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5909",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the deadly greater hive golem they call Writhing Sveeth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5926",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Maelkashishi and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5910",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the giant mudcrab called Mother Jagged-Claw.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5927",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Ashurnabitashpi and gather as many historic relics as I can find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5913",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the powerful kagouti called King Razor-Tusk.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5820",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Eastmarch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5908",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the deadly nix-hound called Tarra-Suj.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5640",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The guild has had laborers around their territory failing to pay their dues and badmouthing its members. The Thieves Guild wants to remind them why they pay protection. I should look for smithing, fishing, or other tools, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4682",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I have a doctor's bag belonging to Hilio Attius, who may be in Cheydinhal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4875",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted the Fighters Guild contract Arkas offered.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3787",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a pair of Argonians, former slaves. They want revenge upon Betina Volek, the last surviving descendant of the family that once owned them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4459",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I used the key to search the House Dres farmhouses outside Mournhold. I found a suspicious-looking trap door hidden under a rug. Naryu thinks we'll discover a connection to the Maulborn down there.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3817",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A large Maulborn force used the sewers to sneak into Mournhold. I need to find them before they can complete their nefarious plan.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3703",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The monastery of Muth Gnaar was attacked by the Vereansu, a violent tribe of Ashlanders. The peaceful monks were caring for the afflicted using an ancient relic called the Tear of Saint Veloth when the Ashlanders attacked.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3874",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Dwarven device fills a chamber deep within the ruins of Bthanual. Kireth has repaired it. Beams of light now shine through prisms set around the room.",["poiIndex"]="39",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3663",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="House Dres raiders and Dwarven constructs attacked a caravan carrying valuable cargo. The House Hlaalu noble who sponsored this caravan will want it back.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3721",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met an artificer who's trying to learn more about the mysterious rod that was used to control Dwarven constructs from Mzithumz.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3661",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I came across the wreckage of a trade caravan on the road between Mournhold and Narsis. Attacks on caravans don't usually occur this close to Mournhold, and the presence of a Dwarven construct makes this incident even more unusual.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3966",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Magister Vox stole an item of power from the Tribunal Templeâ€”the hammer known as Veloth's Judgment. She fled east, away from Mournhold. Almalexia asked me to track her down before she gains the full power of the artifact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5610",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The guild has had laborers around their territory failing to pay their dues and badmouthing its members. The Thieves Guild wants to remind them why they pay protection. I should look for smithing, fishing, or other tools, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3858",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Sees-All-Colors has had Doshia's journal translated. From it she believes she may have discovered information relating to the mysterious Mortuum Vivicus.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3885",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Guildmaster Sees-All-Colors has plans to make use of the crystal and tome we found in the depths of Mzeneldt.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3898",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Council of Province Generals has ordered an investigation into the death of the former Guildmaster, Jofnir Iceblade.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3973",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Fighters Guild has sentenced Sees-All-Colors to death for the murder of Jofnir Iceblade.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4476",["level"]="30",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Now that I've recruited at least one of the people Kaleen wanted, we can pull off her heist whenever I'm ready.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4864",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a Knight of St. Pelin in the Crypt of the Exiles who died while on an important quest. She sought to recover a sacred Redguard artifact, the Memory Stone of Makela Leki, and return it to a Redguard scholar.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4210",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While in Silsailen, I learned that the imposters have taken real Auridon Marines captive.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4208",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The town of Silsailen is under attack by imposters disguised as First Auridon Marines. The townspeople suspect these men and woman are a part of a group called the Veiled Heritance.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4209",["level"]="18",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Teldur has kidnapped Canonreeve Valano and taken him into the manor.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4219",["level"]="19",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Maormer pirates took the lighthouse at South Beacon and are signalling more pirate ships to come into port. If they're not stopped, they'll have the numbers they need to move on the port of Vulkhel Guard.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4441",["level"]="19",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I stumbled onto an investigator named Pirondil being threatened by an unknown Altmer assailant in a Goblin cave. He's enlisted me to help get to the bottom of the situation.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4450",["level"]="19",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I ran into a captive Khajiit in Toothmaul Gully. I've opted to free him and entertain his offer.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4272",["level"]="20",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a lost member of the Queen's entourage near the entrance to a hidden Vale. She told me that her fellow entourage members have been taken. A mad mage apparently holds them in the Vale.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4223",["level"]="19",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Strange stones emanating necromantic energy have appeared on the sacred grounds of Tanzelwil. Priestess Langwe believes they might be tied to the disturbed demeanor of the Ancestral Spirits.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4264",["level"]="21",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The town of Phaer is beset by a mysterious plague. The town alchemist, Hendil, has taken steps to treat the ill.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4266",["level"]="21",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Velatosse is suspicious about the plague's origins. She's asked me to look into the source of this mysterious illness.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4038",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Iron-Claws thinks he's found a way to use the otherwise docile netch against the Daggerfall Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4024",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Argonian named Esqoo lost most of his guar herd. They were spooked by scary noises in the fields behind Dhalmora. He wants me to collect the missing ones.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4022",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Covenant sent an advance force into Bal Foyen. They're destroying the fields behind Dhalmora.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4023",["level"]="25",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="We've landed safely. Captain Rana is going to muster the remaining Bleakrock villagers and the people of Dhalmora. She wants me to ensure the fires are lit in the nearby watchtower so we can warn Davon's Watch, the port city in Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4051",["level"]="27",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I should head to Davon's Watch, so I can ensure the troops have been warned about the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3860",["level"]="29",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A shady character named Naril Heleran contacted me at Davon's Watch. He said we could both profit if I \"procured\" a rare and expensive bottle of wine for him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4410",["level"]="22",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Neetra's petâ€”a Dwarven constructâ€”has broken down. She wants me to steal parts so that she can repair it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5754",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="I ran into a researcher in the city wing of Shada's Tear who told me that the rest of her research team drank the cursed waters of Shada's Tear and went mad. She asked me to save her friend, Nahlia, who was captured by the mad researchers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5900",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tythis Nirith has come to the Forgotten Wastes searching for his sister, Nevena. It seems she has fallen under the sway of some artifact. I've volunteered to help Tythis find her.",["poiIndex"]="35",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4221",["level"]="23",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In the ruins of Ezduiin, I found an enterprising researcher working with Telenger. She's concerned about the recent appearance of the spirits. She seeks a way to lay them to rest.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4220",["level"]="22",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered a Mages Guild expedition at the ruins of Ezduiin. A scholar named Telenger is in charge.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4327",["level"]="23",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met an Argonian named Delves-Deeply in the ruins of Quendeluun. She's asked me to help me secure her freedom.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4326",["level"]="23",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a mer named Rolancano near the ruin known as Quendeluun. He claims the Veiled Heritance took his daughter. He tracked them to the site.",["poiIndex"]="31",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4362",["level"]="24",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A restless spirit of Castle Rilis named Lisondor has asked me to retrieve his soul from a mad jester's playroom.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4365",["level"]="23",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I revealed High Kinlady Estre is the Veiled Queen. Queen Ayrenn wants me to make sure Dawnbreak is safe for her to continue her campaign.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4355",["level"]="24",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The town of Dawnbreak has been overrun by Daedra. In response, First Auridon Marines have arrived to aid the town.",["poiIndex"]="34",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4338",["level"]="25",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Maormer struck Greenwater Cove, and now lay waste to the town. Auridon troops tried and failed to retake the area, and now await reinforcements before trying again. I've been tasked with reactivating an ancient Aldmeri device on the nearby cliffs.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4408",["level"]="22",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ancalin, an old Altmer woman, asked me to pray at the grave markers of her four children. She hopes my travels around the island will give them some peace.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5702",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="An Argonian Shadowscale named Tsatva-Lan went missing while investigating the lair of a rival group of assassins known as the Silken Ring. His former student, Hides-the-Ashes, asked me to help her track down her mentor and rescue him.",["poiIndex"]="61",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3221",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Keep for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3595",["level"]="31",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Furon is worried that his brother Giron has joined a \"circle of mages.\" He wants my help to understand what they're doing.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4329",["level"]="24",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I arrived at a place called the College of Aldmeri Propriety. One of the students claims this Thalmor training ground heaps hardship and abuse upon the Wood Elf and Khajiit students. She's asked me to investigate.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4301",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Torinaan's strange little relic-keeper worries the holy relics will be corrupted by Daedric energies.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4300",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Torinaan is a holy site dedicated to the Divines. It's been corrupted by Daedra. The loyal clergy there want my aid in cleansing the area.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4411",["level"]="23",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A list of various Veiled Heritance members was found. Egranor is ensuring the people listed are brought to justice.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4055",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Nord soldier Droi burns with fever from a witch's curse. I need to collect a plant called Kyne's Breath to help reduce his fever.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4030",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met two Nord soldiers near the shrine of Kynesgrove. They claim that the shrine has been taken over by evil witches and that the rest of their brigade never returned from the shrine. Now they just wait, afraid to enter the shrine.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4056",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Keepers of the Kynesgrove shrine have become Daedric witches. The loss of their loved ones to war has made them lash out against Kyne. I need to find a way to resolve this.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4096",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I wandered into Cragwallow, a small settlement used by the Skald-King's royal work crews. After a lot of hard work maintaining the roads, they're preparing to throw a party.",["poiIndex"]="34",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4099",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lothgar Steady-Hand was grievously wounded by the creatures that attacked Cragwallow. He appears to be dying.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4138",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jomund and his miners have no idea what to make of the mysterious metal they found. However, Jomund has a friend at Fort Amol who might be able to help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4204",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dralof Waterwalker and his friends bathe in the hot springs south of Wittestadr. Their friend, Grida, went off to gather bath salts for the water, but she never returned.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4588",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Thulvald's logging camp has been overrun by spriggans and trolls. He came to check on his workers and was chased off by the hostile creatures. Now he's worried about his workers and expects that his business is ruined.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4169",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Stormy-Eyes seems to be recovering from the Dreamstride experience. King Jorunn and Prince Irnskar have gone ahead to Jorunn's Stand, a large encampment near Skuldafn.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4069",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Skald-King and the other Ebonheart Pact leaders have established a base at Jorunn's Stand. While the Skald-King recovers, the leaders need to decide how to deal with Fildgor Orcthane.",["poiIndex"]="35",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4070",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The sentry captain, Ula-Reen, keeps the camp secure. She asked me to help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4078",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Dark Elves and Argonians are finally willing to work with Prince Irnskar and meet in a council of war. Now the Prince wants me to convince the Eastmarch thanes to attend the war council as well.",["poiIndex"]="35",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4585",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a Nord in the Bastard's Tomb. He had been captured by the Stormfist Brigade on his way to his sister's wedding. He promised me a reward if I rescued him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4087",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Jorunn wants me to make my way to Skuldafn. He wants to deal with Fildgor Orcthane and then bring the rest of the Pact leaders to the ancient dragonshrine.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4116",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Fildgor the usurper fled to the ancient dragonshrine of Skuldafn to steal Queen Nurnhilde's spirit and force the Crown of Freydis to recognize him. I need to stop him.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4117",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Inside the tombs of Skuldafn, I discovered that Fildgor Orcthane crossed into Sovngarde. To defeat Fildgor, I must follow him there.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4584",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found an exquisitely carved urn within Old Sord's Cave. It appears to belong to Agvar of Windhelm.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4206",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Inside a broken tower, I found a wounded woman named Imwyn Frost-Tree. She told me of a powerful symbol of her faith, the Sigil of Nature's Accord.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4212",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I wandered into a strange rift between the living world and the land of the dead. Here, I met the spirit of Sonya Lastblood, who said that her husband killed her and her three daughters.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4446",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The traveling merchant Sigunn has asked for help retrieving supplies he lost after a giant attack.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3919",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Captain Attiring asked me to seek out Vigrod Wraithbane at Shor's Stone to help him defend it against the Reachmen.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3921",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Some of the miners beneath Shor's Stone still live!",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3920",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've breached the barrier to the mine beneath Shor's Stone. The Reachmen have assaulted the foreman and his crew. I need to find the foreman, Gandis, and figure out what the Reachmen are doing here.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3974",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Reachmen attacked Shor's Stone and brought the giant Sinmur back to life. Now they've overrun Fallowstone Hall, an ancient seat of the Companions. Vigrod wants my help regaining the Hall.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4171",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Skald Svari has been proposed as the next Sage of Fallowstone Hall. She must pray at Fallowstone's shrines to ask the approval of the Companion spirits. I've been asked to accompany her.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3961",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A dying soldier named Melril has asked me to avenge his death.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3959",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Boulderfall Pass has been attacked by Sinmur and the Reachmen. The soldiers defending this area need my help.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4174",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tovisa wants help at Northwind Mine. The Reachmen have taken over the mine and we need to find out why.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4447",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A wanted bandit named Yngrel the Bloody has been causing trouble along the northern road in the Rift. I've been offered a reward to bring him down.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3977",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A scout sent by Centurion Gjakil has found me near Fallowstone Hall. The scout reports Reachmen movement near Vernim Woods.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4448",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Nord woman who's searching for her father in the northern hills of the Rift.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4251",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Widulf, a priest of Kyne, proctors the Trial of Spirit. It apparently involves drinking a somewhat poisonous mead and then running around the island. Widulf assures me the poison will connect me with my inner spirit.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4249",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The warrior Daljari Half-Troll oversees the Trial of the Body, a test of brawn over brain.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4250",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Iroda, a member of the Thane's household, proctors the Trial of the Mind. She's going to pose riddles to me. I need to seek out the answers to each on the island, then return to her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4248",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Geirmund's Hall hosts a festival, and Thane Vofknir is looking for brave souls willing to participate in an epic challenge. Those who pass the tests are named Geirmund's Guardian.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4252",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A bunch of dumb, drunken bards have gotten themselves stuck in a giant camp near Ivarstead. They tried to charm the giants with music. Now I need to run over there and save them.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4317",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4321",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The farmer Odunn Gray-Sky requested my help in dealing with a glowfly infestation in his hay at Ivarstead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4225",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've put a stop to the threat of the Reachmen, but the threat to the Rift is far from over. The Worm Cult is massing in force, and the settlements west of Nimalten need to be warned.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4167",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A merchant in Nimalten claims his silk was stolen by bandits. I've been asked to retrieve it for the angry businessman.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4133",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Worm Cultists have attacked Treva's Farm.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3923",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The residents of Treva's Farm have fled. A Worm Cult attack drew the attention of nearby giants. The besieged farmers ran for their lives.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4311",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="There's a Worm Cult ritual going on in the Ragged Hills. Amitra needs my help in stopping it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4140",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Walks-in-Ash, an Argonian healer, told me that many Pact soldiers lie wounded around Honrich Tower.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3925",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="There are tomes scattered across the islands of Skald's Retreat that all have something to do with Vaermina.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3924",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The sky over the bardic college of Skald's Retreat is something out of nightmares, and monsters stalk its paths.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4289",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Frostmoon Farmstead has been attacked, resulting in several grisly murders. Guard Jorald needs help uncovering the killer or killers.",["poiIndex"]="60",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4287",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult is up at the top of the dragonshrine. I'm not sure what they're doing, but it can't be good.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5011",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Pact soldier and his brother were captured by bandits after being caught spying. They were investigating the cult-like activity of the bandits.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4164",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Even though we've won a victory over the Worm Cult, Jorunn the Skald-King tells me that Sinmur is headed toward Riften. I should follow in the wake of the giant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4320",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nilwen is living in a shack outside Ivarstead. She tells of fierce beasts nearby and needs someone to slay them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5005",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a keg containing wine with magical properties.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4318",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note on the charred corpse of an assassin who was sent to kill a mage named Malsia. She stole Dwarven artifacts and plans to open a portal to someplace. The Mages Guild wants her dead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4254",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Necromancer Gullveig has captives imprisoned at the Worm Cult camp. I should try to rescue them.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4283",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Svein fears that the fate of the dead in Lost Prospect will never be known to their families in Riften.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4160",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've received a chilly welcome at Fullhelm Fort. The garrison is beset by undead, and the old Thane is not welcoming strangers.",["poiIndex"]="22",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4173",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Preparations were completed just in time - the undead are attacking Fullhelm Fort! Hallfrida has asked me to help defeat the attack.",["poiIndex"]="22",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4201",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've discovered a Worm Cult cell has come to the ruins of a Dragon Cult stronghold. No good can come of this.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5008",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found an abandoned campfire at the entrance to Broken Helm Hollow. I should figure out what happened to the campers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4178",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Gamwyn, Rigvar, and Irgnar are missing and likely in trouble. Snorrvild has asked me to help find them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4273",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Jorunn the Skald-King is encamped at Trolhetta with the bulk of the Ebonheart Pact's army. The Worm Cult is dug in, and hoping to hold on until they can gather the shards of Wuuthrad for some nefarious purpose.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4189",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ebonheart Pact soldiers carry amulets into battle, so they can be identified if they die. Collecting these amulets may bring solace to the families of the dead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4186",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult has barred the route to Trolhetta. King Jorunn has asked me to clear the way.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4276",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Reachmen beseige Shor's Stone. One of the villagers, a seeress of sorts, asked me to kill the clan leader and her co-conspirator.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4306",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sage Svari has asked me to recover Winter's Hammer from bandits at Fort Greenwall.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4307",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sage Svari has asked me to find and return Winter's Bite. She believes it's being held at Faldar's Tooth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4188",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="We're almost there. We must fight through Worm Cultists to reach Sinmur and defeat him!",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4780",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Vanus Galerion of the Mages Guild has a plan to stop Molag Bal's incursion of Tamriel. It requires convincing the three alliances to join forces with the Mages Guild and Fighters Guild to assault Coldharbour.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4783",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="I convinced the leaders of the three alliances to meet to discuss a plan to attack Molag Bal's realm of Coldharbour. The meeting takes place on the historic island of Stirk. Hopefully, the meeting will go smoothly.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4351",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered the Library of Dusk, an Ayleid ruin, just beyond the Hollow City. Several treasure-hunters and scholars in the service of the Mages Guild have been trapped within the ruins by Daedra.",["poiIndex"]="31",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4352",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Mages Guild hired dungeon-delvers and scholars to bolster their expedition force. A group of these treasure hunters are trapped in the Library of Dusk, including Kireth Vanos' brother, Raynor.",["poiIndex"]="31",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4392",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While exploring Coldharbour, I came across the Tower of Lies. Instead of a tower, the place is actually a hole in the ground where members of the Fighters Guild have been imprisoned.",["poiIndex"]="22",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4371",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An ancient Argonian settlement called Haj Uxith occupies a dark corner of Coldharbour. The Argonians want to help me in my quest, but they seem to be divided over something related to their Hist tree.",["poiIndex"]="23",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4399",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I came across an abandoned pack at the edge of a dark forest. The pack suggests that members of the Fighters Guild might have been here.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4679",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I decided to ask Faraniel for help getting into the tower. Before she shows me the secret, however, she wants me to help her convince the Wood Elves to leave the forest and stop working for Molag Bal.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4602",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="This tower is a lightless oubliette, a prison of darkness that binds King Laloriaran Dynar, the last Ayleid King.",["poiIndex"]="33",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4748",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a hastily written note from Lady Laurent's servant, Stibbons. He was captured by Daedra after we arrived in Coldharbour and is being held in a nearby tower.",["poiIndex"]="32",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4743",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found Minstrel Idria's lute abandoned in the Grotto of Depravity.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4623",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Gadris the Dark Elf and Zur the Khajiit. These two mages share a single body, as their souls were melded at this Vile Laboratory when they arrived in Coldharbour. This soul-meld has weakened them. If they remain combined, they will surely die.",["poiIndex"]="30",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4642",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Some of the mages who helped open the initial portal to Coldharbour were captured when they arrived. Now they're prisoners in the Daedric Court of Contempt, awaiting the verdict of Judge Xiven in the Hall of Judgment.",["poiIndex"]="24",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4347",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I came across a dead body on the path to the Everfull Flagon. The dead body clutches a note.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4354",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered the Cliffs of Failure, where Molag Bal's failed servants compete to get back into his good graces. Lost members of the Mages Guild have been ensnared in this twisted game, and I need to join in to save them.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4369",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="To save the members of the Mages Guild that were forced to compete in the Observer's game, I decided to side with Thallik. Now I just need to find a way to win the game.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4746",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a pendant with the names Ahirunz and Ernabi engraved upon it while exploring the Cave of Trophies.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4541",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Three villages were absorbed into a plane of Oblivion, in an attempt to bring them into Coldharbour: one Dunmer, one Khajiit, and one Orc. The Dunmer Suronii has a plan to help herself and the other village leaders escape.",["poiIndex"]="40",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4626",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I came across a magical recording of Vanus Galerion. The message says that the mage decided to enter the Black Forge on his own. He plans to reach the Great Shackle and destroy it, thus completing our mission in Coldharbour.",["poiIndex"]="28",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4730",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I restored Vanus Galerion and disrupted activities at the Black Forge. Now we need to assault the Great Shackle and end the threat of the Planemeld once and for all.",["poiIndex"]="37",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4610",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I need to rebuild my army if we're going to have any chance of confronting Molag Bal and stopping the Planemeld. The mysterious Groundskeeper suggests I rescue as many people as I can and send them to the Hollow City.",["poiIndex"]="36",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4701",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The army has been gathered and the time has come to take the battle to Molag Bal! But to reach the planar vortex at the heart of the Dark Lord's inner sanctum, we have to cross the well-defended Chasm.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4715",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Vampires occupy the Orchard beyond the Chasm, somehow empowered by Molag Bal's Harvest Heart. The vampires need to be dealt with before our forces can push forward toward the planar vortex.",["poiIndex"]="26",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4757",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Soul Shriven named Fatahala. She claims that this Manor of Revelry isn't what it appears to be. Furthermore, she wants me to help Stibbons, who she tells me is in mortal danger here.",["poiIndex"]="34",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4348",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The pirate captain One-Eye and her crew reached Coldharbour through a whirlpool while searching for a legend called the Lost Fleet. They seem intent on investigating the nearby wrecks.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4814",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered the body of one of the Fighters Guild soldiers in Mal Sorra's Tomb. She started writing a note to her cousin, Grundskar, another soldier.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4374",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a talking skull in the Lost Fleet. It seems  he can resist the power of the Crown of Bones, but was broken to bits because of this.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4358",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Captain One-Eye was forced to kill her own crew, and now she's vowed to destroy the apparition that controlled the cursed sailors.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4747",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Dark Elf named Dralnas who claims that Dremora have taken his soul to feed to something he calls the Anguish Gem.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4774",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Dynar has devised a two-pronged attack to take control of the Reaver Citadel. It utilizes the old Fighters and Mages Guilds' halls located in this ancient Nirn city.",["poiIndex"]="35",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4758",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The final assault to end the Planemeld is at hand. We need to fight our way through Molag Bal's defenses and reach the portal to the planar vortex. Only then can we end this threat and save our world.",["poiIndex"]="38",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4847",["level"]="50",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The time has come to confront Molag Bal and reclaim my soul.",["poiIndex"]="46",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4357",["level"]="25",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After aiding the people of Dawnbreak, Landare asked me to move down the road to Firsthold. If Dawnbreak faced the Daedra, chances are the city of Firsthold has as well.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4260",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Firsthold is under assault by High Kinlady Estre. The First Auridon Marines have arrived to try and save the city, but the city is overrun with Daedra and the castle proper is surrounded by a magical barrier.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4261",["level"]="26",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="In order to save Firsthold and all of Auridon from High Kinlady Estre, the Oblivion portals must be closed and Estre defeated for good.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3218",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Chalman Keep for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6058",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Halls of Regulation have begun to break down, threatening the water supply throughout Clockwork City. I've agreed to help Tilelle the Mender make repairs by protecting her as we gather parts and fix machinery.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6045",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lector Naril oversees the Everwound Wellspring, an oasis in the mechanical desert that is the Clockwork City. He has found a way to grow plants in the metallic soil. Once every year, he shares his harvest and selects a new apprentice.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6453",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A man named Dahfnar recently arrived at the Dragonguard Sanctum, claiming we should be gathering ingredients from Dragon corpses on our hunts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5793",["level"]="29",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Auridon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5045",["level"]="30",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met an Ashlander hunter named Shuldrashi looking for her Argonian friend.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6049",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="One of Sotha Sil's Clockwork Apostles, an adjunct named Daro, asked me to use an unusual device called a perception tabulator to find his associate and investigate a mysterious portal that appeared in the Radius.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3438",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Herminius Sophus, a scholar from Cyrodiil, asked me to search the Yokudan ruins at Ancestor's Landing for an ancient sword.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4469",["level"]="34",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I have entered the Blessed Crucible to test my strength and take the Brimstone Crown. Talres Voren has financially backed my bid to become champion with the promise of riches and rewards.",["poiIndex"]="42",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4974",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While traveling in Grahtwood, I found a shrine dedicated to the animals of the Valenwood. Gerweruin said the shrine was created by Brackenleaf's Briars, an elite group of hunters.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3123",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2878",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Glademist Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5819",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Deshaan.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6249",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I encountered an expedition party searching for a Dwarven vault in a glacier. Their leader, a scholar named Tharayya, made me an offer to assist her in locating an artifact known as the Wrathstone.",["poiIndex"]="60",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4523",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Bloodthorn Cult recently attacked Stonetooth Fortress. The Orcs repelled the attack but something was stolen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6140",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tableau is debuting as an artist. Manacar fears that she may be in danger. He's asked me to help things run smoothly.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5824",["level"]="39",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Greenshade.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3223",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Keep for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3245",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Lumbermill for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2813",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2778",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Keep for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3261",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2790",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2776",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Keep for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3207",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2674",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Glademist for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2955",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2745",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Lumbermill  for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2933",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2840",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Warden for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="1489",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A wine merchant named Geron Drothan was robbed on the road to Ebonheart. Now he's deep in his cups, and he wants help getting his shipment back.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3854",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While attempting to test a new spell, Denthis Romori transformed his brother, Dithis, into a female Goblin. The Goblin lass has been kidnapped by a local Goblin warlord named Chieftain Grimmstal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4714",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Engitaale in Vlastarus is wanted by a pack of werewolves.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4449",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My investigations of the Bloodthorn Cult's activities have convinced Chief Tazgol that they threaten the Orcs on Betnikh.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4566",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My actions have convinced Chief Tazgol to join the Daggerfall Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3011",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Glutton, the prized pig that belongs to the Daggerfall swineherd Wickton, is missing. Wickton suspects pig thieves, or at least one particular pig thief.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3000",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The bustling city of Daggerfall holds many mysteries. It appears that I stumbled right into one of them.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3006",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Bloodthorn assassins plan to kill King Casimir. If the King dies, the entire Daggerfall Covenant could fall apart.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3017",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Someone's murdering Daggerfall's poor. A beggar named Matthew thinks he's going to be the next one to die. He asked me to find the killer before that happens.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3414",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Athel Baelborne just learned that he inherited an estate. Unfortunately, the estate appears to be haunted and is overrun by imps.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3060",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Beldama Wyrd asked for my help. The Wyrd rely on the elemental guardians for guidance and counsel, but the spirits have become mysteriously silent.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3063",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Angof Gravesinger has imprisoned the elemental guardians that the Beldama Wyrd rely on for protection and counsel. I agreed to help the Wyrd set the guardians free.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3183",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The elemental guardian asked me to head for the Wyrd Tree. I need to find Wyress Gwen and help save the Wyrd Tree.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3191",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Angof's Bloodthorn cultists threaten the Wyrd Tree. I should help the Beldama Wyrd save the tree.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3235",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The guardians wait inside the Wyrd Tree, ready to assist me against Corruption of the Tree. Once Corruption of the Tree is destroyed, the Wyrd Tree will be purified. Then the corruption will start to fade.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4535",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lord Diel of Daggerfall and his sons are investigating the recent harpy attacks all along the coast. They hired a group of mercenaries called the Daggers to help them with their research, but the Daggers never returned from the Shrieking Scar.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2976",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Aleswell Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2960",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2699",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Chalman Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2894",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Dragonclaw Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2961",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3009",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The forest itself seems to have turned against the village of Deleyn's Mill and the villagers are in danger. I should see if I can help.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2599",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The village of Deleyn's Mill is under siege. Fire threatens to burn the village to the ground while enraged forest creatures attack the remaining villagers. The witches of the Beldama Wyrd are trying to contain the situation. I should help them.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3016",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Beldama Wyrd want to use the roots of the Wyrd Tree to help the villagers get away. But the same corruption that caused all this trouble has sapped the roots of their power.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3001",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Red Rooks attacked a caravan and escaped to a noble's house on the outskirts of Daggerfall, where they've taken hostages. Captain Farlivere of the Daggerfall Guard has ordered her soldiers to surround the estate.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3003",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The nobles now have the wolf's woe plants. Unfortunately, the bandits set traps all around the estate. The nobles will never be able to slip out past those traps or the bandits.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3004",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Red Rook leader, Tharkul, stole Lady Noellaume's jewelry box. She's grateful that her family is safe, but she would love to have her lockbox returned to her once she's safely away from the bandits.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3283",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Wyress Gwen said that the Wyrd Tree will recover, but another danger has appeared in the north.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4335",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I ran across a Lion Guard recruit who had been captured by the Bloodthorn cult in the swamps outside of Aldcroft. He wants me to help him complete his mission.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3040",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alexia Dencent was the sole survivor of the Bloodthorn cult's attack on the Aldcroft lighthouse. She asked me to retrieve her father's pipe from his cottage so she will have something to remember him by.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3094",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help re-capture Drakelowe Keep for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3174",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="General Gautier believes his son Darien, the Captain of the Camlorn Guard is still alive inside the city. He hopes to use Darien's master key to unlock the Camlorn gates. Then the Lion Guard can surround Faolchu's werewolves and retake the city.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3189",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Alinon the Alchemist is working on a way to cure the unique lycanthropy that Faolchu has spread through the city. General Mandin asked me to help him complete the cure.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3267",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I stand with Captain Darien Gautier and the rescued Camlorn citizens. The time to retake Camlorn from Faolchu has arrived.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4340",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tamien, an ex-Red Rook bandit, claims he wants to save the town of Eagle's Brook. The Lion Guard, however, don't trust him. Tamien says the Bloodthorns are turning townfolk into zombies. He wants my help to prepare a spell to protect the villagers.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4341",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I cast Merien's White Mask, a spell to hide the villagers from the Bloodthorn invaders. Now Merien wants my help to stop the Bloodthorn activity in Eagle's Brook.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3019",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The town of Westtry is cursed, haunted by the spirits of its inhabitants and the raiders who slaughtered them. The spirit of Leon Milielle, Westtry's priest, asked me to lift the curse.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3020",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Leon made a pact with Molag Bal that placed a curse upon Westtry. The final twist was when Molag Bal turned Leon's wife and the captain of the guard, Rosalind, into a vengeful shade. She may hold the key to ending this curse.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3416",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Aldmeri Dominion forces have captured Farwatch Tower. They're using the tower to signal their fleet at sea.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3440",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Lion Guard scouting party, made up mostly of new recruits, has gone missing near Farwatch Tower.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3631",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The herd of guar at the sulfur pools stampeded during the Covenant attack. Now they're scattered. If I can calm them and fit them with the proper harnesses, the animals should return to the stable on their own.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3621",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Forces of the Daggerfall Covenant are occupying the volcanic sulfur pools east of Heimlyn Keep. The Othrys family worked the site, but they've been run off their property.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3751",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Covenant attacked the Argonian town of Lukiul Uxith. The residents repelled the attack. They seem to be quite confident about their safety.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3917",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nojaxia wants to join the Mages Guild in Ebonheart. She's trying to create an elixir that replicates the visions an Argonian receives after licking a Hist Tree.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3133",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2844",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Aleswell for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5638",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Some law-abiding citizens have been meddling in the affairs of the Thieves Guild. The guild wants its pickpockets to teach the meddlers to mind their own business. I should look for ornaments, writings, or other oddities, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5644",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Some law-abiding citizens have been meddling in the affairs of the Thieves Guild. The guild wants its pickpockets to teach the meddlers to mind their own business. I should look for ornaments, writings, or other oddities, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5641",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bards and entertainers are failing to pay their dues and badmouthing the guild's members. The Thieves Guild wants to remind them why they pay protection. I should look for games, musical instruments, or children's toys, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5639",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The guild has had laborers around their territory failing to pay their dues and badmouthing its members. The Thieves Guild wants to remind them why they pay protection. I should look for smithing, fishing, or other tools, but any treasures will do.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3121",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Rayles Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6549",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Ravenwatch, a society of vampires working for the greater good, has requested I meet with their agent Gwendis to find out more about the Gray Host.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3752",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Pash-Riha hasn't returned to town yet. She's still hunting a Covenant lieutenant. Seven-Bellies is concerned for her safety. He believes she may be hunting southwest of the town.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5040",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A Pact Mage named Sees-Many-Paths is examining the wards at Tormented Spire. She wants word sent to her egg-sister, Walks-in-Ash, that they are unstable.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3642",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Heimlyn Keep is under a terrible curse. A group of Covenant soldiers attacked, thinking they were assaulting a military target. Instead they loosed an ancient magic hidden beneath in the vaults.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3643",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've helped the survivors at Heimlyn Keep. Now I need to end the curse. Its mystical corruption emanates from a Telvanni reliquary.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3699",["level"]="47",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Renegade Kagesh Ashlanders beseige Iliath Temple. A Kagesh wise woman needs help diffusing the hostilities.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3794",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Curate Brethis knows his monks cannot defend Iliath Temple against a determined assault from the Kasgesh Ashlanders. He's asked me to appeal to the Tribunal for aid.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3806",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The renegade Ashlanders have broken through a storage tunnel beneath Iliath Temple, taking the monks and their defenders by surprise. If the attack can't be repelled, the monastery is sure to fall.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3646",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A frightened soldier on the road told me about a slave revolt at Sathram Plantation. Ulov Stormwall led troops to the plantation, intending to suppress the revolt. Mysterious circumstances induced him to turn his blade on his own troops.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3647",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ra'shadda, the Khajiiti shaman who summoned the monster, didn't leave the plantation. Ruvali speculates that he wanted to stay behind to watch the monster tear them apart.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3648",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note on a dead Khajiit with plans for the riot. Apparently, the riot started with fires, followed by the freeing of prisoners.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5039",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A High Elf named Caalorne was ambushed by a group of Argonians on the road to Kragenmoor. They stole a number of potions from him, and he wants them back.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3697",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A guar herder named Ral Savani has lost control of his herd. Tanval's Vanguard drove them out of their pen, and Ral now fears for their safety.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3156",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4894",["level"]="41",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Llodos plague is ravaging the Deshaan countryside. I met someone from a town known as the Serk. He's on his way to warn people about the plague.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3122",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5606",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The arena master has posted an open challenge for warriors brave enough to fight one of the top gladiators to the death in Kvatch Arena.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2828",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Chalman Lumbermill  for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3239",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Lumbermill for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3248",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Black Boot Lumbermill for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3964",["level"]="44",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Redguard named Paldeen, held prisoner by the Khajiit bandits in the Lost City of the Na-Totambu. He asked for my help in opening the sealed inner chamber.",["poiIndex"]="28",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3970",["level"]="44",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a letter on a dead man named Tavo in the Lost City of the Na-Totambu. His wife, Nahrina, wanted him to recover some Yokudan relics  and return to Sentinel to pay off a debt. I can recover the relics in his stead.",["poiIndex"]="28",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2862",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2812",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3343",["level"]="25",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tamien Sellan says the Crosswych resistance has gained enough momentum. It's time to deal with the Red Rooks' leader, Sternis Gelves himself.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2836",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Roebeck Lumbermill  for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2795",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2832",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Lumbermill  for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3265",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Roebeck Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2834",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Lumbermill  for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3199",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Dragonclaw Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3269",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6505",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Gwendis is investigating the schemes of a mad alchemist named Arkasis and his secret laboratory known only as the Stone Garden. I agreed to help Gwendis discover what Arkasis is up to and stop him if necessary.",["poiIndex"]="30",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6507",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Gwendis arrived at Castle Thorn to investigate a story that Lady Thorn has started amassing an army. She wants to know what the lady is planning and asked me to help uncover it.",["poiIndex"]="57",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5514",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Orcish animal handler named Arushna is desperate to get her hands on special durzog feed that can only be found in the Kennel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5521",["level"]="41",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A foul corruption besets the Wrothgar wilderness. This dark sorcery has blighted the land and driven wild animals mad. The Orcish shaman, Ushang, believes that we can cleanse the corruption through old magic and force of arms.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5507",["level"]="41",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dragonstar Caravan Company job broker, Guruzug, has tasked me with retrieving some mysterious eggs from Coldperch Cavern.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5067",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Alchemist Nilyne Hlor doesn't trust the proprietary formula the Maulborn use to make their curative. She wants to examine a few bottles so she can determine how the elixir is made.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5057",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The virulent Llodos plague spreads throughout Deshaan, and the town known as the Serk suffers under the effects of the ravaging disease. A group known as the Maulborn arrived to help, but some of the townsfolk are dubious about their true intentions.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5068",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Aerona is worried about her uncle, Ornis. He hasn't gotten any better since we returned from the quarantine. In fact, she thinks he's taken a turn for the worse.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3958",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Maulborn cultists are causing trouble throughout Deshaan. Quarantine Serk was only the beginning. A House Hlaalu guard asked me to take word of what happened to Narsis, a town south of the Serk.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3610",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The threat of the Llodos plague has allowed paranoia to run rampant. Many people in Narsis claim that friends and family members have vanished in the night.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3659",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I shared everything I learned with Councilor Ralden. He plans to seal Narsis so that no one can enter or leave. I've been granted an exception while I work for the councilor.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3652",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Minister Ralden and Giron are missing. Advisor Varon believes that Giron is working with the Maulborn and has abducted Ralden.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3658",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I agreed to help Madras rescue the missing villagers. However, I need to prove myself to him before he'll tell me where they're being held.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3660",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Councilor Ralden and Giron are missing, along with many villagers. Varon Davel believes Giron is working with the Maulborn. Apparently, Giron abducted Ralden. I need to find them before it's too late.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3955",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The mysterious operative called Naryu has been investigating the evidence I discovered at the Maulborn camp.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3796",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Kotholl, a hired hand from the merchants' camp, was ordered to guard three specific chests with his life. He states it would be bad for the contents to fall into the hands of the Maulborn.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3673",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Maulborn have occupied the Obsidian Gorge, the pass to Mournhold. House Hlaalu guards have cordoned off the area to keep anyone else from walking into a trap.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3705",["level"]="47",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Scout Kanat says that the rest of the scouting party is dead or afflicted, too far gone to be saved. He also says the Maulborn are protected from the Llodos plague by arcane wards.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3797",["level"]="47",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Llodos plague has been unleashed and it's spreading through the gorge. Despite this, some Hlaalu guards are searching for the Maulborn alchemist.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3956",["level"]="47",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Varon asked me to travel to Mournhold. I should inform the Ordinators about the events at the Obsidian Gorge.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4453",["level"]="47",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I arrived in Mournhold, the capital city of the Ebonheart Pact. As the seat of Dunmer power, it is home to the Tribunal Temple. Due to recent events, the city is bustling with visitors.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3205",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6263",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="According to Jee-Lar, poison-sniffing skinks can provide some much-needed security in the wilds of Murkmire. He needs me to acquire one of these valuable lizards in Alik'r.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6257",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jee-Lar needs bug repellent candles for Cyrodilic Collections' explorers in Murkmire. He requested that I gather materials so his contact, Tamira Dobar, can create these candles.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6255",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jee-Lar informed me that a Wood Elf named Mindileth knows the recipe for a particularly potent anti-venom. This brew may prove vital for the company's explorers in Murkmire. Apparently, the ingredientsâ€”and Mindilethâ€”can be found in Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6256",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jee-Lar asked me to help recruit adventurers to join Cyrodilic Collections' expedition to Murkmire. Posting recruitment handbills and performing a traditional Argonian dance will help drum up interest.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3477",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4620",["level"]="10",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The shoreline of Khenarthi's Roost is lined with the shattered hulls of Aldmeri Dominion sailing vessels. Equipment and personnel are scattered along the beach.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4680",["level"]="10",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I found a letter addressed to me while exploring Khenarthi's Roost. Someone named \"Razum-dar\" wishes to pay me for information.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4624",["level"]="12",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Aldmeri Dominion seeks to secure the loyalty of Khenarthi's Roost, but an old treaty with the Maormer prevents this.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5489",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Drake of Blades' contact in Legion Zero has not checked in for weeks. The Drake has requested that I go try to establish contact myself.",["poiIndex"]="27",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4944",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I discovered a research journal kept by an Orc named Grularz in Crestshade Mine. She was apparently studying the trolls until they decided to kill her. The journal referred to a brother named Gothurg in Shornhelm.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3257",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3242",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Blue Road Lumbermill for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6508",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Castle Thorn.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4705",["level"]="34",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've reached the siege range. Zan advised me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Firamo and Miniel to learn more about the weapons.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4706",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Taralin says there is much more for me to learn about the war in Cyrodiil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3124",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Aleswell Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3153",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Roebeck Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5565",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Treasure-hunting pirates have disturbed the undead necromancers in Bahraha's Gloom. Now the great seal that kept them trapped has been weakened and the necromancers may soon be free to threaten all of Hew's Bane.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5535",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Quen asked me for help in dealing with a personal matter.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5552",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Shark's Teeth Grotto has been overrun by pirates and Shalug needs some help dealing with them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5920",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Someone extinguished Seyda Neen's lighthouse to cause a shipwreck. Deputy Governor Deminah Salvi suspects slavers and asked me to help her investigate the matter.",["poiIndex"]="33",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2892",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Ash Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3190",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I am now officially a member of the Ash'abah, and I am setting forth to destroy the Withered Hand. Talia suggested I visit Tu'whacca's Throne to see if the Withered Hand has been there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2184",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Withered Hand has taken over Tu'whacca's Throne and begun using the Ansei Wards to raise the consecrated remains of fallen heroes. I agreed to help the Throne Keeper activate defenses to cleanse the temple.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2192",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Throne Keeper and I have lit the sacred braziers at the cardinal points of the temple. When we light the final brazier, Tu'whacca should send his \"Breath\" to come and help us cleanse the temple. Then we can kill Uwafa and recover the Ansei Wards.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2187",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The dead have risen at Tu'whacca's Throne, and an Ash'abah here is particularly worried that three ancient heroes have been raised. I agreed to visit their graves, and if they have been raised, then I will kill them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2193",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Throne Keeper Farvad says I should continue my search for the remaining Ansei Wards in Bergama to the east.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4622",["level"]="36",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a man named Armin in the bottom of Divad's Chagrin mine. After seven years searching, he found his ancestors remains and wants to send word to his wife that he will soon return home.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6319",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Iraya and Izanji, two siblings in charge of a museum in Riverhold called the House of Histories, have fallen on hard times after a recent theft. I intend to help them solve this theft and return the missing items.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6320",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The ancient Khajiiti mural known as the Rithana-di-Renada has been completed, but Iraya feels like something is still missing. Legends say the mural emits some kind of music.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4654",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I decided to ask Tzik'nith for help getting into the tower. Before she shows me the secret, however, she wants me to help her against the Wood Elves.",["poiIndex"]="4",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6506",["level"]="50",["type"]="15",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="Urgarlag Chief-bane of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Stone Garden.",["poiIndex"]="30",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5889",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I encountered an escaped captive named Filand who warned me that the Reachmen are kidnapping people to labor at a strange, ancient Forge in this valley. He asked me to help rescue the other prisoners before the Reachmen work them to death, or worse.",["poiIndex"]="74",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6205",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4767",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="2",["backgroundText"]="I've been invited to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6312",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I agreed to retrieve mysterious Akaviri relics from the Tomb of the Serpents so that a messenger named Kiseravi can share their secrets with the world.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2569",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've discovered evidence of something amiss at the Windridge Caves in Alcaire. The fates of a knight and his comrades seem inexorably tied to the existence of The Three, a trio of bandit chieftains who once dwelled in these caves.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6389",["level"]="28",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An Imperial named Elianna Pevengius asked me to recover her stolen belongings from a nearby camp of Ruddy Fang bandits.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5833",["level"]="42",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Glenumbra.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6204",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6311",["level"]="28",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mizzik Thunderboots has requested my help investigating an abduction in Riverhold.",["poiIndex"]="15",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3172",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Crown bride, Tiela, has been left at the altar because the Forebear groom, Casnar, hasn't shown up for the wedding. Both families are angry, and I've agreed to help settle the matter.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2251",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="People are disappearing from the streets of Bergama, and I've decided to help investigate the matter.",["poiIndex"]="9",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2854",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Castle Roebeck for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4678",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Mansa fishing in the cold waters of northern Cyrodiil. She asked if I could bring some of her catch to her friend Hannura in Chorrol.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2903",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Faregyl Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2879",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Ash Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5510",["level"]="27",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4761",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A courier came to me with an urgent request to go help Prince Azah fight in the small town of Tava's Blessing and to send the Scholar's apprentice, Shiri, back to Bergama.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2222",["level"]="38",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="An army of Withered Hand soldiers necromancers attacked Tava's Blessing and killed everyone. Whatever they are planning here, I plan to stop them.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2356",["level"]="38",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The spirits of HoonDing's Watch have awoken to test me. I must vanquish the spirits of the Redguards' ancient foes and claim their essence to summon their leaders.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3296",["level"]="38",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The spirits of four legendary Redguards stand around the central shrine atop HoonDing's Watch. Each poses a challenging choice based on a difficult decision they once had to make.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2403",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Shiri, the scholar's apprentice, has disappeared along with the text she recovered from Tava's Blessing. I've agreed to help find Shiri â€¦ and the text.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2404",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Imperial forces have seized control of Satakalaam. King Fahara'jad's army is here to take the city back, but General Thoda needs to rescue four hostages the Imperials are holding first.",["poiIndex"]="12",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2997",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The final Ansei Ward has been tracked to the Motalion Necropolis. I must help Prince Azah recover the Ward and put an end to the Withered Hand's plot.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2998",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I recovered all three Ansei Wards and defeated the heirs of Suturah. The Withered Hand is broken. Their campaign of terror has ended. All that remains is to restore the Ansei Wards to safekeeping in Sentinel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3566",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Fahara'jad has informed me of dire circumstances in Bangkorai. King Eamond is dead and the Reachmen are marching on the kingdom's capital of Evermore. He has asked me to go there and try to rally the city's defenses.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6326",["level"]="28",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A traveler bade me seek out a suspicious Khajiit lurking near the Abode of Ignominy.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6313",["level"]="30",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A vain Khajiit named Sarazi challenged me to kill all the master hunters lurking on Predator Mesa, as well as a feisty gryphon called Quillmane.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6301",["level"]="30",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Prowl recently suffered a devastating Dragon attack. In the aftermath, violent poachers seized control of the area. If left unchecked, these reckless hunters could ruin this hunting ground for generations.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5771",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Titus Valerius sent word that I should meet him near the observatory in Belkarth. The messenger had few details, but the situation sounds urgent.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5776",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Celestial Warrior is worried about his champion, Titus Valerius. Lost in time, Titus' memory has begun to break apart. He no longer remembers who he is or his connection to the Warrior. Without his memory, the Warrior can't send him home.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5777",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a book describing an ancient Nedic hero named Ranev the Coal-Eyed Wanderer and her legendary pilgrimage along \"The Gray Passage.\" According to the text, those who complete the pilgrimage in the allotted time gain the favor of the Stars.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5755",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="Refugees outside of Elinhir told me that the city has been ransacked by mad mages. They sent me to Minerva Lauzon, who is gathering survivors in the sewers.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5751",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="Outside the school of blades called Rahni'Za, I encountered an intiate of the school who told me that the Sword-Disciples have been turned into thralls by a traitor. This betrayer now hides in the cavern at the end of the school's five trials.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5762",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="Within the burial grounds of Shada's Tear, I encountered an undead Nede named Nhalan, who told me about the curse Shada placed on the waters of the city.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5750",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="I found the ruins of a city called Shada's Tear in the middle of the Craglorn desert. A mercenary told me that some researchers from Belkarth went into the ruins, but that strange things started happening when they did.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6242",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Concordia Mercius of Cyrodilic Collections needs my help to stop Margus Derius and the Blackguards from obtaining the Golden Skull of Beela-Kaar.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6295",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a notice calling for warriors to join a Death-Hunt.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6246",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="An explorer named Famia Mercius is recruiting adventurers to join her on an expedition into a sunken Argonian xanmeer. Ancient treasures and mortal danger both await within this mysterious ruin.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6258",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The influential Bright-Throat tribe broker alliances with their neighbors through a complex system of bonding rituals. It is a delicate time for the tribe and it seems that this season's preparations have been plagued by unforeseen complications.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6278",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hands-That-Heal has lost a wooden box with great sentimental value to him after being attacked by hackwings. He's offered a reward if I successfully return the box to him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6275",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a pack with a romantic poem and frog totem in the middle of the swamp. If I return these items to their rightful owner, I may receive a reward.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6277",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A local dispute over a saltrice farm has now gotten to the point where Sulahkeesh, a former Shadowscale, must arbitrate for a resolution to be found. I volunteered to ask the former assassin for her help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6265",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A local crafter, Nesh-Deeka, hopes to establish a trade agreement with Captain Jimila to sell an Argonian musical instrument abroad. He wants me to act as his agent and secure a deal for his vossa-satl.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6293",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="As the Bright-Throat tribe prepares to commence their most important ritual of the year, things may be in for a rocky start as none of their visiting guests seem in any hurry to participate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6270",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Twelve tablets were stolen from the Xinchei-Konu, an ancient Argonian calendar. Jekka-Wass Vozei, the keeper of the calendar, has tasked me to return the first missing tablet.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6266",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My companion from the xanmeer, Famia Mercius, needs my help. Several of her employees have gone missing in recent days, and she fears the worst. I need to try to find out what happened to them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6254",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Naga-Kur, or Dead-Water tribe, has sentenced Kishi, a member of the tribe, to death for interfering in the rites of passage and saving a few young Nagas from certain death. One of the survivors asked if I could help Kishi.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6241",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A band of notorious criminals known as the Blackguards are searching for a powerful Argonian relic called the Remnant of Argon. I'll need allies if I'm going to find it first.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6259",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The riddles I uncovered with Xukas and Jaxsik-Orrn pointed us to a mysterious locale known as the Swallowed Grove. According to Famia, I will have to undertake a dream-wallow vision to learn the truth of the Remnant of Argon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6284",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lady Laurent and her manservant, Stibbons, have come to Murkmire in search of an antique Argonian renewal charm. Lady Laurent needs it or she won't be able to observe the annual rite of renewal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6280",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nisswo Uaxal, a priest of Sithis, wishes to create a monument to honor Sithis and his people's connection to the concept of change.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6271",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Though I've gathered all the tablets, the Xinchei-Konu remains powerless. Jekka-Wass Vozei wishes to perform a ritual to help the monument regain its magical properties, but needs the help of his mentor Nisswo Paraxeeh to do so.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6243",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Kassandra betrayed usâ€”she claimed the sap-speaker's staff and set out after the Remnant on her own. I need to reach her before she takes the Remnant for herself.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6244",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Kassandra, having evaded Jaxsik-Orrn and Xukas, entered a second xanmeer called Vakka-Bok. Famia and I must enter this vast ruin and prevent Kassandra from acquiring the Remnant of Argon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6245",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After a lengthy chase and a harrowing battle with Kassandra, Famia and I finally retrieved the Remnant of Argon. Now, we need to learn how to release the souls that reside within it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6336",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Battlemage and former Imperial advisor Abnur Tharn summoned me to Northern Elsweyr to help him and the Khajiiti deal with a rage of Dragons.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6374",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Khajiit named Hadamnargo needs me to burn the wasp nests in his fields and find his lost guar, Gordon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6354",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="A preacher from Sunspire invited me to travel to the temple to see the god Alkosh incarnate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6348",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a notice urging me to take up arms in defense of Northern Elsweyr.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6314",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a flier for a traveling menagerie in Rimmen. I should investigate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6338",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After learning that Mulaamnir the Dragon considers Euraxia, the usurper queen of Rimmen, to be nothing more than a puppet, Abnur Tharn believes parley is our best course of actionâ€”especially considering the current state of the Khajiiti army.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6296",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Euraxia, the Usurper Queen of Rimmen, has ordered her forces to attack Riverhold. I need to help defend the town.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6378",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An eerily clever terror bird called Wily Kee'va has been harassing sugar traders and devouring their camels near Scar's End. Left unchecked, this beast could bring trade in southwestern Anequina grinding to a halt.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6377",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The elderly job broker, Ri'hirr, urged me to defeat Sword Master Vhysradueâ€”a peerless warrior who camps on the Hill of Shattered Swords.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6380",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A powerful necromancer named Na'ruzz the Boneweaver lurks in the Bone Pitsâ€”a cursed gulch near Orcrest. His dark influence presents a danger to any Khajiit who strays too close.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6304",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After successfully defending Riverhold from Euraxia's forces, Abnur Tharn and the war council think the time has come to assault Rimmen and remove the Usurper Queen from the throne.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6364",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a keg of sweet rotmeth brew. If I return it to its rightful owner, I may receive a reward.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6366",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A ragged preacher warned me that my wealth and status attract a lot of dangerous attention in Elsweyr, particularly from the folk-hero-turned-god, Rajhin. The preacher solicited me to steal offerings to appease the Khajiit thief-god.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6375",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note offering a reward for three mysterious bottles of stolen wine. I should find the bottles and bring them to Hofgrad Kjisorssen in the Stitches to receive the reward.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6308",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a traveler who warned me that the Stiches has a new and unpopular leader named Khasda. He also told me that a rival of Khasda's by the name of Tasnasi is offering a job well suited to someone passing through.",["poiIndex"]="23",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6303",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The adeptorium, S'rendarr's Cradle, suffers under a terrible drought. Unfortunately, something or someone halted the flow of water from the Anequina Aqueduct. Without the aqueduct, the adepts of S'rendarr's Cradle will not last long.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6355",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Khajiit spirit has awakened from eternal slumber. His descendent Saviwa needs me to find a proper place for the urn in Rimmen Necropolis, so that his ancestor can be at peace, and Saviwa can have some peace and quiet.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6307",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dark Elf Ashur has come to Hakoshae to investigate Magnate Feina-Darak. Rumor has it that she's the descendant of the Akaviri Potentate. I agreed to help him in his investigation.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6321",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hundreds of Khajiiti undead emerge from the ruins of the Ashen Scar. A mysterious High Elf mage named Vastarie is trying to keep the corpses at bay, but without my help, the waves of undead might overwhelm Elsweyr.",["poiIndex"]="22",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6316",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Travelers in the Weeping Scar are falling prey to an ancient clan of vampires called the Tenarr Zalviit, but I met an exile of this clan named Yushiha, who is determined to stop the bloodshed.",["poiIndex"]="20",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6358",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A follower of Peryite, the Daedric Prince of Pestilence, has asked me to rescue his friend from the flu-ridden city of Orcrest.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6310",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Khajiiti temple of Two Moons at Tenmar has been afflicted by mass hysteria. The priests blindly follow the bizarre prophecies of their Moon-Bishop, which grow more deranged and deluded by the day.",["poiIndex"]="24",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6325",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sweetwater Farmstead in Merryvale seeks workers to replace those that have gone missing. I should investigate this mystery and see if I can help.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6300",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="While investigating Darkpool Mine, a Khajiit named Mara'dahni, and her partner, Hadaz, were set upon by Daedric cultists and their minions. Mara'dahni escaped. Hadaz wasn't so lucky. I agreed to investigate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6302",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Iokkas' companions are lost in the nearby oasis caverns, surrounded by noxious fumes and hostile undead. I offered to help rescue them.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6371",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rigurt the Brash was sent to Elsweyr to improve relations with the Khajiit, but he's already lost his collection of Nord peace offerings. I agreed to help Rigurt deliver his missing gifts, and complete his diplomatic mission.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6398",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sai Sahan and I discovered the location of the Horn of Ja'darri, a powerful Dragonhorn made by the Dragonguard. It awaits us in a Dragon's lair, nestled within a dormant volcano in Southern Elsweyr.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6279",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The skinned bodies of Argonians are being placed on display around Murkmire by a killer dubbed \"the Skin Taker.\" I have been asked to help find this killer before anyone else falls victim to their grisly methods.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4528",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A tailor tried to take a shortcut through Cambray Pass and was attacked by a pack of wild wolves. He lost the tools of his trade as he fled. He asked me to retrieve his possessions and meet him at the northern end of the pass.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4667",["level"]="17",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A spirit named Cartirinque warned me of dark knowledge sealed in three forbidden tomes. She asked me to find all three and destroy them in a shrine on Khenarthi's Roost.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2827",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Dragonclaw Lumbermill  for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2732",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5672",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4873",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Arkas at the Southern Morrowind gate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3142",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5569",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The assassin Naryu Virian must kill a Dark Elf noble in Kvatch to fulfill a contract for her shadowy organization. However, she doesn't want to attract the attention of the Dark Brotherhood as she completes her work, so she asked for my help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4184",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The spirit Valdur worries about his fellow companion spirit, bound to Pinepeak Cavern. He's asked me to check on her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5036",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Hakra has been saved and Pinepeak is secure, but it seems Honrich Tower has been taken by the Worm Cult.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4852",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Torog's Spite Bandits are dedicated to profit and vengeance from targeting families descended from those who sacked Orsinium. An Orc historian named Maaga wants to record the bandits' deeds but needs to know which Orc clan deserves credit.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5761",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="When called to destroy a Dark Anchor in Craglorn, atronachs turned on the mages who summoned them. One mage who escaped believes a Celestial caused it to happen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5748",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I learned of a strange Imperial being held captive by the Dragonstar Arena Guard. He claims to know how to defeat the cursed army of Anka-Ra that has laid siege to Craglorn since the Celestials appeared.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6066",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Associate Zanon has asked for my assistance in rebuilding an ancient factotum. Doing so will allow him to better understand the creation of factotums, a mystery to all but Sotha Sil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5763",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a Star-Gazer who told me that two High Elf women inside the Crossroad Tavern claim to be aspects of the Celestial Mage. I should talk to them and investigate their claims.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5760",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Hara has decided it's time to do something about the third guardian, the Thief. The Thief has been mysteriously absent except for when she appears to speak to me in private.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5768",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A woman named Regent Cassipia has plans for the Scaled Court. It seems she opposes the Serpent.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5774",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Regent Cassipia has asked me to find her seneschal, Little Leaf, somewhere along the road through the northeast passage. She wants me to offer my aid to Little Leaf and help her foil another one of the Scaled Court's plans.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5769",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A Wood Elf named Little Leaf claims she's on a mission to stop the Iron Orcs from building a troll army. She tried to appeal to the Orc leaders, but diplomacy didn't work. Now she wants me to come along and try a more forceful approach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6063",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Divayth Fyr is convinced that something sinister is driving Sotha Sil's recent change of character. He asked me to help him root out the cause of the Clockwork God's new and peculiar behavior.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6025",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="In the wake of the Shadow of Sotha Sil's attack, Gascone has gone missing.  I should find him and see if he has any insight into what the shadow is and why it was in the Brass Fortress.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5664",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A flier indicates that an Imperial named Reman Mevavius seeks someone for an urgent and dangerous job in the Gold Coast.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2974",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2770",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Ash for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="1799",["level"]="39",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The city of Evermore is in dire straits. King Eamond is dead, and a Reachmen army marches toward the city gates even now. The people of Evermore need help, and they need hope.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3281",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After we thwarted the Imperial plot in Evermore, Uela the crow paid me another visit to say we're enemies again now and that her Reachmen army is going to kill everyone in Evermore.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5964",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lady Clarisse Laurent and her man-servant Stibbons, along with a number of research assistants on loan from the Mages Guild, have been studying the ruins of Bal Fell. Now, everyone but Lady Laurent has disappeared.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5508",["level"]="37",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4899",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Reachmen attacked Northglen. They must be stopped before they can attack the city of Evermore.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5513",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5482",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Molag Bal seeks to destroy the Sublime Brazierâ€”the key to rekindling the Dragonfires. Working with The Drake of Blades, Captain Caudex, and Father Egnatius, I must find a way to protect the Dragonfire Cathedral, and the brazier within.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6393",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Sai Sahan received a letter from Abnur Tharn. It seems the old battlemage discovered something about a threat to Southern Elsweyr and needs our help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3151",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4949",["level"]="35",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Queen Maraya has asked a personal favor. She's heard disturbing rumors about some of her father's enemies returning, so she's asked me to go to Sentinel in the Alik'r Desert and ensure that both the kingdom and her father are safe.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4959",["level"]="43",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After their defeat at Bangkorai Garrison, the Imperial forces retreated south, and King Emeric believes they will make their last stand here at the ancient temple known as the Hall of Heroes.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4960",["level"]="43",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Imperial Magus-General Septima Tharn captured King Emeric and took him into the Chamber of Passage. It's apparently a gateway to the plane known as the Far Shores, where Redguards go in the afterlife.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5490",["level"]="37",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Drake of Blades wants me to recover a book that the Daedra refuse to burn and whose contents must therefore be very important.",["poiIndex"]="25",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2814",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3202",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3247",["level"]="19",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Lumbermill for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3783",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered a wounded Lion Guard member named Sir Edgard in the Bonesnap Ruins. He and his soldiers were sent to retrieve pieces of an artifact, but were ambushed.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3784",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Daedric creature is loose in Bonesnap Ruins, and Battlemage Gaston has found a way to contain the creature by repairing a Welkynd Stone that's been damaged by invading Goblins.",["poiIndex"]="21",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5477",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Someone calling themselves The Rat left a note claiming that the Daedra are slaughtering people in the Imperial Arena. If I slay the Daedra, instead, The Rat promised to reward me with a secret about Molag Bal's plan for Imperial City.",["poiIndex"]="26",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3026",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Wyress Helene discovered that Reach magic has somehow corrupted the forest and silenced the elemental guardians.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5487",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Ebonheart Pact is locked in an epic struggle for control of the Imperial City. The forces of Molag Bal hold the city in an iron grip, but enemy bannermen also vie for power. The Pact needs my help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2979",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2986",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Roebeck Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6555",["level"]="50",["type"]="14",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Gwendis and I discovered a letter from Rada al-Saran to her mentor, Verandis, in a hidden room in Ravenwatch Castle. She asked me to accompany her to investigate the secret island, Grayhome, and the Gray Host castle mentioned in the letter.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2707",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Roebeck Mine for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4992",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A group of soldiers from Bangkorai Garrison lead by Sir Dubroc went out in search of the Reachman leader in Jackdaw Cove.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2731",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5104",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Worm Cult has stolen the legendary axe Wuuthrad and plans to perform dark deeds with it. There are even rumors it was shattered, in which case we must find the shards of Wuuthrad wherever they may be.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4370",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="To save the Mages Guild members that were forced to compete in the Observer's game, I decided to side with Kinlady Estre. Now I just need to find a way to win the game.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3262",["level"]="32",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3229",["level"]="32",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Bloodmayne for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2820",["level"]="32",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Black Boot Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5668",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Before the Thieves Guild sends me after more lucrative targets, I need to prove I know how to pick pockets.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5556",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Zeira wants to know what really happened to Magnifica Falorah's dowry. She has a plan to uncover the truth of what happened during the guild's failed heist.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5537",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Quen deciphered her father's ledger. She asked for my help with what she uncovered.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5570",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Walks-Softly wants some more of my help with the situation involving his old friend, Anais Velmont. The letter he left indicates he's come up with a solution that he wants to run by me.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5604",["level"]="46",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a contract to destroy the beast named Ironfang. It's being held captive deep in the ruins of Garlas Agea by the Gold Coast Trading Company. Additionally, the job calls for me to appropriate company ledgers from their operation there.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5603",["level"]="46",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cleric Arvina in Anvil has posted a bounty for any group brave enough to enter Hrota Cave and destroy Exulus, a wispmother claiming the cave as her own. He also asked that the pauldrons of his fallen warriors be retrieved.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5547",["level"]="46",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Vampire hunter Mel Adrys has come to Hrota Cave to track down the dangerous vampire lord Zalar-do, who has been preying on the people of Anvil. I promised to help him slay the vampire and rescue the victims she kidnapped.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4073",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Talmo's family banner has been stolen. He believes it was taken by bandits who visited Vlastarus.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5710",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts, which requests the indiscriminate slaughter of citizens of Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5599",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Hildegard never returned to the Sanctuary after going out to pray for Tanek. Kor asked me to help him find her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5619",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
