{["internalId"]="3023",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bloodthorn cultists attacked a group of Camlorn refugees. They kidnapped the group's women and dragged them into the Fens.",["poiIndex"]="2",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3437",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dusty old scroll beside an ancient Ayleid coffer in the vault beneath Dresan Keep.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3315",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered the spirit of Richard Dusant, who died searching for the hidden treasure of Dresan Keep. He wants me to finish his search for the Keep's ancient secrets.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3322",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The spirit of Richard Dusant said I should take the Dresan Index to someone in the Mages Guild.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3039",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a dead Orc in the bog. He carried a broadsheet, as well as a handful of sharp crocodile teeth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2672",["level"]="39",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I have accepted a mission to travel to Fort Warden and scout that stronghold for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2973",["level"]="38",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Rayles Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2721",["level"]="48",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Warden Farm for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2972",["level"]="48",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Lumbermill for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6047",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Luciana and I cleared the way to the Cogitum Centralis. Now we must delve deep into the core of the Clockwork City to stop the Shadow of Sotha Sil.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6048",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="My companions and I turned back the Daedric incursion into the Clockwork City and rescued Sotha Sil from his own shadow. Now, the Clockwork God has some wisdom to share before he leaves.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4656",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I've found a note from a Dwemer researcher's journal named Tharayya. She appears to have been searching for an ancient artifact referred to as the \"Guardian's Eye.\"",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4925",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="In ruined Klathzgar, I found a note from an Altmeri scholar investigating an ancient mystery. An Ayleid princess named Urenenya vanished centuries ago, and the scholar came here after learning of her connection to the Dwemer architect Klazthgar.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4663",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Tertius Falto is out in the wilds, looking for his son, Donus.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4683",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Saldir needs herbs delivered to Jafola in Bruma.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4639",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a bundle of damaged gifts meant for Kjakur Gray-Fists who lives in Bruma Anchor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4658",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a notebook full of observations about the Ayleid wells around Cyrodiil. The book's owner may want it back.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4666",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a small silver flute in a crate. An inscription on the flute reads, \"Halion of Chorrol.\" There might be a reward for the flute's return.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4238",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Mael asked me to find his friend Lucius, who was carrying supplies for Weynon Priory.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6347",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dragons have not been seen in Tamriel for generations, and the Khajiit are unsure how best to fight against them. The ancient Nords recorded Dragon fighting techniques on scrolls they keep in their crypts. I need to find these scrolls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3089",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help re-capture Chalman Keep for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6318",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="From ancient Khajiit legends, Zahari has learned that weapons imbued with enchantments powered by Daedric souls are particularly powerful against Dragons. I need to collect these souls to help fight back against the Dragon threat.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6586",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a hunter named Medone by Briar Rock. Hagravens of the Thornroot clan imprisoned her clan and are turning them into Briarhearts. Medone wants me to free her clan and punish the Thornroot clan by destroying their Briarheart Tree.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6565",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Adusa-daro needs my help to rescue her friend Kathad from a clan of evil vampires known as the Lothid, and their leader, Boss Trenlor.",["poiIndex"]="18",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6590",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Reach clans Six-Fords and Eagleseers don't get along. They plan to rectify that through the marriage of two of their young members, Eslyn and Madearn. A handfasting rite must be performed to announce their intention to marry.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6532",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a notice about the opportunity to join a guild of like-minded adventurers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6553",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A notice indicates that someone seeks adventurers in Markarth for dangerous work.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6569",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bralthahawn explained that his contacts in the Wildblood clan think a hagraven matron is influencing the Thornroot clan. I need to take a powerful totem in her possession in order to weaken her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6582",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Ard's Stonehands asked me to investigate a Reach clan's witch matron and put a stop to a dangerous ritual. Supposedly, the ritual creates tears in reality. I also need to close any I find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6558",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nelldena charged me with finding allies to assault the harrowstorm ritual sites springing up across the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6599",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the body of Kitza-Enoo. It looks like he died after stealing a sacred relic from the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6562",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hiretta asked me to look for her husband, Bolfalgar, and their pet bunny Snowy. She thinks they might be lost in the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6575",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a recent recruit of the Psijic Order. He asked for my help investigating strange behavior in the local plant life, which he fears may be a result of his own errant magic. I agreed to accompany him into the cave to take a closer look.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6591",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a faded scrap of parchment in the depths of Blackreach. It's an account written by a Nord scout, Falkfyr, after he became lost in the great cavern. If I wish to discover Falkfyr's fate, I should follow the directions in his notes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6573",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A crazed mage performing experiments in Gloomreach has a strange egg that has the potential to be dangerous if it hatches. I volunteered to destroy the egg.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6609",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="High Shaman Glynroch sent Apprentice Orla to find the Symbol of Uricanbeg, the final sacred relic needed to dedicate the shrine, at Lost Valley Redoubt. She hasn't returned yet, so he asked me to go aid her.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6550",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Count Verandis Ravenwatch seeks to uncover a plot to conquer the Reach by an army of vampires and werewolves that calls itself the Gray Host. To succeed, he needs to earn the trust of the region's sovereign: the dreaded Despot of Markarth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6551",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Count Verandis wants to see me in Understone Keep in Markarth. He wants to discuss how we deal with the Gray Host, and I still need to tell him about the Dwarven relic Lady Belain seeksâ€”the Arkthzand Keystone.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6547",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Count Verandis Ravenwatch tracked Lady Belain and Rada al-Saran to a mysterious Dwarven edifice. But with the keystone in hand, our enemies have a clear advantage. Braving this ruin and learning its secrets may be our best hope of stopping them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6548",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Arana believes that her former clan knows about dark Reach magic and old prophecies. If I can find the Ghostsong clan and convince the witches to share their lore, I may learn what Lady Belain plans for the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5922",["level"]="31",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="After a harrowing experience at the hands of Magister Gothren, Sun-in-Shadow finds herself at a crossroadsâ€”torn between a mage's ambition and the fruits of companionship. Dedicating herself to one may well destroy her chances at the other.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5103",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A shipment from Artisans Craftworks in Mournhold never made it to the merchant, Blivisi Beleth.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="728",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The lighthouse south of Koeglin Village was attacked, and its signal fires were extinguished. Until someone repairs it, ship captains will have difficulty navigating the harbor.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6080",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Clockwork Apostle entered the Shadow Cleft and hasn't returned. What's worse, he forgot to take his perception tabulator with him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6056",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cultists have attacked the Mnemonic Planisphere in order to steal Sotha Sil's memories, manifested as glowing stars. Amili Lloryn has tasked me to rescue these stars and return them to the Planisphere's sky.",["poiIndex"]="7",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6095",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a sequence plaque on the road in the Clockwork City Radius. An engraving on the plaque asks that it be returned to the Clockwork Registrar in the Brass Fortress.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6088",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Clockwork Apostles have tasked me to continue maintenance in the Halls of Regulation. I need to replace several water filters in order to stop the possibility of contamination.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6079",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Clockwork Apostles sent a member of the Mages Guild through the portal to explore the Shadow Cleft. She hasn't returned.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6346",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dragons have not been seen in Tamriel for generations, and the Khajiit are unsure how best to fight against them. The ancient Nords recorded Dragon fighting techniques on scrolls they keep in their crypts. I need to find these scrolls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6418",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A young Imperial named Catina recently lost her mother, Honoria. In the weeks that followed, images of the Forsaken Citadel plagued her dreams. Honoria clearly has unfinished business in the ruined academy, and she needs the living to help settle it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4956",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a journal on the body of Klaandor Axe-Bearer. It details his transformation into a vampire. Seems like he was looking for someone to kill him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5799",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Two Argonian slaves named Eoki and Sun-in-Shadow have hatched a plot to win their freedom from the Dark Elves of House Telvanni.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5859",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The recently freed Argonian slave, Sun-in-Shadow, seeks to continue her climb through the ranks of House Telvanni. She needs my help to claim the next title.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5901",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="With my help, Sun-in-Shadow achieved the rank of retainer in the Great House Telvanni. If she is to help free Eoki, she will need to climb the ranks even further. Unfortunately, becoming an oathman may present a greater challenge than she expects.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="523",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The town of Crestshade has been subjected to a blood-curse that turned the townsfolk feral. While some refugees were able to escape to the south, the mayor remained behind to aid any survivors.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4721",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Honorless criminals are left in the Tears of the Dishonored. Darius begged me to find the remains of his wife, Zariya, and consecrate them as he believes she was innocent.",["poiIndex"]="52",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2679",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Keep for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="2675",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Ash for the Dominion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3886",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I purchased a strange statue from an Ashlander merchant in the wilderness. It may be a religious fetish.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6554",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Verandis detected a growing concentration of dark energyâ€”Void energyâ€”within Nighthollow Keep. Perhaps we'll find the Dark Heart somewhere within those ancient ruins.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6566",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Dark Heart has awakened and grows more powerful with every beat. While Verandis attempts to deal with Rada al-Saran, I need to go to Markarth and stop Lady Belain from sacrificing the entire city to the Void.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6589",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Lyris Titanborn requested my assistance. She found something at the Reachwind Ritual Site and needs help solving a problem.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6552",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Verandis believes Rada al-Saran has set his final plan in motion. He seeks my help to put a stop to the Gray Host once and for all.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6560",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rada al-Saran used the orrery to reach his sanctuary realm in Oblivion, where he will perform the Darkstorm ritual that will destroy the Reach and make the Gray Host truly immortal. To stop him, we must follow him into the Void.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6570",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Rada al-Saran is dead and the victims of the Gray Host's assault on Markarth have been restored to life thanks to Verandis.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6075",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Now that I found all of the Precursor's parts, Associate Zanon wishes to present the factotum to his mentor.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6057",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The High Elf explorer, Neramo, and his two associates, Kireth and Raynor, have a plan to win the sponsorship of an influential Clockwork Apostle named Varuni Arvel. We'll need her support to become bonafide citizens of the Clockwork City.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4026",["level"]="13",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've made my decision. I'm standing with Darj the Hunter and defending Fort Zeren.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6081",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Clockwork Apostles have tasked me to continue maintenance in the Halls of Regulation. I need to grease a ventilation fan using oil found within the repair factotums.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3653",["level"]="21",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Guard Rila wants me to slow down a group of agitated citizens to keep them from getting killed. She asked me to disrupt their meeting by using something they fear. I need rats.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2872",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Roebeck Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5787",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Bangkorai.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5012",["level"]="45",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A crew hired to hunt harpies in Silverhoof Vale may need my help to complete the job.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2046",["level"]="38",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cultists called Supernal Dreamers are up to no good in Moonlit Maw. Master Muzgu, a monk from Pariah Abbey, led other monks here to stop them. But they were ambushed by the cultists.",["poiIndex"]="14",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6089",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Clockwork Apostles have tasked me to continue maintenance in the Halls of Regulation. I need to replace several brass commutators to prevent the galvanic engine from shutting down.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6000",["level"]="13",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="I met an apprentice to Divayth Fyr in Vivec City, she mentioned an incident at her master's tower involving some kind of rift.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5548",["level"]="18",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Razum-dar tracked an Imperial war criminal to the Garlas Agea ruins to make her pay for attacking innocent noncombatants in Bravil. I agreed to help him dispatch this Captain Jena Apinia and recover the items they stole.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4911",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Scholar Herminius Sophus and his guide, Azei at-Owynok became separated in the Sunken Road.",["poiIndex"]="50",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3143",["level"]="26",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Aleswell Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2797",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Mine for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6397",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Kaalgrontiid's plan to fulfill the prophecy of the Dark Aeon and become a god continues as he sent his island, Dragonhold, into the sky. Now we need to find a way to reach the island.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6402",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="We reformed the Dragonguard and defeated Kaalgrontiid. I should see if there's anything else we need to take care of here in Southern Elsweyr.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3436",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found Lashgikh within the tunnels of Obsidian Scar. She claims she and her husband, Esmaeel, were kidnapped by the Oathbound, at the behest of an Orc named Osgrikh. She managed to escape, but needs help rescuing her husband.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5742",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="3",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I summoned one of the fabled witchmothers, who are rumored to appear only during the Witches Festival! Legends say these strange beings can be bargained with for power.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5546",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Raynor and Kireth Vanos were recently marooned on the Gold Coast. The captain they hired to sail them to Sentinel delivered them to Anvil instead, and now they lack the funds to finish their journey. They asked me to help them find work.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2869",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5797",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Reaper's March.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4684",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Apphia Matia asked me to let Brielus Colus of Cheydinhal know that she is bearing his child.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4558",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Darien mentioned that a small group of Lion Guard soldiers went to search for Angof in the north. I should head in that direction and attempt to find them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3082",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="To hold back Angof's undead army, the Lion Guard built a redoubt on a hill outside Cath Bedraud. As they struggle to find a way to breech Angof's defenses, they have to fend off hordes of Bloodthorn cultists and zombie thralls.",["poiIndex"]="10",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4443",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Dame Dabienne has expressed concerns about events unfolding at Alcaire Castle. She asked me to go there and see if I can help.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2552",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Fahara'jad of Alik'r has sent an army to Alcaire Castle. They claim to be on a diplomatic mission, but the Knights of the Flame believe otherwise. This situation could threaten the very fabric of the Daggerfall Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2566",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Dame Falhut was apparently behind the assassination attempts on Duchess Lakana. We must apprehend her quickly to ensure the duchess's safety.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2567",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Dame Falhut is dead, and the threat against Duchess Lakana is over, at least for the moment.",["poiIndex"]="17",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2576",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Sir Hughes murdered Duchess Lakana in Alcaire Castle. I promised Duke Nathaniel that I will track Sir Hughes down to answer for his crimes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="736",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Knights of the Flame are divided over whether to attack the redguard army at Alcaire Castle. Sir Croix and other knights would potentially destroy the Covenant. They need to be stopped. I've agreed to rally knights to Sir Edmund's cause.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="737",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Sir Edmund and the knights who have rallied to our cause are prepared to attack. We must retake Firebrand Keep and put an end to the plan that would threaten the Daggerfall Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="467",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="After murdering Duchess Lakana, Sir Hughes fled to Firebrand Keep. I've come to confront him and if necessary, bring him to justice for his crimes.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5786",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Cardea Gallus of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Alik'r Desert.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4863",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a Bosmer Adventurer named Gluineth locked in a cell in Troll's Toothpick. I've agreed to spring her from the cell and escort her out of the cave.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3598",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Reesa is grateful the dead have been put to rest. She wants to give of herself to restore the Starved Plain. She's proposed a sacrifice from herself and her students that will allow plants to grow again on the plain.",["poiIndex"]="3",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5041",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I met an Argonian named Onuja at Othrenis. He asked me to aid Davon's Watch in their battle against the Daggerfall Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4662",["level"]="28",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a set of robes in a bandit camp.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1678",["level"]="31",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Supernal Dreamers have attacked the Vanne Farm and captured the owner, Ingride Vanne, with the intention of subjecting her to some dark ritual.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1709",["level"]="31",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Supernal Dreamers also took Ingride's daughter, Rozenn Vanne, and they're apparently planning a similar ritual using her as the vessel for some daedric spirit. I promised Ingride I would stop them.",["poiIndex"]="16",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5827",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Alvur Baren of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Rivenspire.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3117",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Farm for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6052",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="According to Gascone, a murder of crows stole a mysterious key from his office in the Clockwork Basilicaâ€”the same key that Clavicus Vile and the mysterious shadow cultists seek. I must find this key before the enemy does.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5544",["level"]="17",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Captain Jimila has been suffering under the oppressive dock fees in Anvil. She asked for my help in stealing the dock master's private stash to pay off her debts.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3125",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Dragonclaw Mine for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5804",["level"]="1",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Vvardenfell promises new experiences and new adventures. I can't wait to see what the land of the Dark Elves has in store for me.",["poiIndex"]="33",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5759",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hermaeus Mora asked me to bring him unique relics from across Craglorn in exchange for knowledge of the Celestials. Perhaps he'll be interested in this strange writing.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5662",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6559",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Nelldena charged me with finding allies to assault the harrowstorm ritual sites springing up across the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6597",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="3",["backgroundText"]="A Reachman named Angair challenged me to complete a clan ritual called the Vateshran's Rites. He says it involves combat against creatures from Oblivion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6585",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A scout of the Ard's Stonehands encountered a new type of Dwarven automaton in a nearby cave that appeared to be dropping scrap metal. The Stonehands asked me to investigate. I need to destroy the construct and gather the scrap.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6610",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Rites Matron challenged me to complete the Vateshran's Rites within Vateshran Hollows. My success determines whether I earn the right to stay in the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="1591",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found an injured Spirit Warden in Pariah Abbey's fields. Falice Menoit said she was attacked by Midnight Union outlaws. She'll be fine, but she's worried about others who were injured in the attack.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1536",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Bandits attacked Pariah Abbey and set its crops on fire.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1529",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Abbot Durak took some Spirit Wardens up to the Cave of Dreams to find a way to deal with the largest fire in the fields. I should check up on them.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1541",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Bandits set fires in the fields to distract the Spirit Wardens. While the wardens were outside fighting the fires, the thieves stole a priceless relic: the Dream Shard.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1735",["level"]="32",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Though the Omen of Fear has been dealt with and Alcaire is free of its influence, Duke Nathaniel is concerned. He's asked me to go seek the counsel of a Spirit Warden named Muranâ€”to see if he can explain what happened.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="499",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="King Emeric believes Count Hosni has the Dream Shard stolen from Pariah Abbey. He wants me to ingratiate myself with the count in hopes of retrieving the shard.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4901",["level"]="40",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="A bloody conflict has erupted between the noble houses of Rivenspire and High King Emeric has asked me to go there on his authority and attempt to restore order.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4903",["level"]="47",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I need to locate Verandis Ravenwatch and find out if he can tell me more about Baron Montclair and where he might be hiding. He may also know more about what set Montclair on this path of destruction.",["poiIndex"]="13",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="465",["level"]="48",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="Captain Janeve, the shield of the Shornhelm Guard and Countess Tamrith's younger sister, has established a camp for refugees displaced by the vampiric menace.",["poiIndex"]="6",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="657",["level"]="49",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the last wishes of someone named Handre. He was going to use a gem he stole from the bandits to buy Fadeel's freedom.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6584",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A scout of the Ard's Stonehands spotted a strange new Dwarven automaton dropping odd beacons in a nearby cave. They want me to investigate and destroy the construct, as well as any beacons I find.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6572",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Animals in Gloomreach seem to have developed the ability to produce a strange fungal mold. The Reachfolk think magic might be at work. They want samples of the mold collected in order to study them further.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6571",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bralthahawn's needs someone to gather a strange kind of mushroom growing in Gloomreach that a few Reach clans are interested in. I volunteered my services.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6583",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="An outsider scholar reported the presence of an unknown Dwarven construct in a nearby cave that's producing new mechanical spiders.The Ard's Stonehands asked me to destroy it and test a Dwarven rod that supposedly renders constructs docile.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6556",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Ard's Stonehands are concerned about a witch matron of a rogue Reach clan attempting a dangerous ritual. I need to put a stop to this ritual and rescue the innocent Reachfolk that were abducted to carry it out",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5674",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4635",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a broken cart with a list of items that were supposed to be delivered to Lorene Menillet of Cropsford.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5764",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="5",["backgroundText"]="Safa al-Satakalaam, a priest of Satakal, is at odds with the Scaled Court. Three of her most powerful acolytes have deserted her to worship the Celestial Serpent. She wants me to punish these traitors and deny their power to the Scaled Court.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6557",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A liaison for the Wildblood clan, Bralthahawn, asked that I enter Briar Rock Ruins and retrieve talismans from Wildblood warriors who were taken prisoner by a rival clan, the Thornroot.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6561",["level"]="50",["type"]="5",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="The Rites Matron challenged me to complete the Vateshran's Rites within Vateshran Hollows. My success determines whether I earn the right to stay in the Reach.",["poiIndex"]="19",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6581",["level"]="50",["type"]="1",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A defector from a local Reach clan informed the Ard's Stonehands that his clan's witch matron is attempting a dangerous ritual. I agreed to investigate and put a stop to the ritual, as well as search for any of the witch matron's notes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6567",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A Reach clan called the Thornroot kidnapped members of a nearby clan, the Wildblood. Now the Thornroot intend to engage in a ritual that will turn their unwilling captives into briarhearts. I need to stop them from performing the ritual.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6606",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Wayward Guardians want to cleanse a sacred shrine atop the Lost Valley Redoubt from the taint of invaders and the Gray Host.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6603",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A scout reported several Reach exiles have been taken captive by strange blind creatures in the depths of Blackreach. The Wayward Guardians want me to rescue them.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6604",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Wayward Guardians fear that Gray Host forces still lurk in the halls of Nchuand-Zel beneath Markarth. They need them driven from those halls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6600",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Wayward Guardians need Dwarven scrap to augment their arms and armor. Ardanir asked me to search the ruins of Bthardamz for the precious metal.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6046",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The Shadow of Sotha Sil, having claimed the Skeleton Key from the Blackfeather Court, is making his way to the center of the Clockwork Cityâ€”The Cogitum Centralis. Proctor Luciana and I must find some way to follow him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5757",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Hermaeus Mora asked me to bring him unique relics from across Craglorn. In exchange for such offerings, he promised to grant me knowledge of the Celestials.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6605",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Wayward Guardians seek writings from Nighthollow Keep so their witches can learn more about the magic of the Nighthollow vampires.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6092",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found the abandoned journal of Dulza, an Orc merchant who somehow entered the Clockwork City during a fierce storm in Craglorn. Her greatest regret is that her clan in Fell's Run will never see their ancestral sword again.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3146",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2889",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Warden Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6365",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I crossed paths with a scoundrel named Jakarn. He invited me to join him on a job that could make us both rich. Unfortunately, some seedy Khajiit are intent on stopping him.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3087",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Aleswell for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6601",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Wayward Guardians need silver ore to coat their arms and armor in order to better fight against the Gray Host. Ardanir asked me to bring him some from the Dwarven ruins of Bthar-Zel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6602",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The shamans of the Wayward Guardians claim that certain Dwarven constructs contain gemstones imbued with powerful magic. Ardanir wants me to acquire some of these gemstones.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3314",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I encountered an injured Lion Guard knight named Sir Malik Nasir in Merovec's Folly. He wants to stop the Bloodthorn cultists from desecrating the dead Lion Guard soldiers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4979",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Herminius Sophus asked me to search the ruins for texts from other scholars who may have previously studied here.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="1687",["level"]="31",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bandits are disguising themselves as Knights of the Flame and robbing people on the road to Wrothgar. I promised Sir Graham I'd get the tabards back.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6342",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6341",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6344",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6345",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Dragons have not been seen in Tamriel for generations, and the Khajiit are unsure how best to fight against them. The ancient Nords recorded Dragon fighting techniques on scrolls they keep in their crypts. I need to find these scrolls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6329",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3482",["level"]="32",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Jarrod tells me his son, Taren, has gone missing somewhere in the oasis near Bergama.",["poiIndex"]="33",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2843",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Fort Ash for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="3286",["level"]="33",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A contingent of Shornhelm Guard soldiers was on patrol when it was attacked by House Montclair troops. The Guard survivors have taken refuge in an old tower on Hinault Farm, where they continue to be under siege by Montclair's forces.",["poiIndex"]="1",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2905",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Brindle Lumbermill for the Pact.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4965",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met Nicolene in the Dead Wolf Inn in Shornhelm. She and Captain Kaleen are here looking for one of King Fahara'jad's former spies, Naruk. Naruk has turned against the Daggerfall Covenant and is now inciting war, but Kaleen is missing.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5840",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The powerful Telvanni mage, Mistress Dratha, teeters on the brink of death. Now her replacement, Master Savarak, rules Vos with an iron fist. The situation seems dire.",["poiIndex"]="8",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4707",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I found a note meant for Marodeen, who apparently lives in Vlastarus. He might appreciate getting it.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4433",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Vyctoria Girien collects Ayleid items. She hasn't been able to search for any since the war started.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4421",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Bandits called The Thorns stole all the Cheydinhal rebels' valuables when war broke out.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4425",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Imperials have captured two of Vyctoria Girien's soldiers.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4924",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a somewhat drunk and totally bootless Breton named Parquier Gimbert outside of Northpoint. He said he lost a valuable mace while hunting for mudcrabs along the shore. He thinks that maybe a Hagraven was involved. Also, he has no shoes.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4876",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Arkas at the Southern Morrowind gate.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4694",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="The dead have risen at Tu'whacca's Throne. Throne Keeper Farvard insists we consult the king before taking any action. I have agreed to take word back to the palace in Sentinel.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6564",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="3",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The Undaunted seek adventurers willing to work for a chance at a cut of the choicest plunder.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4942",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I met a man named Beryn in the woods, recovering from an epic drinking bout at his camp. He's worried because he fears his friend Garth has wandered into a nearby spider cave on a dare.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4510",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="To get off Stros M'Kai, I need passage on a ship. Neramo knows a Redguard captain who will help us if we first help her with a heist.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5013",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="10",["backgroundText"]="I've found a scroll bearing marks from the Aldmeri Dominion. It details a series of unsolved murders in Stormhold.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="3982",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Ganthis, an agent of the Vicecanons, asked me to join the expedition to Bogmother. They'll be searching for Argonian relics.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="4696",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Fabanil has asked that I travel to Vlastarus and inform his brother Angiente that his wife is dead.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4938",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Fallen Grotto is under the control of Brinarch and his Reachmen.",["poiIndex"]="5",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="2811",["level"]="50",["type"]="7",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Farm for the Covenant.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6134",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="3",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The New Life Festival is celebrated across Tamriel and all are welcome to join in. I should find out more about this celebration.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5852",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of Haven's New Life Festival in Grahtwood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5838",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of a Skywatch New Life Festival in Auridon.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5834",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of Rawl'kha's New Life Festival in Reaper's March.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5855",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of Hissmir's New Life Festival in Shadowfen.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5837",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of an Ebonheart New Life Festival in Stonefalls.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5811",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald, spoke of a Lower Yorgrim New Life Festival in Eastmarch.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5839",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of Bergama's New Life Festival in Alik'r Desert.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5845",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of Alcaire Castle's New Life Festival in Stormhaven.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5856",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Breda, a New Life Herald in Eastmarch, spoke of the New Life Festival in Betnikh.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6592",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a contract to craft supplies using blacksmithing for civilians displaced by the Three Banners War.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6594",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a contract to craft supplies using woodworking for civilians displaced by the Three Banners War.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6588",["level"]="50",["type"]="12",["repeatType"]="2",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="Petronius Galenus told me about the Old Life tradition in which people write messages to those that have passed on and burn them at special shrines.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="6593",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a contract to craft supplies using the clothier craft for civilians displaced by the Three Banners War.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6595",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted a contract to craft supplies using provisioning for civilians displaced by the Three Banners War.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="6485",["level"]="50",["type"]="4",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="4998",["level"]="20",["type"]="2",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="1",["backgroundText"]="Cadwell has approached me and offered me a chance to see how events might have played out if I'd washed up on the shores of a different alliance after escaping Coldharbour.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5835",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="A naked Nord stands frozen in place in the wilds of Vvardenfell. He claims a Dark Elf witch cast a spell on him, and only she can remove it. He asked me to find her and get her to set him free.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5914",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="My ambitious companion, Sun-in-Shadow, succeeded in replacing Magister Gothren's Mouth, Ralasa Delvi. But even success carries risk in Sadrith Mora. Rumor has it that Magister Gothren leaves no slight unpunished.",["poiIndex"]="11",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5541",["level"]="50",["type"]="0",["repeatType"]="0",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="The pirate captain Crafty Lerisa has come to Kvatch to convince her sister, Josseline, to abandon the Society of the Dragon, a cult headed by the Grand Chanter of the Akatosh Cathedral for believers not ready to commit to the priesthood.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="1"},
{["internalId"]="5671",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
{["internalId"]="5620",["level"]="50",["type"]="3",["repeatType"]="1",["displayType"]="0",["backgroundText"]="I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing, so I may execute the target at my discretion.",["poiIndex"]="294967291",["isShareable"]="0"},
